_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Items worn to cover the body.","main_translations_es":["vestimenta","indumentaria","prendas"],"collocations":["change of clothes","clothes line","clothes rack","clothes store"],"example_sentence":"I bought new clothes for the trip.","example_es":"Compré ropa nueva para el viaje.","example_en":"I bought new clothes for the trip.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Zapatos","english_text":"Shoes","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Footwear that covers and protects the feet, typically consisting of a sole and a heel.","main_translations_es":["Zapatos","Calzado"],"collocations":["shoes off","shoes on","shoes for sale"],"example_sentence":"I bought new shoes for the wedding.","example_es":"Me compré unos zapatos nuevos para la boda.","example_en":"I bought new shoes for the wedding.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Calcetines","english_text":"Socks","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A piece of clothing worn on the feet, usually covering the ankle and sometimes extending up the leg.","main_translations_es":["calcetines","medias","calcetas"],"collocations":["pair of socks","sock drawer","warm socks","sock hop"],"example_sentence":"My socks are wet after the rain.","example_es":"Mis calcetines están mojados después de la lluvia.","example_en":"My socks are wet after the rain.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Lavadora","english_text":"Washing machine","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A household appliance used to wash laundry.","main_translations_es":["lavadora","máquina de lavar ropa","máquina de lavado"],"collocations":["run the washing machine","load the washing machine","wash clothes in the washing machine","washing machine cycle"],"example_sentence":"I bought a new washing machine because the old one broke.","example_es":"Compré una lavadora nueva porque la anterior se rompió.","example_en":"I bought a new washing machine because the old one broke.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Toalla","english_text":"Towel","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A piece of absorbent fabric used for drying or wiping something.","main_translations_es":["toalla","pañuelo","paño"],"collocations":["hand towel","bath towel","towel rack"],"example_sentence":"I dried my hands with a towel.","example_es":"Me sequé las manos con una toalla.","example_en":"I dried my hands with a towel.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Jabón","english_text":"Soap","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A cleansing substance, usually a solid or liquid, used for washing and removing dirt and oils.","main_translations_es":["jabón","sabonete","jaboncillo"],"collocations":["soap opera","hand soap","soap suds","soap bar"],"example_sentence":"I bought soap to wash my hands.","example_es":"Compré jabón para lavar mis manos.","example_en":"I bought soap to wash my hands.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Champú","english_text":"Shampoo","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A liquid soap used for cleaning hair.","main_translations_es":["champú","shampoo","gel para el cabello"],"collocations":["shampoo and conditioner","anti-dandruff shampoo","wash your hair with shampoo"],"example_sentence":"I bought a shampoo that makes the hair very soft.","example_es":"Compré un champú que deja el cabello muy suave.","example_en":"I bought a shampoo that makes the hair very soft.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cepillo","english_text":"Brush","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A tool with bristles used for cleaning, grooming, or applying substances.","main_translations_es":["cepillo","cepillado","cepilladora"],"collocations":["brush teeth","brush hair","paint brush","brush up"],"example_sentence":"I need a brush to comb my hair.","example_es":"Necesito un cepillo para peinar mi cabello.","example_en":