lt?","example_es":"Perdón, ¿puedes pasarme la sal?","example_en":"Excuse me, can you pass me the salt?","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"De nada","english_text":"You are welcome","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite response indicating that the speaker is happy to have helped.","main_translations_es":["No hay de qué","Con gusto","A la orden"],"collocations":["You’re welcome!","No problem","Anytime","My pleasure"],"example_sentence":"You''re welcome, it was a pleasure to help you.","example_es":"De nada, fue un placer ayudarle.","example_en":"You''re welcome, it was a pleasure to help you.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Nos vemos luego","english_text":"See you later","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A casual way to say goodbye, indicating that you will meet again later.","main_translations_es":["Hasta luego","Nos vemos después","Hasta pronto"],"collocations":["See you later, alligator","See you later, gator","See you later, buddy"],"example_sentence":"See you later at the cafe.","example_es":"Nos vemos luego en el café.","example_en":"See you later at the cafe.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Buenas noches","english_text":"Good night","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite phrase used to wish someone a pleasant night, typically said when parting in the evening.","main_translations_es":["Buenas noches","Que tengas una buena noche","Que descanses"],"collocations":["Good night, sweet dreams","Good night, see you tomorrow","Good night, everyone","Good night, sleep tight"],"example_sentence":"Good night, see you tomorrow.","example_es":"Buenas noches, nos vemos mañana.","example_en":"Good night, see you tomorrow.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Tengo hambre","english_text":"I am hungry","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that the speaker feels the need to 