ón.","example_en":"Please turn off the light when you leave the room.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Lava la ropa","english_text":"Wash the clothes","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To clean the clothing by using water and detergent.","main_translations_es":["Lava la ropa","Lava la ropa sucia","Haz la colada"],"collocations":["wash the clothes thoroughly","wash the clothes in cold water","wash the clothes before drying","wash the clothes regularly"],"example_sentence":"Wash the clothes before it starts to rain.","example_es":"Lava la ropa antes de que empiece a llover.","example_en":"Wash the clothes before it starts to rain.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Saca la basura","english_text":"Take out the trash","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To remove the garbage from a location and place it in a waste container or outside for collection.","main_translations_es":["Saca la basura","Lleva la basura al contenedor"],"collocations":["take out the trash","take out the trash before dinner","take out the trash daily"],"example_sentence":"Take out the trash before the guests arrive.","example_es":"Saca la basura antes de que lleguen los invitados.","example_en":"Take out the trash before the guests arrive.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Haz la compra","english_text":"Do the shopping","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To purchase groceries or other needed items.","main_translations_es":["Haz la compra","Ir de compras","Hacer la compra"],"collocations":["do the shopping","do the grocery shopping","do the weekly shopping","do some shopping"],"example_sentence":"Tomorrow, do the shopping for the food we need.","example_es":"Mañana haz la compra de los alimentos que necesitamos.","example_en":"Tomorrow, do the shopping for the food we need.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Voy al banco","english_text":"I am going to the bank","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that the speaker is traveling to the bank.","main_translations_es":["Voy al banco","Me dirijo al banco","Voy a ir al banco"],"collocations":["I''m going to the bank tomorrow","I''m going to the bank later today","I''m going to the bank to deposit some money","I''m going to the bank for a loan"],"example_sentence":"I''m going to the bank right now.","example_es":"Voy al banco ahora mismo.","example_en":"I''m going to the bank right now.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Voy a la farmacia","english_text":"I am going to the pharmacy","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that the speaker is heading to the pharmacy.","main_translations_es":["Me dirijo a la farmacia","Voy a la farmacia","Voy a la botica"],"collocations":["going to the pharmacy","head to the pharmacy","stop by the pharmacy","run to the pharmacy"],"example_sentence":"I am going to the pharmacy to buy medicine.","example_es":"Voy a la farmacia para comprar medicina.","example_en":"I am going to the pharmacy to buy medicine.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Voy al gimnasio","english_text":"I am going to the gym","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that the speaker is heading to the gym.","main_translations_es":["Voy al gimnasio","Me dirijo al gimnasio","Me voy al gimnasio"],"collocations":["go to the gym","hit the gym","work out at the gym","exercise at the gym"],"example_sentence":"I go to the gym every day to stay fit.","example_es":"Voy al gimnasio todos los días para mantenerme en forma.","example_en":"I go to the gym every day to stay fit.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Toma el autobús","english_text":"Take the bus","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To travel by riding a bus.","main_translations_es":["Coge el autobús","Sube al autobús","Toma el bus