ute","bus schedule","bus driver"],"example_sentence":"The bus arrives at eight.","example_es":"El autobús llega a las ocho.","example_en":"The bus arrives at eight.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Parada de autobús","english_text":"Bus stop","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A designated place where buses pick up and drop off passengers.","main_translations_es":["Parada de bus","Estación de autobuses","Parada de transporte público"],"collocations":["bus stop sign","bus stop light","bus stop shelter","bus stop announcement"],"example_sentence":"I''m going to the bus stop to catch the bus.","example_es":"Voy a la parada de autobús para coger el bus.","example_en":"I''m going to the bus stop to catch the bus.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Taxi","english_text":"Taxi","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A vehicle for hire that transports passengers for a fare.","main_translations_es":["taxi","táxi","cabina de taxi"],"collocations":["take a taxi","call a taxi","taxi fare","taxi driver"],"example_sentence":"I need a taxi to get to the airport.","example_es":"Necesito un taxi para ir al aeropuerto.","example_en":"I need a taxi to get to the airport.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Metro","english_text":"Subway","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"An underground railway system used for urban transit.","main_translations_es":["metro","subterráneo","metro de la ciudad"],"collocations":["take the subway","subway station","subway line","subway map"],"example_sentence":"I take the subway every morning to get to work.","example_es":"Voy al metro cada mañana para ir al trabajo.","example_en":"I take the subway every morning to get to work.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Ida y vuelta","english_text":"Round trip","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A journey that starts and ends at the same place.","main_translations_es":["ida y vuelta","ida y regreso","ida y retorno"],"collocations":["round-trip ticket","round-trip flight","round-trip journey","round-trip fare"],"example_sentence":"I bought a round trip ticket for my trip to Madrid.","example_es":"Compré un billete de ida y vuelta para mi viaje a Madrid.","example_en":"I bought a round trip ticket for my trip to Madrid.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Solo ida","english_text":"One-way ticket","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A ticket that allows travel in only one direction, not a return.","main_translations_es":["Solo de ida","Solo ida","Solo ida de viaje"],"collocations":["buy a one-way ticket","one-way ticket to","one-way ticket for","one-way ticket price"],"example_sentence":"The price of a one-way ticket is cheaper than that of a round-trip ticket.","example_es":"El precio del solo ida es más barato que el del ida y vuelta.","example_en":"The price of a one-way ticket is cheaper than that of a round-trip ticket.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Reserva","english_text":"Reservation","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the act of reserving something in advance, or a booking made for a future use","main_translations_es":["Reserva","Reservación"],"collocations":["make a reservation","hold a reservation","reservation fee","reservation system"],"example_sentence":"I made a reservation for two people.","example_es":"He hecho una reserva para dos personas.","example_en":"I made a reservation for two people.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Mapa","english_text":"Map","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A diagram that represents an area, showing features such as roads, borders, or terrain.","main_translations_es":["Mapa","Plano"],"collocations":["world map","map out","map of","map the route"],"example_sentence":"The treasure map is hidden under the table.","example_es":"El mapa del tesoro está escondido bajo la mesa.","example_en":"The treasure map is hidden under the table.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"A la izquierda","english_text":"On the left","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Indicates a location to the left side.","main_translations_es":["Al lado izquierdo","En el lado izquierdo","A la izquierda de"],"collocations":["on the left side","on the left-hand side","on the left of","on the left side of the room"],"example_sentence":"On the left of the store, you''ll find the park.","example_es":"A la izquierda de la tienda, encontrarás el parque.","example_en":"On the left of the store, you''ll find the park.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"A la derecha","english_text":"On the right","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Located or positioned to the right side.","main_translations_es":["a la derecha de","en la derecha","a la derecha de la calle"],"collocations":["on the right side","on the right hand side","on the right side of the road","on the right side of the page"],"example_sentence":"Keep going on the right until you reach the park.","example_es":"Sigue a la derecha hasta el parque.","example_en":"Keep going on the right until you reach the park.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Todo recto","english_text":"Straight ahead","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Straight ahead means directly forward, in a straight line.","main_translations_es":["Todo recto"],"collocations":["straight ahead of the road","straight ahead of the line","straight ahead of the path"],"example_sentence":"Keep going straight ahead until the intersection.","example_es":"Sigue todo recto hasta el cruce.","example_en":"Keep going straight ahead until the intersection.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Esquina","english_text":"Corner","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"a point where two lines or surfaces meet, forming an angle.","main_translations_es":["Rincón","Ángulo","Borde"],"collocations":["corner store","corner office","corner of the room","corner of the eye"],"example_sentence":"The cat hid in the corner of the hallway.","example_es":"El gato se escondió en la esquina del pasillo.","example_en":"The cat hid in the corner of the hallway.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cerca","english_text":"Near","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"At or within a short distance.","main_translations_es":["Alrededor","Próximo","Junto a"],"collocations":["near the border","near the station","near the end","near the beginning"],"example_sentence":"The park is near my house.","example_es":"El parque está cerca de mi casa.","example_en":"The park is near my house.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Lejos","english_text":"Far","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"at a great distance from a particular point or place.","main_translations_es":["Distante","A distancia","Lejano"],"collocations":["far away","far from","far enough","far too"],"example_sentence":"The lighthouse is far from the coast.","example_es":"El faro está lejos de la costa.","example_en":"The lighthouse is far from the coast.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cruce","english_text":"Crossing","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A place where one can cross from one side to another.","main_translations_es":["intersección","cruce de caminos","cruce de calles"],"collocations":["crossing guard","crossing the street","crossing the bridge","crossing the border"],"example_sentence":"The crossing of the street is signaled with flashing lights.","example_es":"El cruce de la calle está señalizado con luces intermitentes.","example_en":"The crossing of the street is signaled with flashing lights.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Semáforo","english_text":"Traffic light","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A device that controls traffic by displaying red, yellow, and green lights.","main_translations_es":["señal de tráfico","señal luminosa","señal de luz"],"collocations":["traffic light signal","traffic light system","traffic light cycle","traffic light colors"],"example_sentence":"The traffic light turned red and the drivers stopped.","example_es":"El semáforo se puso rojo y los conductores se detuvieron.","example_en":"The traffic light turned red and the drivers stopped.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Calle","english_text":"Street","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A public road in a city or town, typically with buildings on one or both sides.","main_translations_es":["avenida","callejón","paseo"],"collocations":["on the street","street address","street name","street corner"],"example_sentence":"The street is full of people.","example_es":"La calle está llena de gente.","example_en":"The street is full of people.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Avenida","english_text":"Avenue","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A wide street, especially one that is lined with trees or buildings.","main_translations_es":["Calle","Vía","Paseo"],"collocations":["Avenue of the Arts","Avenue of the Americas","Broadway Avenue"],"example_sentence":"The main avenue is full of shops.","example_es":"La Avenida principal está llena de tiendas.","example_en":"The main avenue is full of shops.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Plaza","english_text":"Square","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A public open space surrounded by buildings, often used for gathering or commerce.","main_translations_es":["plaza","plazuela","parque"],"collocations":["public square","town square","city square","square footage"],"example_sentence":"The square of the town is full of people.","example_es":"La plaza del pueblo está llena de gente.","example_en":"The square of the town is full of people.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Giro","english_text":"Turn","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"a movement or rotation around an axis","main_translations_es":["Vuelta","Rotación","Cambio"],"collocations":["turn on","turn off","turn around","turn over"],"example_sentence":"I turn the steering wheel to change lanes.","example_es":"Giro el volante para cambiar de carril.","example_en":"I turn the steering wheel to change lanes.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Centro","english_text":"Downtown","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the central business district of a city, typically characterized by high-rise buildings and commercial activity.","main_translations_es":["centro","centro de la ciudad","centro urbano"],"collocations":["downtown area","downtown core","downtown business district","downtown shopping"],"example_sentence":"I like walking around downtown.","example_es":"Me gusta caminar por el centro de la ciudad.","example_en":"I like walking around downtown.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Dirección","english_text":"Address","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the details of a place where someone lives or works.","main_translations_es":["Ubicación","Localización","Sitio"],"collocations":["home address","email address","physical address","address a letter"],"example_sentence":"What is your address?","example_es":"¿Cuál es tu dirección?","example_en":"What is your address?","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Hotel","english_text":"Hotel","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"a building where people pay to stay for a short time","main_translations_es":["hotel","albergue","posada"],"collocations":["hotel room","hotel staff","hotel reservation","hotel lobby"],"example_sentence":"The hotel is near the city center.","example_es":"El hotel está cerca del centro.","example_en":"The hotel is near the city center.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Recepción","english_text":"Reception","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the act of receiving guests or visitors, especially at an entrance","main_translations_es":["Bienvenida","Entrada","Recepción"],"collocations":["reception desk","reception area","reception hall","reception party"],"example_sentence":"The hotel''s reception is open 24 hours a day.","example_es":"La recepción del hotel está abierta las 24 horas.","example_en":"The hotel''s reception is open 24 hours a day.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Habitación","english_text":"Room","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A separate area within a building used for a particular purpose.","main_translations_es":["cuarto","dormitorio","habitación"],"collocations":["living room","bedroom","room for improvement","room to spare"],"example_sentence":"The room is clean and tidy.","example_es":"La habitación está limpia y ordenada.","example_en":"The room is clean and tidy.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Llave","english_text":"Key","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A small metal instrument used to open locks or secure items.","main_translations_es":["clave","código"],"collocations":["key point","key player","key issue","key to success"],"example_sentence":"The key to the door is in the drawer.","example_es":"La llave de la puerta está en el cajón.","example_en":"The key to the door is in the drawer.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Toalla","english_text":"Towel","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A piece of absorbent cloth or paper used for drying or wiping.","main_translations_es":["toalla","paño","pañuelo"],"collocations":["hand towel","bath towel","towel rack","towel dry"],"example_sentence":"I need a clean towel.","example_es":"Necesito una toalla limpia.","example_en":"I need a clean towel.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Baño","english_text":"Bathroom","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A room in a house or apartment equipped for washing and personal hygiene.","main_translations_es":["Baño","Cuarto de baño","Sanitario"],"collocations":["washroom","bathroom facilities","bathroom break","bathroom sign"],"example_sentence":"I''m going to the bathroom before leaving.","example_es":"Voy al baño antes de salir.","example_en":"I''m going to the bathroom before leaving.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cama doble","english_text":"Double bed","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A bed that is larger than a single bed, typically accommodating two people.","main_translations_es":["Cama matrimonial","Cama doble estándar","Cama doble grande"],"collocations":["double bed room","double bed size","double bed mattress","double bed furniture"],"example_sentence":"The room has a double bed so guests feel comfortable.","example_es":"La habitación tiene una cama doble para que los huéspedes se sientan cómodos.","example_en":"The room has a double bed so guests feel comfortable.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Una noche","english_text":"One night","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A single night, a period of 24 hours.","main_translations_es":["una noche"],"collocations":["one night stand","one night only","one night in","one night out"],"example_sentence":"One night, the cat hid under the bed.","example_es":"Una noche, el gato se escondió bajo la cama.","example_en":"One night, the cat hid under the bed.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Registrarse","english_text":"Check in","section_name":"Travel Phrases","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to register upon arrival, typically at a hotel or event","main_translations_es":["Inscribirse","Matricularse","Registrarse en línea"],"collocations":["check 