ics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A coffee beverage made with espresso and steamed milk.","main_translations_es":["café con leche","café con leche caliente","café con leche tibio"],"collocations":["order a latte","latte art","vanilla latte","cold latte"],"example_sentence":"I would like a latte, please.","example_es":"Quiero un café con leche, por favor.","example_en":"I would like a latte, please.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Té helado","english_text":"Iced tea","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A cold beverage made by chilling tea, often served with ice.","main_translations_es":["té frío","té con hielo","té refrescante"],"collocations":["a glass of iced tea","iced tea with lemon","iced tea on a hot day"],"example_sentence":"I like drinking iced tea on hot days.","example_es":"Me gusta tomar té helado en los días calurosos.","example_en":"I like drinking iced tea on hot days.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Croissant","english_text":"Croissant","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A buttery, flaky, crescent-shaped pastry commonly eaten for breakfast.","main_translations_es":["croissant","cruasán","cruasan"],"collocations":["have a croissant for breakfast","freshly baked croissant","buttery croissant","croissant sandwich"],"example_sentence":"I love eating a freshly baked croissant in the morning.","example_es":"Me encanta comer un croissant recién horneado en la mañana.","example_en":"I love eating a freshly baked croissant in the morning.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Magdalena","english_text":"Muffin","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A small, sweet, individual cake or quick bread, typically round and baked in a cup-shaped mold.","main_translations_es":["magdalena","bizcocho","pastelito"],"collocations":["blueberry muffin","chocolate muffin","English muffin","muffin top"],"example_sentence":"I ate a muffin for breakfast.","example_es":"Me comí una magdalena en el desayuno.","example_en":"I ate a muffin for breakfast.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Galleta","english_text":"Cookie","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A sweet baked snack, typically small, flat, and either crisp or soft.","main_translations_es":["galleta","biscocho","galleta dulce"],"collocations":["cookie jar","chocolate chip cookie","fortune cookie","cookie cutter"],"example_sentence":"I ate a chocolate cookie after dinner.","example_es":"Me comí una galleta de chocolate después de la cena.","example_en":"I ate a chocolate cookie after dinner.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Tarta","english_text":"Cake","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A sweet baked dessert typically made from flour, sugar, and other ingredients.","main_translations_es":["Pastel","Bizcocho","Torta"],"collocations":["piece of cake","have your cake and eat it too","icing on the cake","cakewalk"],"example_sentence":"I bought a chocolate cake for my sister''s birthday.","example_es":"Compré una tarta de chocolate para el cumpleaños de mi hermana.","example_en":"I bought a chocolate cake for my sister''s birthday.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Bocadillo","english_text":"Sandwich","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A food item consisting of two slices of bread with a filling such as meat, cheese, or vegetables placed between them.","main_translations_es":["sándwich","emparedado","bocata"],"collocations":["sandwich shop","sandwich maker","sandwich filling","sandwich bread"],"example_sentence":"I ate a ham and cheese sandwich in the park.","example_es":"Me comí un bocadillo de jamón y queso en el parque.","example_en":"I ate a ham and cheese sandwich in the park.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Tostada","english_text":"Toast","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A slice of bread that has been browned by heat.","main_translations_es":["Pan tostado","Tostada de pan","Tostada integral"],"collocations":["make toast","buttered toast","toast and jam","toast the bread"],"example_sentence":"I like to eat toast with butter and jam.","example_es":"Me gusta comer tostada con mantequilla y mermelada.","example_en":"I like to eat toast with butter and jam.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Ensalada","english_text":"Salad","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A dish made of mixed raw or cooked vegetables, often served with a dressing.","main_translations_es":["ensalada mixta","ensalada verde","ensalada fresca"],"collocations":["Caesar salad","garden salad","fruit salad","salad dressing"],"example_sentence":"I like to eat salad with chicken.","example_es":"Me gusta comer ensalada con pollo.","example_en":"I like to eat salad with chicken.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sopa","english_text":"Soup","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A liquid dish made by boiling ingredients such as meat, vegetables, or legumes in water or stock.","main_translations_es":["caldo","consomé","sopa"],"collocations":["chicken noodle soup","soup of the day","soup kitchen"],"example_sentence":"I like hot soup in winter.","example_es":"Me gusta la sopa caliente en invierno.","example_en":"I like hot soup in winter.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Yogur","english_text":"Yogurt","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A creamy, fermented dairy product made from milk, commonly eaten as a snack or used in cooking.","main_translations_es":["yogur","yogur natural","yogur griego"],"collocations":["Greek yogurt","yogurt parfait","low-fat yogurt","yogurt drink"],"example_sentence":"I like to eat yogurt with fruit for breakfast.","example_es":"Me gusta comer yogur con frutas en el desayuno.","example_en":"I like to eat yogurt with fruit for breakfast.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Queso","english_text":"Cheese","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A dairy product made from curdled milk, commonly eaten as food.","main_translations_es":["queso","queso curado","queso fresco"],"collocations":["cheese plate","cheese sandwich","cheese sauce","cheese cake"],"example_sentence":"I like to eat cheese with crackers.","example_es":"Me gusta comer queso con galletas.","example_en":"I like to eat cheese with crackers.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Mantequilla","english_text":"Butter","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A pale yellow dairy product made by churning cream, used as a spread or in cooking.","main_translations_es":["Mantequilla","Manteca de leche"],"collocations":["spread butter","butter up","melt butter","butter the toast"],"example_sentence":"I like to spread butter on the bread.","example_es":"Me gusta untar mantequilla en el pan.","example_en":"I like to spread butter on the bread.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Mermelada","english_text":"Jam","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A sweet spread made from fruit and sugar, typically used on bread or toast.","main_translations_es":["Conserva de frutas","Dulce de fruta"],"collocations":["traffic jam","jam session","jam‑packed"],"example_sentence":"I like spreading jam on toast every morning.","example_es":"Me gusta untar mermelada en el pan tostado cada mañana.","example_en":"I like spreading jam on toast every morning.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Azúcar","english_text":"Sugar","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A sweet, crystalline substance used to sweeten foods and drinks, derived from sugarcane, sugar beet, or other plants.","main_translations_es":["azúcar","endulzante","dulce"],"collocations":["sugar rush","add sugar","sugar coating",