o pedir una ración de paella para cenar.","example_en":"I want to order one portion of paella for dinner.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Medio","english_text":"Half","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"One of two equal parts of a whole.","main_translations_es":["Mitad","Parcial","Semi"],"collocations":["half the time","half a dozen","half way","half past"],"example_sentence":"I ate half a sandwich.","example_es":"Comí medio sándwich.","example_en":"I ate half a sandwich.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Entero","english_text":"Whole","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Complete; not divided or lacking any part.","main_translations_es":["completo","total","integral"],"collocations":["the whole story","the whole world","the whole truth","the whole shebang"],"example_sentence":"I ate a whole apple.","example_es":"Comí una manzana entera.","example_en":"I ate a whole apple.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"¿Algo más?","english_text":"Anything else?","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A polite way of asking if there is any additional request or information.","main_translations_es":["¿Algo más?","¿Hay algo más?","¿Algo más que necesites?"],"collocations":["Anything else?","Anything else you need?","Anything else I can do?","Anything else you want to add?"],"example_sentence":"Anything else?","example_es":"¿Algo más?","example_en":"Anything else?","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Eso es todo","english_text":"That is all","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means that there is nothing more; that is everything.","main_translations_es":["Eso es todo"],"collocations":["That''s all for now","That''s all she wrote","That''s all folks","That''s all there is"],"example_sentence":"That is all, thank you for your attention.","example_es":"Eso es todo, gracias por su atención.","