er","cash register receipt","cash register tape"],"example_sentence":"The cash register ran out of paper.","example_es":"La caja registradora se quedó sin papel.","example_en":"The cash register ran out of paper.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Pago","english_text":"Payment","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A sum of money given in exchange for goods, services, or to settle a debt.","main_translations_es":["Abono","Desembolso","Cancelación"],"collocations":["make a payment","payment method","payment terms","payment deadline"],"example_sentence":"The payment will be made tomorrow.","example_es":"El pago se realizará mañana.","example_en":"The payment will be made tomorrow.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Tarjeta","english_text":"Card","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A small piece of paper or plastic used for identification, payment, or playing games.","main_translations_es":["cédula","credencial","carné"],"collocations":["credit card","gift card","business card","card game"],"example_sentence":"I need my credit card to pay the bill.","example_es":"Necesito mi tarjeta de crédito para pagar la cuenta.","example_en":"I need my credit card to pay the bill.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Efectivo","english_text":"Cash","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Money in the form of coins and banknotes that is readily available for transactions.","main_translations_es":["Dinero en efectivo","Dinero","Plata"],"collocations":["cash flow","cash register","cash on hand","cash payment"],"example_sentence":"I prefer to pay in cash.","example_es":"Prefiero pagar en efectivo.","example_en":"I prefer to pay in cash.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cambio","english_text":"Change","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the act or result of making something different, a transformation or alteration.","main_translations_es":["alteración","modificación","variación"],"collocations":["make a change","change of pace","change your mind","change the subject"],"example_sentence":"The change in weather affects me.","example_es":"El cambio de clima me afecta.","example_en":"The change in weather affects me.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Propina","english_text":"Tip","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A small amount of money given to someone as a gratuity for their service.","main_translations_es":["propina","corte","gratificación"],"collocations":["leave a tip","tip the waiter","tip jar","tip amount"],"example_sentence":"I left a good tip for the waiter.","example_es":"Dejé una buena propina al camarero.","example_en":"I left a good tip for the waiter.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Recibo","english_text":"Receipt","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A written acknowledgment that something, typically a payment, has been received.","main_translations_es":["Comprobante","Factura","Ticket"],"collocations":["receipt of payment","receipt number","receipt for"],"example_sentence":"I kept the receipt of the purchase so I could return the item.","example_es":"Guardé el recibo de la compra para poder devolver el artículo.","example_en":"I kept the receipt of the purchase so I could return the item.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cuenta separada","english_text":"Separate bill","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A bill that is issued separately from other charges.","main_translations_es":["Factura separada","Cuenta individual","Dividir la cuenta"],"collocations":["ask for a separate bill","receive a separate bill","separate bill for each person"],"example_sentence":"Could you bring me the separate bill, please?","example_es":"¿Podrías traerme la cuenta separada, por favor?","example_en":"Could you bring me the separate bill, please?","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"¿Puedo pagar ahora?","english_text":"Can I pay now?","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"Asking if it is possible to make a payment now.","main_translations_es":["¿Puedo pagar ya?","¿Me dejo pagar ahora?","¿Es posible pagar ahora?"],"collocations":["Can I pay now or later?","Can I pay now with a credit card?","Can I pay now and get a receipt?"],"example_sentence":"Can I pay now?","example_es":"¿Puedo pagar ahora?","example_en":"Can I pay now?","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"¿Aceptan tarjeta?","english_text":"Do you take cards?","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A polite way to ask if a business accepts credit or debit cards.","main_translations_es":["¿Aceptan tarjetas?","¿Se puede pagar con tarjeta?","¿Pagan con tarjeta?"],"collocations":["Do you take cards?","We take cards.","Do you accept credit cards?","We accept all major cards."],"example_sentence":"Do you take cards?","example_es":"¿Aceptan tarjeta?","example_en":"Do you take cards?","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Falta algo","english_text":"Something is missing","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that an item or element is absent.","main_translations_es":["Algo falta","Se echa de menos algo","Hay algo que falta"],"collocations":["something is missing from","something is missing here","something is missing altogether","something is missing in the report"],"example_sentence":"Something is missing from the song; it doesn''t sound complete.","example_es":"Falta algo en la canción; no suena completa.","example_en":"Something is missing from the song; it doesn''t sound complete.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sin cebolla","english_text":"No onion","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that there is no onion.","main_translations_es":["Sin cebolla","Sin cebollas","Sin cebolla añadida"],"collocations":["no onion pizza","no onion, please","no onion in the salad"],"example_sentence":"I would like the pizza without onion, please.","example_es":"Quisiera la pizza sin cebolla, por favor.","example_en":"I would like the pizza without onion, please.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sin leche","english_text":"No milk","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"A statement indicating that there is no milk.","main_translations_es":["Sin leche","No hay leche","Sin leche disponible"],"collocations":["No milk, please","I want coffee, no milk","No milk in my tea"],"example_sentence":"I want coffee with no milk.","example_es":"Quiero café sin leche.","example_en":"I want coffee with no milk.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Más agua","english_text":"More water","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"An increased amount of water.","main_translations_es":["Más agua","Más líquido","Más agua, por favor"],"collocations":["drink more water","add more water","need more water","more water, please"],"example_sentence":"I would like more water, please.","example_es":"Quiero más agua, por favor.","example_en":"I would like more water, please.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Otra servilleta","english_text":"Another napkin","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"A second napkin, used as a replacement or additional one.","main_translations_es":["Otra servilleta","Una servilleta más","Otra toalla de mesa"],"collocations":["hand me another napkin","need another napkin","grab another napkin","spill the sauce, get another napkin"],"example_sentence":"Can you pass me another napkin, please?","example_es":"¿Puedes pasarme otra servilleta, por favor?","example_en":"Can you pass me another napkin, please?","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"La mesa está sucia","english_text":"The table is dirty","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that the table is not clean.","main_translations_es":["La mesa está mugrienta","La mesa está sucia","La mesa está ensuciada"],"collocations":["dirty table","clean the table","wipe the table","clear the table"],"example_sentence":"The table is dirty.","example_es":"La mesa está sucia.","example_en":"The table is dirty.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Está delicioso","english_text":"It is delicious","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that something tastes very good.","main_translations_es":["Qué rico","Está sabroso","Se ve delicioso"],"collocations":["This dish is delicious","That was delicious","It tastes delicious","The food is delicious"],"example_sentence":"The cake is delicious.","example_es":"El pastel está delicioso.","example_en":"The cake is delicious.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Está muy caliente","english_text":"It is very hot","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that the temperature is high.","main_translations_es":["Hace mucho calor","Está muy caluroso","Hace un calor tremendo"],"collocations":["It''s very hot today","It''s very hot outside","It''s very hot in here","It''s very hot during summer"],"example_sentence":"The coffee is very hot.","example_es":"El café está muy caliente.","example_en":"The coffee is very hot.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Buen provecho","english_text":"Enjoy your meal","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite phrase said to someone before they start eating, wishing them a pleasant meal.","main_translations_es":["Que aproveche","¡A comer!","Disfruta tu comida"],"collocations":["Enjoy your meal!","Enjoy your meal, everyone","Enjoy your meal and dessert"],"example_sentence":"Enjoy your meal!","example_es":"¡Buen provecho!","example_en":"Enjoy your meal!","mnemonic_en":null}]'::jsonb) as x(
  spanish_text text, english_text text, section_name text, part_of_speech text, definition_en text,
  main_translations_es jsonb, collocations jsonb, example_sentence text, example_es text, example_en text, mnemonic_en text
)
where not exists (
  select 1 from public.cards c2
  where c2.deck_id = dk.id
    and lower(c2.spanish_text) = lower(x.spanish_text)
    and lower(c2.english_text) = lower(x.english_text)
);

-- english-c1-vocabulary (100 cards)
insert into public.decks (slug, title, description, language_from, language_to)
values ('english-c1-vocabulary', 'English C1 Vocabulary', 'Advanced English words and expressions for upper-level learners.', 'es', 'en')
on conflict (slug) do nothing;

insert into public.cards (deck_id, spanish_text, english_text, is_enabled, generation_phase, generation_metadata, section_name, part_of_speech, definition_en, main_translations_es, collocations, example_sentence, example_es, example_en, mnemonic_en)
select dk.id, x.spanish_text, x.english_text, true, 'refined', '{}'::jsonb, x.section_name, x.part_of_speech, x.definition_en,
       coalesce(x.main_translations_es, '[]'::jsonb), coalesce(x.collocations, '[]'::jsonb), x.example_sentence, x.example_es, x.example_en, x.mnemonic_en
from (select id from public.decks where slug = 'english-c1-vocabulary') dk
cross join jsonb_to_recordset('[{"spanish_text":"Aclarar","english_text":"Clarify","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to make something clear or easier to understand","main_translations_es":["Explicar","Precisar","Elucidar"],"collocations":["clarify the situation","clarify your doubts","clarify the meaning","clarify the issue"],"example_sentence":"Could you clarify the steps we need to follow to complete the project?","example_es":"¿Podrías aclarar los pasos que debemos seguir para completar el proyecto?","example_en":"Could you clarify the steps we need to follow to complete the project?","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Recalcar","english_text":"Emphasize","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give special importance or attention to something.","main_translations_es":["Destacar","Subrayar","Enfatizar"],"collocations":["emphasize the importance","emphasize the need","emphasize that","emphasize the point"],"example_sentence":"The teacher wanted to emphasize the importance of punctuality.","example_es":"El profesor quiso recalcar la importancia de la puntualidad.","example_en":"The teacher wanted to emphasize the importance of punctuality.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sostener","english_text":"Maintain","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To keep something in its existing state or condition.","main_translations_es":["Mantener","Conservar","Sustentar"],"collocations":["maintain a balance","maintain control","maintain the status quo","maintain relationships"],"example_sentence":"It is important to maintain a balanced diet to stay healthy.","example_es":"Es importante sostener una dieta equilibrada para mantenerse saludable.","example_en":"It is important to maintain a balanced diet to stay healthy.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cuestionar","english_text":"Challenge","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To invite someone to compete or to question the validity of something.","main_translations_es":["Desafiar","Poner en duda","Interrogar"],"collocations":["rise to the challenge","meet the challenge","challenge yourself","face a challenge"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to challenge the sources before believing them.","example_es":"Es importante cuestionar las fuentes antes de creer en ellas.","example_en":"It''s important to challenge the sources before believing them.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Respaldar","english_text":"Substantiate","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To provide evidence or proof that something is true or valid.","main_translations_es":["Apoyar","Confirmar","Sustentar"],"collocations":["substantiate a claim","substantiate the evidence","substantiate the allegations","substantiate findings"],"example_sentence":"The researcher must substantiate his conclusions with solid data.","example_es":"El investigador debe respaldar sus conclusiones con datos sólidos.","example_en":"The researcher must substantiate his conclusions with solid data.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Desestimar","english_text":"Dismiss","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To reject, disregard, or send away someone or something.","main_translations_es":["Rechazar","Descartar","Desestimar"],"collocations":["dismiss a case","dismiss the allegations","dismiss the idea","dismiss someone from their job"],"example_sentence":"The judge decided to dismiss the case due to lack of evidence.","example_es":"El juez decidió desestimar el caso por falta de pruebas.","example_en":"The judge decided to dismiss the case due to lack of evidence.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Impulsar","english_text":"Foster","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To encourage or promote the development or growth of something.","main_translations_es":["Promover","Estimular","Fomentar"],"collocations":["foster growth","foster relationships","foster development","foster innovation"],"example_sentence":"The government wants to foster technological innovation in the country.","example_es":"El gobierno quiere impulsar la innovación tecnológica en el país.","example_en":"The government wants to foster technological innovation in the country.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Conllevar","english_text":"Entail","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To involve or require something as a necessary consequence.","main_translations_es":["implicar","suponer","acarrear"],"collocations":["entail consequences","entail risks","entail a cost","entail responsibility"],"example_sentence":"This project entails a great financial risk.","example_es":"Este proyecto conlleva un gran riesgo financiero.","example_en":"This project entails a great financial risk.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Mitigar","english_text":"Mitigate","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To make something less severe, harmful, or painful.","main_translations_es":["Aliviar","Reducir","Suavizar"],"collocations":["mitigate the risk","mitigate the damage","mitigate the effects","mitigate the impact"],"example_sentence":"The government implemented new policies to mitigate the effects of climate change.","example_es":"El gobierno implementó nuevas políticas para mitigar los efectos del cambio climático.","example_en":"The government implemented new policies to mitigate the effects of climate change.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Agravar","english_text":"Exacerbate","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To make a problem, situation, or feeling worse or more intense.","main_translations_es":["Empeorar","Intensificar","Agravarse"],"collocations":["exacerbate the problem","exacerbate tensions","exacerbate symptoms","exacerbate the situation"],"example_sentence":"Lack of sleep can exacerbate the symptoms of depression.","example_es":"La falta de sueño puede agravar los síntomas de la depresión.","example_en":"Lack of sleep can exacerbate the symptoms of depression.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Plantear","english_text":"Put forward","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To propose or suggest something for consideration.","main_translations_es":["proponer","exponer","presentar"],"collocations":["put forward a proposal","put forward an argument","put forward a suggestion","put forward a theory"],"example_sentence":"The committee decided to put forward a new strategy for the next year.","example_es":"El comité decidió plantear una nueva estrategia para el próximo año.","example_en":"The committee decided to put forward a new strategy for the next year.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Abordar","english_text":"Address","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To direct attention to, discuss, or deal with something.","main_translations_es":["Tratar","Enfocar","Abordar"],"collocations":["address the issue","address a problem","address the audience","address the question"],"example_sentence":"The committee must address the climate change problem as soon as possible.","example_es":"El comité debe abordar el problema del cambio climático lo antes posible.","example_en":"The committee must address the climate change problem as soon as possible.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Determinar","english_text":"Determine","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To find out or establish something through investigation, calculation, or reasoning.","main_translations_es":["Establecer","Fijar","Precisar"],"collocations":["determine the cause","determine the outcome","determine the best approach","determine if"],"example_sentence":"Scientists must determine the cause of the outbreak.","example_es":"Los científicos deben determinar la causa del brote.","example_en":"Scientists must determine the cause of the outbreak.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Comprensivo","english_text":"Comprehensive","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Including all or nearly all elements or aspects; thorough and complete.","main_translations_es":["amplio","extenso","integral"],"collocations":["comprehensive review","comprehensive plan","comprehensive guide","comprehensive analysis"],"example_sentence":"The report is very comprehensive and covers all aspects of the project.","example_es":"El informe es muy comprensivo y cubre todos los aspectos del proyecto.","example_en":"The report is very comprehensive and covers all aspects of the project.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Matizado","english_text":"Nuanced","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Having subtle distinctions or variations in meaning, expression, or tone.","main_translations_es":["Sutil","Detallado","Con matices"],"collocations":["nuanced argument","nuanced perspective","nuanced approach","nuanced understanding"],"example_sentence":"His argument is nuanced and considers several points of view.","example_es":"Su argumento es matizado y considera varios puntos de vista.","example_en":"His argument is nuanced and considers several points of view.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Ambiguo","english_text":"Ambiguous","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Open to more than one interpretation or having an unclear meaning.","main_translations_es":["Vago","Confuso","Equívoco"],"collocations":["ambiguous meaning","ambiguous statement","ambiguous result","ambiguous situation"],"example_sentence":"The message of the ad was ambiguous, so many interpreted it in different ways.","example_es":"El mensaje del anuncio era ambiguo, por lo que muchos lo interpretaron de distintas maneras.","example_en":"The message of the ad was ambiguous, so many interpreted it in different ways.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Coherente","english_text":"Coherent","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Logical, consistent, and forming a unified whole.","main_translations_es":["Lógico","Consistente","Razonable"],"collocations":["coherent argument","coherent plan","coherent theory","coherent response"],"example_sentence":"His argument is coherent and easy to follow.","example_es":"Su argumento es coherente y fácil de seguir.","example_en":"His argument is coherent and easy to follow.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Preciso","english_text":"Precise","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Exact and accurate, leaving no room for error or ambiguity.","main_translations_es":["Exacto","Concreto","Detallado"],"collocations":["precise measurement","precise timing","precise language","precise answer"],"example_sentence":"I need a precise watch to measure the race time.","example_es":"Necesito un reloj preciso para medir el tiempo de la carrera.","example_en":"I need a precise watch to measure the race time.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Convincente","english_text":"Compelling","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Evoking interest, attention, or admiration in a powerful and persuasive way.","main_translations_es":["Persuasivo","Irresistible","Cautivador"],"collocations":["compelling argument","compelling evidence","compelling story","compelling reason"],"example_sentence":"The lawyer''s argument was so compelling that the jury had no doubts.","example_es":"El argumento del abogado fue tan convincente que el jurado no tuvo dudas.","example_en":"The lawyer''s argument was so compelling that the jury had no doubts.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Discrepancia","english_text":"Discrepancy","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A difference or inconsistency between two or more things that should be the same.","main_translations_es":["Desacuerdo","Diferencia","Incongruencia"],"collocations":["discrepancy in the data","notice a discrepancy","account for the discrepancy","resolve the discrepancy"],"example_sentence":"There is a large discrepancy between what the witness said and the evidence.","example_es":"Hay una gran discrepancia entre lo que dijo el testigo y la evidencia.","example_en":"There is a large discrepancy between what the witness said and the evidence.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Supuesto","english_text":"Assumption","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Something that is accepted as true without proof.","main_translations_es":["Hipótesis","Presunción","Suposición"],"collocations":["make an assumption","under the assumption that","assumption of risk","questionable assumption"],"example_sentence":"The assumption that the project will be profitable is optimistic.","example_es":"El supuesto de que el proyecto será rentable es optimista.","example_en":"The assumption that the project will be profitable is optimistic.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Planteamiento","english_text":"Approach","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A way of dealing with a problem or task.","main_translations_es":["Enfoque","Propuesta","Idea"],"collocations":["new approach","different approach","take an approach","approach the problem"],"example_sentence":"The project''s approach was approved by the committee.","example_es":"El planteamiento del proyecto fue aprobado por el comité.","example_en":"The project''s approach was approved by the committee.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Marco","english_text":"Framework","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A basic structure or system that supports the development or organization of something.","main_translations_es":["estructura","esquema","marco"],"collocations":["software framework","framework agreement","framework for","framework of"],"example_sentence":"The framework of the theory allows understanding the basic concepts.","example_es":"El marco de la teoría permite entender los conceptos básicos.","example_en":"The framework of the theory allows understanding the basic concepts.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Perspectiva","english_text":"Perspective","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A particular way of regarding something; a point of view.","main_translations_es":["Punto de vista","Enfoque","Óptica"],"collocations":["from a different perspective","gain perspective","broaden one''s perspective","new perspective"],"example_sentence":"From my perspective, the project has a lot of potential.","example_es":"Desde mi perspectiva, el proyecto tiene mucho potencial.","example_en":"From my perspective, the project has a lot of potential.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Hallazgo","english_text":"Finding","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A piece of information discovered as a result of investigation or research.","main_translations_es":["Descubrimiento","Resultado","Observación"],"collocations":["finding a solution","finding the truth","finding evidence","finding a cure"],"example_sentence":"The archaeologist''s finding changed the understanding of the civilization.","example_es":"El hallazgo del arqueólogo cambió la comprensión de la civilización.","example_en":"The archaeologist''s finding changed the understanding of the civilization.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Evidencia","english_text":"Evidence","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Evidence is information or objects that support a claim, belief, or conclusion.","main_translations_es":["prueba","testimonio","indicio"],"collocations":["gather evidence","present the evidence","lack of evidence","beyond a doubt"],"example_sentence":"The evidence suggests that the suspect was at the crime scene.","example_es":"La evidencia sugiere que el sospechoso estaba en la escena del crimen.","example_en":"The evidence suggests that the suspect was at the crime scene.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Restricción","english_text":"Constraint","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A limitation or restriction that controls what can be done or achieved.","main_translations_es":["limitación","condición","restricción"],"collocations":["budget constraint","time constraint","constraint satisfaction","constraint programming"],"example_sentence":"The speed constraint on the highway is 100 km/h.","example_es":"La restricción de velocidad en la autopista es de 100 km/h.","example_en":"The speed constraint on the highway is 100 km/h.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Viable","english_text":"Feasible","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Possible to do or achieve; capable of being carried out successfully.","main_translations_es":["Factible","Viable","Realizable"],"collocations":["feasible solution","feasible option","feasible approach","feasible plan"],"example_sentence":"The project is feasible if we secure more funding.","example_es":"El proyecto es viable si conseguimos más financiación.","example_en":"The project is feasible if we secure more funding.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sostenible","english_text":"Sustainable","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Capable of being maintained over the long term without depleting resources or causing harm.","main_translations_es":["Sustentable","Duradero","Ecoamigable"],"collocations":["sustainable development","sustainable growth","sustainable energy","sustainable practices"],"example_sentence":"This company has implemented sustainable practices to reduce its carbon footprint.","example_es":"Esta empresa ha implementado prácticas sostenibles para reducir su huella de carbono.","example_en":"This company has implemented sustainable practices to reduce its carbon footprint.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Controvertido","english_text":"Controversial","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Describing something that provokes public disagreement or debate.","main_translations_es":["Polémico","Discutido","Contencioso"],"collocations":["controversial issue","controversial figure","controversial topic","controversial decision"],"example_sentence":"The issue of euthanasia remains controversial in many countries.","example_es":"El tema de la eutanasia sigue siendo controvertido en muchos países.","example_en":"The issue of euthanasia remains controversial in many countries.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Generalizado","english_text":"Widespread","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Existing or occurring over a large area or among many people.","main_translations_es":["Extenso","General","Difuso"],"collocations":["widespread use","widespread adoption","widespread problem","widespread belief"],"example_sentence":"The use of mobile phones has become very widespread throughout the country.","example_es":"El uso de los teléfonos móviles se ha vuelto muy generalizado en todo el país.","example_en":"The use of mobile phones has become very widespread throughout the country.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Predominante","english_text":"Predominant","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Being the most common, strongest, or most important element in a group or situation.","main_translations_es":["principal","dominante","preponderante"],"collocations":["predominant theme","predominant factor","predominant position","predominant in"],"example_sentence":"The color blue is predominant in the room''s decor.","example_es":"El color azul es predominante en la decoración de la habitación.","example_en":"The color blue is predominant in the room''s decor.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Subyacente","english_text":"Underlying","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Existing beneath the surface or forming the basis of something.","main_translations_es":["subyacente","latente","de base"],"collocations":["underlying cause","underlying principle","underlying assumption","underlying issue"],"example_sentence":"The underlying problem is the lack of communication.","example_es":"El problema subyacente es la falta de comunicación.","example_en":"The underlying problem is the lack of communication.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Trascender","english_text":"Transcend","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To go beyond or rise above something, especially limits, expectations, or ordinary experience.","main_translations_es":["sobrepasar","ir más allá","superar"],"collocations":["transcend boundaries","transcend the ordinary","transcend time","transcend expectations"],"example_sentence":"Van Gogh''s art manages to transcend time and continues to inspire new generations.","example_es":"El arte de Van Gogh logra trascender el tiempo y sigue inspirando a nuevas generaciones.","example_en":"Van Gogh''s art manages to transcend time and continues to inspire new generations.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Perjudicar","english_text":"Undermine","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To weaken or damage something gradually or subtly.","main_translations_es":["dañar","desmejorar","afectar negativamente"],"collocations":["undermine confidence","undermine authority","undermine credibility","undermine efforts"],"example_sentence":"Constant criticism can undermine the team''s confidence.","example_es":"Las críticas constantes pueden perjudicar la confianza del equipo.","example_en":"Constant criticism can undermine the team''s confidence.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cumplir","english_text":"Comply with","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to act in accordance with a rule, request, or demand","main_translations_es":["Obedecer","Acatar","Cumplir con"],"collocations":["comply with regulations","comply with the law","comply with standards","comply with requirements"],"example_sentence":"It is important to comply with the safety regulations.","example_es":"Es importante cumplir con las normas de seguridad.","example_en":"It is important to comply with the safety regulations.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Ajustarse a","english_text":"Adhere to","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to follow or comply with a rule, guideline, or request","main_translations_es":["adaptarse a","cumplir con","acatar"],"collocations":["adhere to guidelines","adhere to the policy","adhere to standards","adhere to a schedule"],"example_sentence":"It is important to adhere to the company''s rules.","example_es":"Es importante ajustarse a las normas de la empresa.","example_en":"It is important to adhere to the company''s rules.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Dar lugar a","english_text":"Give rise to","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to cause something to happen or exist","main_translations_es":["Provocar","Causar","Originar"],"collocations":["give rise to problems","give rise to controversy","give rise to questions","give rise to a new trend"],"example_sentence":"The new policy can give rise to massive protests.","example_es":"La nueva política puede dar lugar a protestas masivas.","example_en":"The new policy can give rise to massive protests.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Tener en cuenta","english_text":"Take into account","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To consider or regard something when making a decision.","main_translations_es":["Considerar","Tomar en consideración","Tener presente"],"collocations":["take into account the fact that","take into account the costs","take into account the risks"],"example_sentence":"You should take into account the weather before going out.","example_es":"Debes tener en cuenta el clima antes de salir.","example_en":"You should take into account the weather before going out.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Llegar a la conclusión","english_text":"Reach the conclusion","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"to arrive at a final decision or judgment after considering the evidence","main_translations_es":["Llegar a una conclusión","Concluir","Llegar a la conclusión"],"collocations":["reach the conclusion that","reach the conclusion after","reach the conclusion based on","reach the conclusion that it is"],"example_sentence":"After reviewing all the data, we reached the conclusion that the project is viable.","example_es":"Después de revisar todos los datos, llegamos a la conclusión de que el proyecto es viable.","example_en":"After reviewing all the data, we reached the conclusion that the project is viable.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"En gran medida","english_text":"To a large extent","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means that something is true or applies to a great degree.","main_translations_es":["En gran medida","En gran parte","Considerablemente"],"collocations":["It is true to a large extent","The impact is felt to a large extent","Results vary to a large extent"],"example_sentence":"The success of the project depends, to a large extent, on the team''s collaboration.","example_es":"El éxito del proyecto depende, en gran medida, de la colaboración del equipo.","example_en":"The success of the project depends, to a large extent, on the team''s collaboration.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"A corto plazo","english_text":"In the short term","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"During a brief period of time, referring to the near future.","main_translations_es":["En el corto plazo","A corto plazo","En el futuro cercano"],"collocations":["In the short term, we expect...","In the short term, the company will...","In the short term, this will improve"],"example_sentence":"In the short term, the company plans to increase its sales by 10%.","example_es":"A corto plazo, la empresa planea aumentar sus ventas en un 10%.","example_en":"In the short term, the company plans to increase its sales by 10%.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"A largo plazo","english_text":"In the long run","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"refers to what will happen over a long period of time","main_translations_es":["A largo plazo","A futuro","En el futuro"],"collocations":["In the long run, it will pay off","In the long run, the benefits outweigh the costs","In the long run, we see improvement"],"example_sentence":"In the long run, investment in education will reduce inequality.","example_es":"A largo plazo, la inversión en educación reducirá la desigualdad.","example_en":"In the long run, investment in education will reduce inequality.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Desde mi punto de vista","english_text":"From my perspective","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to indicate that something is being considered from one''s own point of view.","main_translations_es":["Según mi punto de vista","A mi parecer","En mi opinión"],"collocations":["From my perspective, ...","From my perspective it seems that ...","From my perspective we can see ..."],"example_sentence":"From my perspective, education should be free.","example_es":"Desde mi punto de vista, la educación debería ser gratuita.","example_en":"From my perspective, education should be free.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"En última instancia","english_text":"Ultimately","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"In the end, after everything else has been considered.","main_translations_es":["Al fin de cuentas","En definitiva","Al final"],"collocations":["ultimately decided","ultimately leads to","ultimately result","ultimately important"],"example_sentence":"Ultimately, the decision depends on you.","example_es":"En última instancia, la decisión depende de ti.","example_en":"Ultimately, the decision depends on you.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"En lo que respecta a","english_text":"As far as ... is concerned","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to indicate that something is being considered or discussed in relation to a particular subject.","main_translations_es":["En cuanto a","Con respecto a","En lo que se refiere a"],"collocations":["as far as I''m concerned","as far as you''re concerned","as far as the matter is concerned","as far as the law is concerned"],"example_sentence":"As far as safety is concerned, the company has implemented new measures.","example_es":"En lo que respecta a la seguridad, la empresa ha implementado nuevas medidas.","example_en":"As far as safety is concerned, the company has implemented new measures.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cabe destacar","english_text":"It is worth noting","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to indicate that something should be emphasized or remembered.","main_translations_es":["Hay que destacar","Vale la pena señalar","Es importante señalar"],"collocations":["It is worth noting that...","It is worth noting the following...","It is worth noting the fact that..."],"example_sentence":"It is worth noting that the research revealed new findings about the climate.","example_es":"Cabe destacar que la investigación reveló nuevos hallazgos sobre el clima.","example_en":"It is worth noting that the research revealed new findings about the climate.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Vale la pena señalar","english_text":"It is worth pointing out","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"idiomatic expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to indicate that something should be highlighted or mentioned.","main_translations_es":["Cabe destacar","Hay que señalar","Vale la pena mencionar"],"collocations":["It is worth pointing out that...","It is worth pointing out the fact that...","It is worth pointing out the importance of..."],"example_sentence":"It is worth pointing out that the report contains several errors.","example_es":"Vale la pena señalar que el informe contiene varios errores.","example_en":"It is worth pointing out that the report contains several errors.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No cabe duda de que","english_text":"There is no doubt that","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to indicate that something is certain and unquestionable.","main_translations_es":["Sin duda","No hay duda de que","Indudablemente"],"collocations":["There is no doubt that…","There is no doubt about it.","No doubt that…"],"example_sentence":"There is no doubt that the new policy will improve the country''s economy.","example_es":"No cabe duda de que la nueva política mejorará la economía del país.","example_en":"There is no doubt that the new policy will improve the country''s economy.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Resulta evidente que","english_text":"It is evident that","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to state that something is clearly apparent or obvious.","main_translations_es":["Es evidente que","Resulta claro que","Se ve que"],"collocations":["It is evident that...","It is evident that the data shows...","It is evident that there is a problem","It is evident that this is the case"],"example_sentence":"It is evident that air pollution is worsening public health.","example_es":"Resulta evidente que la contaminación del aire está empeorando la salud pública.","example_en":"It is evident that air pollution is worsening public health.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sin perjuicio de","english_text":"Without prejudice to","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase indicating that something does not affect or limit another matter.","main_translations_es":["sin que ello implique","sin afectar","sin menoscabar"],"collocations":["without prejudice to the rights of","without prejudice to any claim","without prejudice to the above","without prejudice to further action"],"example_sentence":"Without prejudice to what has been agreed, the company may change the working hours.","example_es":"Sin perjuicio de lo acordado, la empresa podrá modificar los horarios.","example_en":"Without prejudice to what has been agreed, the company may change the working hours.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"En aras de","english_text":"For the sake of","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to indicate that something is done in order to achieve or benefit something else.","main_translations_es":["con el fin de","a fin de","por el bien de"],"collocations":["for the sake of argument","for the sake of clarity","for the sake of completeness"],"example_sentence":"For the sake of safety, they closed the road during the storm.","example_es":"En aras de la seguridad, cerraron la carretera durante la tormenta.","example_en":"For the sake of safety, they closed the road during the storm.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"De ahí que","english_text":"Hence","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"As a result; for that reason.","main_translations_es":["Por eso","Así que","De esa forma"],"collocations":["henceforth","hence the","hence we can","hence the result"],"example_sentence":"It was raining heavily, hence they cancelled the match.","example_es":"Estaba lloviendo mucho, de ahí que cancelaron el partido.","example_en":"It was raining heavily, hence they cancelled the match.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Dado que","english_text":"Given that","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"conjunction","definition_en":"Considering that; used to introduce a reason or condition.","main_translations_es":["Considerando que","Puesto que","Ya que"],"collocations":["Given that you are here","Given that it''s raining","Given that we have no choice","Given that the data is correct"],"example_sentence":"Given that it is raining, we will cancel the picnic.","example_es":"Dado que está lloviendo, cancelaremos el picnic.","example_en":"Given that it is raining, we will cancel the picnic.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Aunque","english_text":"Albeit","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"conjunction","definition_en":"It means ''although'' or ''even though''.","main_translations_es":["aunque","aun cuando","si bien"],"collocations":["albeit briefly","albeit unlikely","albeit not","albeit with reservations"],"example_sentence":"Albeit he was tired, he kept working late.","example_es":"Aunque estaba cansado, siguió trabajando hasta tarde.","example_en":"Albeit he was tired, he kept working late.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Mientras que","english_text":"Whereas","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"conjunction","definition_en":"Used to introduce a contrast or comparison between two statements.","main_translations_es":["En cambio","A diferencia de","Mientras"],"collocations":["as opposed to","in contrast to","whereas the former","whereas the latter"],"example_sentence":"I prefer tea, whereas my brother prefers coffee.","example_es":"Yo prefiero el té, mientras que mi hermano prefiere el café.","example_en":"I prefer tea, whereas my brother prefers coffee.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"En cambio","english_text":"By contrast","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adverbial phrase","definition_en":"Used to introduce a statement that is different from or opposite to what has just been mentioned.","main_translations_es":["Por el contrario","En contraste","A diferencia"],"collocations":["by contrast, ...","by contrast with","by contrast to"],"example_sentence":"I prefer tea; by contrast, my brother always chooses coffee.","example_es":"Yo prefiero el té; en cambio, mi hermano siempre elige café.","example_en":"I prefer tea; by contrast, my brother always chooses coffee.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Asimismo","english_text":"Likewise","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"In the same way or manner; similarly.","main_translations_es":["Igualmente","De igual manera","Del mismo modo"],"collocations":["Likewise, thank you","Likewise, I agree","Likewise, we will proceed","Likewise, the same applies"],"example_sentence":"Likewise, we must consider the costs before making a decision.","example_es":"Asimismo, debemos considerar los costos antes de tomar una decisión.","example_en":"Likewise, we must consider the costs before making a decision.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Por consiguiente","english_text":"Consequently","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"In a way that indicates a result or effect; therefore.","main_translations_es":["En consecuencia","Por lo tanto","Así que"],"collocations":["Consequently, the results were significant","Consequently, we decided to proceed","Consequently, the project was delayed"],"example_sentence":"Consequently, the project was delayed by a week.","example_es":"Por consiguiente, el proyecto se retrasó una semana.","example_en":"Consequently, the project was delayed by a week.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No obstante","english_text":"Nevertheless","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"in spite of that; however","main_translations_es":["Sin embargo","Aun así","Con todo"],"collocations":["Nevertheless, ...","Nevertheless, we must","Nevertheless, it is","Nevertheless, she continued"],"example_sentence":"Nevertheless, he decided to continue with the project.","example_es":"No obstante, decidió continuar con el proyecto.","example_en":"Nevertheless, he decided to continue with the project.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Aun así","english_text":"Even so","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to introduce a statement that contrasts with or qualifies what has just been said.","main_translations_es":["Sin embargo","No obstante","Aun así"],"collocations":["Even so, ...","Even so, he continued","Even so, the outcome changed","Even so, they agreed"],"example_sentence":"Even so, he decided to go to the concert despite the rain.","example_es":"Aun así, decidió ir al concierto a pesar de la lluvia.","example_en":"Even so, he decided to go to the concert despite the rain.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Poner de relieve","english_text":"Highlight","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To emphasize or make something stand out.","main_translations_es":["Resaltar","Destacar","Subrayar"],"collocations":["highlight the main points","highlight a problem","highlight in yellow","highlight the differences"],"example_sentence":"The report highlights the importance of early education.","example_es":"El informe pone de relieve la importancia de la educación temprana.","example_en":"The report highlights the importance of early education.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Poner en tela de juicio","english_text":"Call into question","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"to express doubt about the truth or validity of something.","main_translations_es":["Cuestionar","Poner en duda","Poner en entredicho"],"collocations":["call into question the validity","call into question the results","call into question his motives","call into question the decision"],"example_sentence":"The committee decided to call into question the validity of the report.","example_es":"El comité decidió poner en tela de juicio la validez del informe.","example_en":"The committee decided to call into question the validity of the report.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sacar provecho de","english_text":"Capitalize on","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to take advantage of something for one''s benefit","main_translations_es":["Aprovechar","Explotar","Beneficiarse de"],"collocations":["capitalize on opportunities","capitalize on trends","capitalize on the situation","capitalize on his strengths"],"example_sentence":"The company knew how to capitalize on the new regulations to cut its costs.","example_es":"La empresa supo sacar provecho de la nueva normativa para reducir sus costos.","example_en":"The company knew how to capitalize on the new regulations to cut its costs.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Hacer frente a","english_text":"Cope with","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to deal effectively with something difficult or challenging","main_translations_es":["Enfrentar","Lidiar con","Hacer frente a"],"collocations":["cope with stress","cope with loss","cope with change","cope with difficulties"],"example_sentence":"It''s hard to cope with the loss of a loved one.","example_es":"Es difícil hacer frente a la pérdida de un ser querido.","example_en":"It''s hard to cope with the loss of a loved one.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Asumir la responsabilidad","english_text":"Take responsibility","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To accept or assume accountability for something.","main_translations_es":["Asumir la responsabilidad","Hacerse cargo","Responsabilizarse"],"collocations":["take responsibility for","take responsibility seriously","take responsibility of","take responsibility and act"],"example_sentence":"It is important to take responsibility for your actions.","example_es":"Es importante asumir la responsabilidad de tus actos.","example_en":"It is important to take responsibility for your actions.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Llegar a un acuerdo","english_text":"Reach an agreement","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To come to a mutual understanding or settlement.","main_translations_es":["Acuerdan","Llegar a un pacto","Cerrar un trato"],"collocations":["reach an agreement on","reach an agreement with","reach a final agreement","reach an agreement quickly"],"example_sentence":"After lengthy negotiations, we finally managed to reach an agreement.","example_es":"Después de largas negociaciones, finalmente logramos llegar a un acuerdo.","example_en":"After lengthy negotiations, we finally managed to reach an agreement.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Tomar medidas","english_text":"Take action","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To do something in order to achieve a result.","main_translations_es":["Actuar","Emprender acciones","Hacer algo"],"collocations":["take action now","take action against","take decisive action","take action to"],"example_sentence":"It''s time to take action to reduce pollution.","example_es":"Es hora de tomar medidas para reducir la contaminación.","example_en":"It''s time to take action to reduce pollution.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Dar prioridad a","english_text":"Prioritize","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give priority to something, treating it as more important than other things.","main_translations_es":["Priorizar","Dar preferencia a","Poner en primer lugar"],"collocations":["prioritize tasks","prioritize safety","prioritize customer needs","prioritize the budget"],"example_sentence":"We must prioritize education in our budget.","example_es":"Debemos dar prioridad a la educación en nuestro presupuesto.","example_en":"We must prioritize education in our budget.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Pasar por alto","english_text":"Overlook","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To fail to notice or consider something.","main_translations_es":["Ignorar","Desatender","Omitir"],"collocations":["overlook the details","overlook a mistake","overlook the fact"],"example_sentence":"You shouldn''t overlook the important details of the contract.","example_es":"No deberías pasar por alto los detalles importantes del contrato.","example_en":"You shouldn''t overlook the important details of the contract.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Contrarrestar","english_text":"Counteract","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To act against something in order to reduce or neutralize its effect.","main_translations_es":["neutralizar","compensar","mitigar"],"collocations":["counteract the effects","counteract the damage","counteract the influence"],"example_sentence":"The new drug helps to counteract the side effects of the treatment.","example_es":"El nuevo medicamento ayuda a contrarrestar los efectos secundarios del tratamiento.","example_en":"The new drug helps to counteract the side effects of the treatment.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Reforzar","english_text":"Reinforce","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To strengthen or support something, often by adding material or effort.","main_translations_es":["Fortalecer","Consolidar","Robustecer"],"collocations":["reinforce the argument","reinforce the structure","reinforce security measures","reinforce the message"],"example_sentence":"The coach decided to reinforce the team''s defense before the next match.","example_es":"El entrenador decidió reforzar la defensa del equipo antes del próximo partido.","example_en":"The coach decided to reinforce the team''s defense before the next match.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Debilitar","english_text":"Weaken","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To make something less strong, less effective, or less able to resist.","main_translations_es":["Atenuar","Mermar","Desgastar"],"collocations":["weaken the economy","weaken the argument","weaken the resolve"],"example_sentence":"The intense cold began to weaken the garden''s plants.","example_es":"El frío intenso comenzó a debilitar las plantas del jardín.","example_en":"The intense cold began to weaken the garden''s plants.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Desencadenar","english_text":"Trigger","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to cause something to happen or to start a process.","main_translations_es":["Provocar","Desatar","Iniciar"],"collocations":["trigger a reaction","trigger an alarm","trigger a response","trigger the event"],"example_sentence":"The discovery of the new particle could trigger a revolution in physics.","example_es":"El descubrimiento de la nueva partícula podría desencadenar una revolución en la física.","example_en":"The discovery of the new particle could trigger a revolution in physics.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Prever","english_text":"Anticipate","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To expect or look forward to something and act in advance based on that expectation.","main_translations_es":["predecir","anticipar","prever"],"collocations":["anticipate the outcome","anticipate a problem","anticipate the results","anticipate the future"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to anticipate problems before they happen.","example_es":"Es importante prever los problemas antes de que ocurran.","example_en":"It''s important to anticipate problems before they happen.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Logro","english_text":"Achievement","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A successful result or accomplishment that someone has attained.","main_translations_es":["Éxito","Triunfo","Conquista"],"collocations":["a great achievement","personal achievement","significant achievement","achievement unlocked"],"example_sentence":"This is my greatest achievement so far.","example_es":"Este es mi mayor logro hasta ahora.","example_en":"This is my greatest achievement so far.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Retroceso","english_text":"Setback","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A reversal or hindrance that delays progress.","main_translations_es":["Retroceso","Reversión","Retrogradación"],"collocations":["a major setback","temporary setback","suffer a setback","setback in progress"],"example_sentence":"The project suffered an unexpected setback after the loss of funding.","example_es":"El proyecto sufrió un retroceso inesperado después de la pérdida de financiación.","example_en":"The project suffered an unexpected setback after the loss of funding.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Aporte","english_text":"Contribution","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Something given or offered, especially to help achieve a common goal.","main_translations_es":["Contribución","Aportación","Colaboración"],"collocations":["make a contribution","significant contribution","financial contribution","contribute to the cause"],"example_sentence":"His contribution to the project was essential for its success.","example_es":"Su aporte al proyecto fue fundamental para su éxito.","example_en":"His contribution to the project was essential for its success.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Carencia","english_text":"Shortcoming","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A fault, deficiency, or lack of a desired quality.","main_translations_es":["Falta","Escasez","Déficit"],"collocations":["a shortcoming of","address the shortcoming","shortcoming in","the shortcoming is"],"example_sentence":"His lack of experience was his greatest shortcoming.","example_es":"Su falta de experiencia fue su mayor carencia.","example_en":"His lack of experience was his greatest shortcoming.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Aseveración","english_text":"Assertion","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A confident statement that something is true.","main_translations_es":["afirmación","declaración","aseguramiento"],"collocations":["make an assertion","assertion of fact","assertion of rights","assertion that"],"example_sentence":"His assertion that the project would be finished on time turned out to be false.","example_es":"Su aseveración de que el proyecto terminaría a tiempo resultó ser falsa.","example_en":"His assertion that the project would be finished on time turned out to be false.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Integridad","english_text":"Integrity","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the quality of being honest and having strong moral principles","main_translations_es":["Honestidad","Rectitud","Honradez"],"collocations":["maintain integrity","integrity and honesty","integrity of the data","integrity in the workplace"],"example_sentence":"The integrity of the data is essential for the system''s security.","example_es":"La integridad de los datos es fundamental para la seguridad del sistema.","example_en":"The integrity of the data is essential for the system''s security.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Fiabilidad","english_text":"Reliability","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The quality of being trustworthy and consistently performing as expected.","main_translations_es":["Confiabilidad","Seguridad","Estabilidad"],"collocations":["high reliability","reliability of the system","reliability engineering","test reliability"],"example_sentence":"The reliability of this car is impressive.","example_es":"La fiabilidad de este coche es impresionante.","example_en":"The reliability of this car is impressive.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Rendición de cuentas","english_text":"Accountability","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The obligation to accept responsibility for one''s actions and decisions.","main_translations_es":["Responsabilidad","Justificación","Transparencia"],"collocations":["accountability measures","accountability framework","hold someone accountable","accountability standards"],"example_sentence":"Accountability is essential for transparency in government.","example_es":"La rendición de cuentas es esencial para la transparencia en el gobierno.","example_en":"Accountability is essential for transparency in government.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Transparencia","english_text":"Transparency","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The quality of being clear, open, and easily understood, or the condition of allowing light to pass through so that objects behind can be seen.","main_translations_es":["Claridad","Visibilidad","Nítido"],"collocations":["transparency in government","financial transparency","transparency and accountability","transparent communication"],"example_sentence":"Transparency in government is essential for citizens'' trust.","example_es":"La transparencia en el gobierno es esencial para la confianza de los ciudadanos.","example_en":"Transparency in government is essential for citizens'' trust.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Imparcial","english_text":"Impartial","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Not favoring one side over another; unbiased.","main_translations_es":["Objetivo","Neutral","Sin sesgo"],"collocations":["impartial judge","impartial decision","impartial opinion","impartial observer"],"example_sentence":"The judge must be impartial when delivering his verdict.","example_es":"El juez debe ser imparcial al dictar su veredicto.","example_en":"The judge must be impartial when delivering his verdict.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Parcial","english_text":"Biased","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Showing an unfair preference or prejudice toward something or someone.","main_translations_es":["Sesgado","Tendencioso","Parcial"],"collocations":["biased opinion","biased view","biased towards","biased against"],"example_sentence":"The judge was biased in his decision.","example_es":"El juez fue parcial en su decisión.","example_en":"The judge was biased in his decision.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Rigurosidad","english_text":"Rigor","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"strictness or exactness in standards, procedures, or conduct","main_translations_es":["rigor","exigencia","precisión"],"collocations":["scientific rigor","rigor of the law","rigor in methodology"],"example_sentence":"The rigor of the scientific method ensures reliable results.","example_es":"La rigurosidad del método científico garantiza resultados fiables.","example_en":"The rigor of the scientific method ensures reliable results.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Coexistir","english_text":"Coexist","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To exist together at the same time or in the same place.","main_translations_es":["convivir","cohabitar","coexistir"],"collocations":["coexist peacefully","coexist with","coexist in harmony","coexist side by side"],"example_sentence":"The different cultural groups must learn to coexist in harmony.","example_es":"Los diferentes grupos culturales deben aprender a coexistir en armonía.","example_en":"The different cultural groups must learn to coexist in harmony.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Conciliar","english_text":"Reconcile","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To restore harmony between parties or to make different ideas consistent.","main_translations_es":["reconciliar","armonizar","comprometer"],"collocations":["reconcile differences","reconcile accounts","reconcile with","reconcile the data"],"example_sentence":"The mediator managed to reconcile the two parties in conflict.","example_es":"El mediador logró conciliar a las dos partes en conflicto.","example_en":"The mediator managed to reconcile the two parties in conflict.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Desplegar","english_text":"Deploy","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To position or arrange resources, personnel, or equipment for use, especially in a strategic or operational context.","main_translations_es":["Implementar","Instalar","Poner en marcha"],"collocations":["deploy a new version","deploy troops","deploy resources","deploy the application"],"example_sentence":"The team decided to deploy the new update tomorrow.","example_es":"El equipo decidió desplegar la nueva actualización mañana.","example_en":"The team decided to deploy the new update tomorrow.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Aprovechar","english_text":"Harness","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To control and use something, especially a resource or energy, for a specific purpose.","main_translations_es":["Utilizar","Explotar","Sacar provecho"],"collocations":["harness the power","harness potential","harness energy","harness resources"],"example_sentence":"We must harness the available resources to the fullest.","example_es":"Debemos aprovechar al máximo los recursos disponibles.","example_en":"We must harness the available resources to the fullest.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Percepción","english_text":"Perception","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of recognizing, interpreting, and organizing sensory information.","main_translations_es":["Percepción","Sensación","Observación"],"collocations":["public perception","perception of reality","visual perception"],"example_sentence":"His perception of the problem changed after hearing the data.","example_es":"Su percepción del problema cambió después de escuchar los datos.","example_en":"His perception of the problem changed after hearing the data.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Tendencia","english_text":"Trend","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A general direction in which something is developing or changing.","main_translations_es":["Moda","Corriente","Dirección"],"collocations":["upward trend","trend towards","trend analysis","trend line"],"example_sentence":"The current trend is to work from home.","example_es":"La tendencia actual es trabajar desde casa.","example_en":"The current trend is to work from home.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Repercusiones","english_text":"Repercussions","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the unintended or indirect consequences of an action or event, especially negative ones","main_translations_es":["Consecuencias","Efectos","Secuelas"],"collocations":["face the repercussions","have serious repercussions","the repercussions were felt","repercussions of the decision"],"example_sentence":"The repercussions of the decision were unexpected.","example_es":"Las repercusiones de la decisión fueron inesperadas.","example_en":"The repercussions of the decision were unexpected.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Plausible","english_text":"Plausible","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Reasonable or probable; appearing worthy of belief.","main_translations_es":["verosímil","creíble","probable"],"collocations":["plausible explanation","plausible deniability","plausible scenario","plausible argument"],"example_sentence":"It is plausible that we will arrive on time.","example_es":"Es plausible que lleguemos a tiempo.","example_en":"It is plausible that we will arrive on time.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Inevitable","english_text":"Inevitable","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Impossible to avoid or prevent; certain to happen.","main_translations_es":["inevitable","inexorable","ineludible"],"collocations":["inevitable outcome","inevitable consequence","inevitable result"],"example_sentence":"It was inevitable that the project would fail.","example_es":"Era inevitable que el proyecto fracasara.","example_en":"It was inevitable that the project would fail.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Rentable","english_text":"Cost-effective","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Providing good value or results relative to the amount spent.","main_translations_es":["económico","asequible","de bajo costo"],"collocations":["cost-effective solution","cost-effective strategy","cost-effective approach","cost-effective measure"],"example_sentence":"This car is very cost-effective for the company.","example_es":"Este coche es muy rentable para la empresa.","example_en":"This car is very cost-effective for the company.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Práctica arraigada","english_text":"Entrenched practice","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"A practice that is firmly established and difficult to change.","main_translations_es":["costumbre arraigada","práctica consolidada","hábito profundo"],"collocations":["deeply entrenched practice","long‑standing entrenched practice","entrenched practice of","entrenched practice in"],"example_sentence":"The entrenched practice of working overtime without extra pay is affecting the team''s morale.","example_es":"La práctica arraigada de trabajar horas extras sin paga adicional está afectando la moral del equipo.","example_en":"The entrenched practice of working overtime without extra pay is affecting the team''s morale.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cumplir con las expectativas","english_text":"Meet expectations","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To fulfill or satisfy the standards or requirements that are anticipated.","main_translations_es":["Estar a la altura de las expectativas","Satisfacer las expectativas","Cumplir las expectativas"],"collocations":["meet expectations","live up to expectations","exceed expectations","fall short of expectations"],"example_sentence":"The new employee managed to meet expectations of the company from his first day.","example_es":"El nuevo empleado logró cumplir con las expectativas de la empresa desde su primer día.","example_en":"The new employee managed to meet expectations of the company from his first day.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Superar las expectativas","english_text":"Exceed expectations","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To go beyond what is expected.","main_translations_es":["Ir más allá de lo esperado","Superar lo esperado","Sobrepasar las expectativas"],"collocations":["exceed expectations","exceed expectations by","exceed expectations consistently","exceed expectations in performance"],"example_sentence":"Our team managed to exceed the client''s expectations with the final project.","example_es":"Nuestro equipo logró superar las expectativas del cliente con el proyecto final.","example_en":"Our team managed to exceed the client''s expectations with the final project.","mnemonic_en":null}]'::jsonb) as x(
  spanish_text text, english_text text, section_name text, part_of_speech text, definition_en text,
  main_translations_es jsonb, collocations jsonb, example_sentence text, example_es text, example_en text, mnemonic_en text
)
where not exists (
  select 1 from public.cards c2
  where c2.deck_id = dk.id
    and lower(c2.spanish_text) = lower(x.spanish_text)
    and lower(c2.english_text) = lower(x.english_text)
);

-- english-workplace-communication (121 cards)
insert into public.decks (slug, title, description, language_from, language_to)
values ('english-workplace-communication', 'Workplace Communication', 'Advanced vocabulary and expressions for meetings, projects, collaboration, and professional communication.', 'es', 'en')
on conflict (slug) do nothing;

insert into public.cards (deck_id, spanish_text, english_text, is_enabled, generation_phase, generation_metadata, section_name, part_of_speech, definition_en, main_translations_es, collocations, example_sentence, example_es, example_en, mnemonic_en)
select dk.id, x.spanish_text, x.english_text, true, 'refined', '{}'::jsonb, x.section_name, x.part_of_speech, x.definition_en,
       coalesce(x.main_translations_es, '[]'::jsonb), coalesce(x.collocations, '[]'::jsonb), x.example_sentence, x.example_es, x.example_en, x.mnemonic_en
from (select id from public.decks where slug = 'english-workplace-communication') dk
cross join jsonb_to_recordset('[{"spanish_text":"Correo electrónico","english_text":"Email","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A system for sending digital messages electronically over the internet.","main_translations_es":["e‑mail","correo","mail"],"collocations":["send an email","check your email","email address","email inbox"],"example_sentence":"I sent you an email yesterday.","example_es":"Te envié un correo electrónico ayer.","example_en":"I sent you an email yesterday.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Asunto","english_text":"Subject line","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"The line of text that identifies the topic of an email or message.","main_translations_es":["Tema","Motivo","Cuestión"],"collocations":["write a compelling subject line","optimize the subject line","subject line testing","subject line preview"],"example_sentence":"In the email, the subject line says \"Meeting tomorrow\".","example_es":"En el correo, el asunto dice \"Reunión mañana\".","example_en":"In the email, the subject line says \"Meeting tomorrow\".","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Adjunto","english_text":"Attachment","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A supplementary item, such as a file or document, that is attached to a message or object.","main_translations_es":["Adjunto","Anexo","Archivo adjunto"],"collocations":["email attachment","attachment size","attachment file","attachment icon"],"example_sentence":"Please find the attachment with the report you requested.","example_es":"Adjunto el informe que solicitaste.","example_en":"Please find the attachment with the report you requested.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Reenviar","english_text":"Forward","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To send something on to another recipient.","main_translations_es":["Remitir","Enviar de nuevo","Reexpedir"],"collocations":["move forward","look forward to","forward slash","forward thinking"],"example_sentence":"Can you forward the email to all team members?","example_es":"¿Puedes reenviar el correo a todos los miembros del equipo?","example_en":"Can you forward the email to all team members?","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Responder a todos","english_text":"Reply all","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"Send a response to all recipients of an email.","main_translations_es":["Responder a todos","Responder a todos los destinatarios","Responder a todos los correos"],"collocations":["click Reply All","use Reply All","select Reply All","press Reply All"],"example_sentence":"Remember to reply all to the group''s messages.","example_es":"Recuerda responder a todos los mensajes del grupo.","example_en":"Remember to reply all to the group''s messages.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Seguimiento","english_text":"Follow-up","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"An action taken to continue or check the progress of something previously started.","main_translations_es":["Control","Monitoreo","Seguimiento"],"collocations":["follow-up email","follow-up meeting","follow-up call","follow-up action"],"example_sentence":"I will do a follow-up on the project next week.","example_es":"Haré un seguimiento del proyecto la próxima semana.","example_en":"I will do a follow-up on the project next week.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Programar una reunión","english_text":"Schedule a meeting","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To arrange a time for a meeting.","main_translations_es":["Organizar una reunión","Concertar una reunión","Fijar una reunión"],"collocations":["schedule a meeting with","schedule a meeting for","schedule a meeting next week","schedule a meeting at"],"example_sentence":"I have to schedule a meeting with the client tomorrow.","example_es":"Tengo que programar una reunión con el cliente mañana.","example_en":"I have to schedule a meeting with the client tomorrow.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Aplazar","english_text":"Postpone","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To delay or put off something to a later time.","main_translations_es":["Posponer","Diferir","Atrasar"],"collocations":["postpone the meeting","postpone the deadline","postpone the launch","postpone the decision"],"example_sentence":"We decided to postpone the meeting until next week.","example_es":"Decidimos aplazar la reunión para la próxima semana.","example_en":"We decided to postpone the meeting until next week.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Reprogramar","english_text":"Reschedule","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To arrange for something to occur at a different time.","main_translations_es":["Posponer","Cambiar la fecha","Reagendar"],"collocations":["reschedule the meeting","reschedule an appointment","reschedule for next week","reschedule at a later date"],"example_sentence":"I will reschedule the meeting for Friday.","example_es":"Voy a reprogramar la reunión para el viernes.","example_en":"I will reschedule the meeting for Friday.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Agenda","english_text":"Agenda","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A list of items to be discussed or acted upon, especially at a meeting.","main_translations_es":["programa","calendario","planificador"],"collocations":["set the agenda","agenda item","agenda for the meeting","agenda of the day"],"example_sentence":"I checked my agenda before the meeting.","example_es":"Revisé mi agenda antes de la reunión.","example_en":"I checked my agenda before the meeting.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Punto del orden del día","english_text":"Agenda item","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A specific topic scheduled for discussion on an agenda.","main_translations_es":["Punto de la agenda","Tema del orden del día","Asunto del día"],"collocations":["add an agenda item","agenda item for discussion","agenda item number","agenda item to be addressed"],"example_sentence":"The next agenda item will be the approval of the budget.","example_es":"El siguiente punto del orden del día será la aprobación del presupuesto.","example_en":"The next agenda item will be the approval of the budget.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Acta","english_text":"Minutes","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A written record of the discussions and decisions made during a meeting.","main_translations_es":["registro","acta de reunión","minuta"],"collocations":["take minutes","meeting minutes","minutes of the meeting","record the minutes"],"example_sentence":"The minutes of the meeting were approved.","example_es":"El acta de la reunión se aprobó.","example_en":"The minutes of the meeting were approved.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Punto de acción","english_text":"Action item","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A specific task or piece of work that needs to be completed.","main_translations_es":["Elemento de acción","Tarea","Acción pendiente"],"collocations":["action item list","action item owner","action item follow‑up","action item deadline"],"example_sentence":"The action item for the next meeting is to review the budget.","example_es":"El punto de acción para la próxima reunión es revisar el presupuesto.","example_en":"The action item for the next meeting is to review the budget.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Fecha límite","english_text":"Deadline","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A date or time by which something must be completed or submitted.","main_translations_es":["Plazo","Fecha de entrega","Vencimiento"],"collocations":["meet the deadline","deadline approaching","miss the deadline","deadline extension"],"example_sentence":"The deadline to submit the report is Monday at 5 p.m.","example_es":"La fecha límite para entregar el informe es el lunes a las 5 p.m.","example_en":"The deadline to submit the report is Monday at 5 p.m.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Hito","english_text":"Milestone","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A significant event or point in development that marks progress or a turning point.","main_translations_es":["evento importante","punto de referencia","marca"],"collocations":["milestone birthday","milestone achievement","milestone event","milestone in history"],"example_sentence":"This project reached a major milestone when we completed the testing phase.","example_es":"Este proyecto alcanzó un hito importante cuando completamos la fase de pruebas.","example_en":"This project reached a major milestone when we completed the testing phase.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Entregable","english_text":"Deliverable","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A tangible or intangible item that must be completed and handed over as part of a project or contract.","main_translations_es":["producto","resultado","entrega"],"collocations":["project deliverable","deliverable deadline","deliverable item","deliverable schedule"],"example_sentence":"The deliverable must be submitted before Friday.","example_es":"El entregable debe enviarse antes del viernes.","example_en":"The deliverable must be submitted before Friday.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Carga de trabajo","english_text":"Workload","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The amount of work assigned to or expected from a person or group.","main_translations_es":["Carga laboral","Volumen de trabajo","Trabajo acumulado"],"collocations":["heavy workload","manage the workload","reduce the workload","workload increase"],"example_sentence":"My workload has increased a lot this month.","example_es":"Mi carga de trabajo ha aumentado mucho este mes.","example_en":"My workload has increased a lot this month.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Priorizar","english_text":"Prioritize","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To arrange or deal with tasks, items, or goals in order of importance, giving precedence to the most important ones.","main_translations_es":["Dar prioridad","Poner en primer lugar","Priorizar"],"collocations":["prioritize tasks","prioritize safety","prioritize customer needs"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to prioritize the most urgent tasks before starting the project.","example_es":"Es importante priorizar las tareas más urgentes antes de comenzar el proyecto.","example_en":"It''s important to prioritize the most urgent tasks before starting the project.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Escalar un problema","english_text":"Escalate an issue","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To raise an issue to a higher level of authority or attention.","main_translations_es":["Elevar un problema","Derivar un problema","Remitir un problema"],"collocations":["escalate an issue to management","escalate an issue quickly","escalate an issue when necessary","escalate an issue promptly"],"example_sentence":"If it isn''t resolved quickly, we will have to escalate an issue to the support team.","example_es":"Si no se resuelve rápidamente, tendremos que escalar un problema al equipo de soporte.","example_en":"If it isn''t resolved quickly, we will have to escalate an issue to the support team.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Resolver un problema","english_text":"Resolve an issue","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To find a solution to a problem or difficulty.","main_translations_es":["Solucionar un problema","Arreglar un problema","Encontrar una solución a un problema"],"collocations":["resolve an issue quickly","resolve an issue promptly","resolve an issue with the team","resolve an issue before deadline"],"example_sentence":"I need to resolve a problem before the meeting.","example_es":"Necesito resolver un problema antes de la reunión.","example_en":"I need to resolve a problem before the meeting.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Ponerse al día","english_text":"Catch up","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To reach the same level or position as someone else after having fallen behind.","main_translations_es":["Actualizarse","Ponerse al corriente","Poner al día"],"collocations":["catch up on","catch up with","catch up later","catch up to"],"example_sentence":"After the holidays, I had to catch up with work.","example_es":"Después de las vacaciones, tuve que ponerme al día con el trabajo.","example_en":"After the holidays, I had to catch up with work.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Informe de progreso","english_text":"Progress report","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A document that details the status and developments of a project or task.","main_translations_es":["Reporte de avance","Informe de avances","Informe de progreso"],"collocations":["submit a progress report","annual progress report","progress report template","progress report deadline"],"example_sentence":"The team submitted the progress report before the deadline.","example_es":"El equipo entregó el informe de progreso antes de la fecha límite.","example_en":"The team submitted the progress report before the deadline.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Estado actual","english_text":"Current status","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The present condition or situation of something.","main_translations_es":["Situación actual","Estado presente","Condición actual"],"collocations":["current status update","check the current status","current status report","as per the current status"],"example_sentence":"The current status of the project is uncertain.","example_es":"El estado actual del proyecto es incierto.","example_en":"The current status of the project is uncertain.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Retrasado","english_text":"Behind schedule","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"adverbial phrase","definition_en":"Later than planned or expected; not on time.","main_translations_es":["Atrasado","Demorado","Tardío"],"collocations":["fall behind schedule","get behind schedule","run behind schedule","be behind schedule"],"example_sentence":"The project is behind schedule and will not be finished on time.","example_es":"El proyecto está retrasado y no se completará a tiempo.","example_en":"The project is behind schedule and will not be finished on time.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Adelantado","english_text":"Ahead of schedule","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Occurring earlier than the planned time.","main_translations_es":["Anticipado","Previo","Por delante"],"collocations":["finish ahead of schedule","be ahead of schedule","run ahead of schedule","complete ahead of schedule"],"example_sentence":"The project is ahead of schedule and we will finish earlier than planned.","example_es":"El proyecto está adelantado y terminaremos antes de lo previsto.","example_en":"The project is ahead of schedule and we will finish earlier than planned.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cumplir el plazo","english_text":"Meet the deadline","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To complete something before or at the specified time limit.","main_translations_es":["Respetar el plazo","Entregar a tiempo","Cumplir la fecha límite"],"collocations":["to meet the deadline","hard to meet the deadline","meet the deadline on time","struggle to meet the deadline"],"example_sentence":"We have to meet the deadline to submit the report.","example_es":"Tenemos que cumplir el plazo para presentar el informe.","example_en":"We have to meet the deadline to submit the report.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Incumplir el plazo","english_text":"Miss the deadline","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To fail to meet a deadline.","main_translations_es":["No cumplir el plazo","Pasar la fecha límite","Atrasarse en la entrega"],"collocations":["miss the deadline","missed the deadline","to miss a deadline","deadline missed"],"example_sentence":"I don''t want to miss the deadline for submission.","example_es":"No quiero incumplir el plazo de entrega.","example_en":"I don''t want to miss the deadline for submission.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Disponibilidad","english_text":"Availability","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The state of being ready for use or obtainable.","main_translations_es":["Disponibilidad","Accesibilidad","Libre disponibilidad"],"collocations":["check availability","availability of resources","availability schedule","availability status"],"example_sentence":"The availability of seats is limited.","example_es":"La disponibilidad de los asientos es limitada.","example_en":"The availability of seats is limited.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Franja horaria","english_text":"Time slot","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A specific period of time allocated for an activity or appointment.","main_translations_es":["Horario","Intervalo de tiempo","Periodo"],"collocations":["book a time slot","available time slot","reserve a time slot","time slot allocation"],"example_sentence":"What is your available time slot for the meeting?","example_es":"¿Cuál es tu franja horaria disponible para la reunión?","example_en":"What is your available time slot for the meeting?","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Conflicto de horario","english_text":"Scheduling conflict","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A situation where two or more events are planned for the same time, making it impossible to attend all of them.","main_translations_es":["Conflicto de agenda","Choque de horarios","Solapamiento de horarios"],"collocations":["due to a scheduling conflict","resolve a scheduling conflict","avoid scheduling conflicts","schedule conflict"],"example_sentence":"I have a scheduling conflict and won''t be able to attend the meeting.","example_es":"Tengo un conflicto de horario y no podré asistir a la reunión.","example_en":"I have a scheduling conflict and won''t be able to attend the meeting.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Plantilla","english_text":"Template","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A pre-designed format or pattern used as a starting point for creating something.","main_translations_es":["Modelo","Formato","Plantilla"],"collocations":["template file","template design","template engine"],"example_sentence":"The template of the report is available on the intranet.","example_es":"La plantilla del informe está disponible en la intranet.","example_en":"The template of the report is available on the intranet.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Borrador","english_text":"Draft","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A preliminary version of a document or plan.","main_translations_es":["Esbozo","Boceto","Proyecto"],"collocations":["draft a letter","draft legislation","draft version","draft copy"],"example_sentence":"I will review the draft of the report before sending it.","example_es":"Voy a revisar el borrador del informe antes de enviarlo.","example_en":"I will review the draft of the report before sending it.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Presupuesto","english_text":"Budget","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A plan that estimates expected income and expenses over a specific period.","main_translations_es":["Presupuesto","Plan financiero","Estimación de costos"],"collocations":["budget plan","budget cuts","budget meeting","budget allocation"],"example_sentence":"The budget for the project was approved last week.","example_es":"El presupuesto para el proyecto se aprobó la semana pasada.","example_en":"The budget for the project was approved last week.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Previsión","english_text":"Forecast","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A prediction or estimate of future events, such as weather or economic conditions.","main_translations_es":["Pronóstico","Predicción","Proyección"],"collocations":["weather forecast","sales forecast","forecast the future"],"example_sentence":"The forecast predicts rain for tomorrow.","example_es":"La previsión del tiempo indica lluvia para mañana.","example_en":"The forecast predicts rain for tomorrow.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Estimación","english_text":"Estimate","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"An approximate calculation or judgment of the value, size, or amount of something.","main_translations_es":["Cálculo","Valoración","Aproximación"],"collocations":["estimate the cost","rough estimate","estimate the time","make an estimate"],"example_sentence":"According to the meteorologist''s estimate, it will rain tomorrow.","example_es":"Según la estimación del meteorólogo, lloverá mañana.","example_en":"According to the meteorologist''s estimate, it will rain tomorrow.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Alcance","english_text":"Scope","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the extent or range of something''s coverage, influence, or operation","main_translations_es":["Ámbito","Cobertura","Extensión"],"collocations":["out of scope","scope of work","broad scope","scope creep"],"example_sentence":"The scope of the project includes the implementation of new technologies.","example_es":"El alcance del proyecto incluye la implementación de nuevas tecnologías.","example_en":"The scope of the project includes the implementation of new technologies.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Requisito","english_text":"Requirement","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Something that is needed or demanded.","main_translations_es":["exigencia","condición","requerimiento"],"collocations":["meeting the requirement","as a requirement","requirement for","mandatory requirement"],"example_sentence":"The requirement to enroll in the course is to be at least 18 years old.","example_es":"El requisito para inscribirse en el curso es tener al menos 18 años.","example_en":"The requirement to enroll in the course is to be at least 18 years old.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Dependencia","english_text":"Dependency","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A condition in which a person, group, or thing relies on or is controlled by another for support or aid.","main_translations_es":["subordinación","adicción","sujeción"],"collocations":["dependency injection","dependency graph","dependency management","dependency relationship"],"example_sentence":"The dependency on fossil fuels is an environmental problem.","example_es":"La dependencia de los combustibles fósiles es un problema ambiental.","example_en":"The dependency on fossil fuels is an environmental problem.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cuello de botella","english_text":"Bottleneck","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A narrow point or stage that restricts flow or progress, causing a delay.","main_translations_es":["Obstáculo","Punto crítico","Cuello de botella"],"collocations":["bottleneck in production","traffic bottleneck","bottleneck effect","bottleneck situation"],"example_sentence":"The project was delayed because there was a bottleneck in production.","example_es":"El proyecto se retrasó porque hubo un cuello de botella en la producción.","example_en":"The project was delayed because there was a bottleneck in production.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Riesgo","english_text":"Risk","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the possibility of loss, injury, or other adverse outcome","main_translations_es":["peligro","amenaza","contingencia"],"collocations":["take a risk","risk assessment","risk management","high risk"],"example_sentence":"Investing in that company carries a great risk.","example_es":"Invertir en esa empresa conlleva un gran riesgo.","example_en":"Investing in that company carries a great risk.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Mitigación","english_text":"Mitigation","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The act of reducing the severity, seriousness, or harmful effects of something.","main_translations_es":["Reducción","Alivio","Atenuación"],"collocations":["risk mitigation","climate change mitigation","mitigation measures","mitigation strategies"],"example_sentence":"Mitigation of climate change requires urgent actions.","example_es":"La mitigación del cambio climático requiere acciones urgentes.","example_en":"Mitigation of climate change requires urgent actions.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Lanzamiento","english_text":"Launch","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The act of sending a product, vehicle, or spacecraft into operation or into the air.","main_translations_es":["Despegue","Salida","Emisión"],"collocations":["launch a product","launch a rocket","launch a campaign","launch into space"],"example_sentence":"The launch of the new phone will be next month.","example_es":"El lanzamiento del nuevo teléfono será el próximo mes.","example_en":"The launch of the new phone will be next month.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Despliegue","english_text":"Rollout","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The act of introducing or launching a new product, service, or system to the market or users.","main_translations_es":["Implementación","Lanzamiento","Puesta en marcha"],"collocations":["rollout plan","product rollout","rollout schedule","rollout strategy"],"example_sentence":"The rollout of the new software is scheduled for next Monday.","example_es":"El despliegue del nuevo software está programado para el próximo lunes.","example_en":"The rollout of the new software is scheduled for next Monday.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Incorporación","english_text":"Onboarding","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of integrating new employees into an organization.","main_translations_es":["Integración","Admisión","Incorporación"],"collocations":["employee onboarding","customer onboarding","onboarding process","onboarding program"],"example_sentence":"The onboarding of the new employees will take place next week.","example_es":"La incorporación de los nuevos empleados se realizará la próxima semana.","example_en":"The onboarding of the new employees will take place next week.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Capacitación","english_text":"Training","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of teaching or developing skills and knowledge.","main_translations_es":["Entrenamiento","Formación","Adiestramiento"],"collocations":["training program","on-the-job training","training session","training manual"],"example_sentence":"Staff training is essential to improve productivity.","example_es":"La capacitación del personal es esencial para mejorar la productividad.","example_en":"Staff training is essential to improve productivity.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Retroalimentación","english_text":"Feedback","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Information or reactions given about a performance, product, or behavior, used to guide improvement.","main_translations_es":["comentarios","opinión","valoración"],"collocations":["give feedback","receive feedback","constructive feedback","feedback loop"],"example_sentence":"User feedback is essential for improving the product.","example_es":"La retroalimentación de los usuarios es esencial para mejorar el producto.","example_en":"User feedback is essential for improving the product.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Evaluación de desempeño","english_text":"Performance review","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A formal assessment of an employee''s work performance.","main_translations_es":["Revisión de desempeño","Valoración del rendimiento","Análisis de desempeño"],"collocations":["annual performance review","performance review meeting","conduct a performance review","performance review process"],"example_sentence":"The performance review will take place next Monday.","example_es":"La evaluación de desempeño se realizará el próximo lunes.","example_en":"The performance review will take place next Monday.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Ascenso","english_text":"Promotion","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A promotion is the advancement of an employee to a higher position, often with increased responsibilities and pay.","main_translations_es":["Promoción","Elevación","Subida"],"collocations":["career promotion","promotion offer","promotion campaign"],"example_sentence":"After three years of hard work, he received a promotion.","example_es":"Después de tres años de trabajo duro, recibió un ascenso.","example_en":"After three years of hard work, he received a promotion.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Renuncia","english_text":"Resignation","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The act of voluntarily giving up a job or position.","main_translations_es":["Dimisión","Renuncia","Abandono"],"collocations":["letter of resignation","resignation letter","accept resignation","submit resignation"],"example_sentence":"His resignation from the position surprised everyone.","example_es":"Su renuncia al cargo sorprendió a todos.","example_en":"His resignation from the position surprised everyone.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Contratación","english_text":"Hiring","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The act of employing someone for a job.","main_translations_es":["Reclutamiento","Selección de personal","Incorporación"],"collocations":["hiring process","hiring manager","hiring freeze","hiring spree"],"example_sentence":"Hiring new employees is a priority this quarter.","example_es":"La contratación de nuevos empleados es una prioridad este trimestre.","example_en":"Hiring new employees is a priority this quarter.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Entrevista","english_text":"Interview","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A formal meeting where one person asks questions and another provides answers, often to assess suitability for a job or to gather information.","main_translations_es":["Entrevista","Charla","Entrevista laboral"],"collocations":["job interview","interview process","interview panel","interview questions"],"example_sentence":"Tomorrow I have a job interview at ten o''clock.","example_es":"Mañana tengo una entrevista de trabajo a las diez.","example_en":"Tomorrow I have a job interview at ten o''clock.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Candidato","english_text":"Candidate","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person who is seeking or being considered for a position, office, or honor.","main_translations_es":["aspirante","postulante","concursante"],"collocations":["job candidate","candidate for office","candidate selection","candidate profile"],"example_sentence":"The candidate won the election with a large majority.","example_es":"El candidato ganó las elecciones con una amplia mayoría.","example_en":"The candidate won the election with a large majority.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Vacante","english_text":"Opening","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A position or opportunity that is available, especially a job vacancy.","main_translations_es":["Puesto disponible","Posición vacante","Oferta de empleo"],"collocations":["job opening","opening ceremony","opening hours","opening statement"],"example_sentence":"There is an opening for a software engineer at the company.","example_es":"Hay una vacante para ingeniero de software en la empresa.","example_en":"There is an opening for a software engineer at the company.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Descripción del puesto","english_text":"Job description","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A written statement outlining the duties, responsibilities, and requirements of a particular job.","main_translations_es":["Perfil del puesto","Resumen del puesto","Descripción del cargo"],"collocations":["write a job description","review the job description","job description template","job description format"],"example_sentence":"The job description includes project management responsibilities.","example_es":"La descripción del puesto incluye responsabilidades de gestión de proyectos.","example_en":"The job description includes project management responsibilities.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Trabajo remoto","english_text":"Remote work","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A work arrangement in which an employee performs their job duties from a location outside the employer''s premises, typically using digital communication tools.","main_translations_es":["Teletrabajo","Trabajo a distancia","Trabajo desde casa"],"collocations":["remote work policy","remote work arrangement","remote work opportunities","remote work culture"],"example_sentence":"I work remotely from home every day.","example_es":"Trabajo remoto desde casa todos los días.","example_en":"I work remotely from home every day.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Trabajo híbrido","english_text":"Hybrid work","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A work arrangement that combines remote and on‑site duties.","main_translations_es":["Modelo híbrido de trabajo","Trabajo mixto","Trabajo a distancia y presencial"],"collocations":["hybrid work model","hybrid work arrangement","flexible hybrid work","remote and on‑site hybrid work"],"example_sentence":"I prefer hybrid work because it combines office and remote work.","example_es":"Prefiero el trabajo híbrido porque combina la oficina y el teletrabajo.","example_en":"I prefer hybrid work because it combines office and remote work.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Presencial","english_text":"On-site","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Located or occurring at the place where the activity takes place.","main_translations_es":["en persona","cara a cara","presencial"],"collocations":["on-site support","on-site training","on-site inspection","on-site meeting"],"example_sentence":"The course will be on-site, so you''ll have to attend in person.","example_es":"El curso será presencial, así que tendrás que asistir en persona.","example_en":"The course will be on-site, so you''ll have to attend in person.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Compañero de trabajo","english_text":"Coworker","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person who works with you, typically in the same organization or workplace.","main_translations_es":["Colega","Compañero de oficina","Colega de trabajo"],"collocations":["my coworker","coworker relationship","coworker collaboration","coworker support"],"example_sentence":"My coworker helped me finish the report.","example_es":"Mi compañero de trabajo me ayudó a terminar el informe.","example_en":"My coworker helped me finish the report.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Parte interesada","english_text":"Stakeholder","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person or group that has an interest or concern in something, especially a business or project.","main_translations_es":["parte interesada","interesado","grupo de interés"],"collocations":["key stakeholder","stakeholder engagement","stakeholder analysis","primary stakeholder"],"example_sentence":"The stakeholder approved the new project plan.","example_es":"La parte interesada aprobó el nuevo plan del proyecto.","example_en":"The stakeholder approved the new project plan.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cliente","english_text":"Client","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person or organization that receives professional services or purchases goods from a business.","main_translations_es":["Cliente","Comprador","Consumidor"],"collocations":["client base","client meeting","client relationship","client service"],"example_sentence":"The client requested a refund.","example_es":"El cliente pidió una devolución.","example_en":"The client requested a refund.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Proveedor","english_text":"Vendor","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person or company that sells goods or services.","main_translations_es":["Suministrador","Distribuidor","Abastecedor"],"collocations":["vendor management","preferred vendor","vendor contract","vendor list"],"example_sentence":"The vendor delivered the goods on time.","example_es":"El proveedor entregó la mercancía a tiempo.","example_en":"The vendor delivered the goods on time.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Negociar","english_text":"Negotiate","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To discuss terms and reach an agreement.","main_translations_es":["tratar","concertar","llegar a un acuerdo"],"collocations":["negotiate a deal","negotiate terms","negotiate a contract","negotiate with"],"example_sentence":"We will negotiate the terms of the contract tomorrow.","example_es":"Vamos a negociar los términos del contrato mañana.","example_en":"We will negotiate the terms of the contract tomorrow.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Llegar a un consenso","english_text":"Reach a consensus","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To arrive at a shared agreement among all parties.","main_translations_es":["Alcanzar un consenso","Lograr un consenso","Conseguir un consenso"],"collocations":["reach a consensus on","reach a consensus among stakeholders","reach a consensus quickly","reach a consensus about"],"example_sentence":"After long discussions, we finally managed to reach a consensus on the project.","example_es":"Después de largas discusiones, finalmente logramos llegar a un consenso sobre el proyecto.","example_en":"After long discussions, we finally managed to reach a consensus on the project.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Alinearse","english_text":"Align on","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to agree upon or adopt a common position or plan","main_translations_es":["coordinarse","ponerse de acuerdo","ajustarse"],"collocations":["align on goals","align on strategy","align on expectations","align on priorities"],"example_sentence":"The teams must align on the company''s objectives.","example_es":"Los equipos deben alinearse con los objetivos de la empresa.","example_en":"The teams must align on the company''s objectives.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Aclarar expectativas","english_text":"Clarify expectations","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To make the expectations clear.","main_translations_es":["Alinear expectativas","Establecer expectativas claras","Definir expectativas"],"collocations":["clarify expectations with the team","clarify expectations early","clarify expectations beforehand"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to clarify expectations before starting the project.","example_es":"Es importante aclarar expectativas antes de iniciar el proyecto.","example_en":"It''s important to clarify expectations before starting the project.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Asumir responsabilidad","english_text":"Take ownership","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To accept responsibility for something.","main_translations_es":["Asumir la responsabilidad","Hacerse cargo","Responsabilizarse"],"collocations":["take ownership of the project","take ownership of your actions","take ownership and lead","take ownership of the issue"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to take ownership of your mistakes.","example_es":"Es importante asumir responsabilidad por tus errores.","example_en":"It''s important to take ownership of your mistakes.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Delegar","english_text":"Delegate","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To entrust a task or responsibility to another person.","main_translations_es":["Encargar","Asignar","Transferir"],"collocations":["delegate authority","delegate tasks","delegate responsibilities","delegate decision‑making"],"example_sentence":"I learned to delegate tasks to be more efficient.","example_es":"Aprendí a delegar tareas para ser más eficiente.","example_en":"I learned to delegate tasks to be more efficient.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Transferir una tarea","english_text":"Hand over a task","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To give responsibility for a task to someone else.","main_translations_es":["Ceder una tarea","Entregar una tarea","Pasar una tarea"],"collocations":["hand over a task to a colleague","hand over the task","hand over tasks","hand over the responsibility"],"example_sentence":"I will hand over a task to my colleague so they can finish it sooner.","example_es":"Voy a transferir una tarea a mi colega para que la termine antes.","example_en":"I will hand over a task to my colleague so they can finish it sooner.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Aprobar","english_text":"Approve","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To officially accept or give consent to something.","main_translations_es":["Autorizar","Ratificar","Aceptar"],"collocations":["approve of","approve the budget","give approval","receive approval"],"example_sentence":"The committee decided to approve the new policy.","example_es":"El comité decidió aprobar la nueva política.","example_en":"The committee decided to approve the new policy.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Rechazar","english_text":"Reject","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To refuse to accept, consider, or agree with something.","main_translations_es":["Denegar","Rehusar","Rechazar"],"collocations":["reject the proposal","reject the offer","reject the hypothesis","reject the application"],"example_sentence":"The committee decided to reject the proposed tariff increase.","example_es":"El comité decidió rechazar la propuesta de aumento de tarifas.","example_en":"The committee decided to reject the proposed tariff increase.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Revisar","english_text":"Review","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To examine or assess something again or in detail.","main_translations_es":["Repasar","Examinar","Corregir"],"collocations":["review the literature","performance review","review meeting","review process"],"example_sentence":"I will review the report before sending it.","example_es":"Voy a revisar el informe antes de enviarlo.","example_en":"I will review the report before sending it.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Redactar","english_text":"Draft","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To prepare a preliminary version of a document or text.","main_translations_es":["Escribir","Elaborar","Redactar"],"collocations":["draft a letter","draft a proposal","draft an email","draft a contract"],"example_sentence":"I will draft the report before the meeting.","example_es":"Voy a redactar el informe antes de la reunión.","example_en":"I will draft the report before the meeting.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Resumir","english_text":"Summarize","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give a brief statement of the main points of something.","main_translations_es":["Sintetizar","Hacer un resumen","Abreviar"],"collocations":["summarize the main points","summarize the findings","summarize the report","summarize briefly"],"example_sentence":"Please summarize the article in three sentences.","example_es":"Por favor, resume el artículo en tres frases.","example_en":"Please summarize the article in three sentences.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Destacar","english_text":"Highlight","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To emphasize or make something stand out.","main_translations_es":["Resaltar","Subrayar","Enfatizar"],"collocations":["highlight the main points","highlight a problem","highlight in yellow","highlight the differences"],"example_sentence":"The report should highlight last year''s achievements.","example_es":"El informe debe destacar los logros del año pasado.","example_en":"The report should highlight last year''s achievements.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Plantear una inquietud","english_text":"Raise a concern","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To bring up or express a worry or issue.","main_translations_es":["Expresar una inquietud","Manifestar una preocupación","Elevar una queja"],"collocations":["raise a concern about","raise a concern with","raise a concern to","raise a concern regarding"],"example_sentence":"I wanted to raise a concern about the new work schedule.","example_es":"Quería plantear una inquietud sobre el nuevo horario de trabajo.","example_en":"I wanted to raise a concern about the new work schedule.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Abordar un asunto","english_text":"Address an issue","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To deal with or discuss a problem or topic.","main_translations_es":["Tratar un tema","Enfrentar un problema","Lidiar con un asunto"],"collocations":["address an issue promptly","address an issue head-on","address an issue in the meeting","address an issue with management"],"example_sentence":"We need to address the issue of safety in the company as soon as possible.","example_es":"Necesitamos abordar el asunto de la seguridad en la empresa lo antes posible.","example_en":"We need to address the issue of safety in the company as soon as possible.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cumplir con el seguimiento","english_text":"Follow through","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To continue an action or plan until it is completed.","main_translations_es":["dar seguimiento","realizar el seguimiento","llevar a cabo el seguimiento"],"collocations":["follow through on a promise","follow through with a plan","follow through on commitments"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to follow through with patient follow-up after surgery.","example_es":"Es importante cumplir con el seguimiento de los pacientes después de la cirugía.","example_en":"It''s important to follow through with patient follow-up after surgery.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cerrar el circuito","english_text":"Close the loop","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To complete a process by providing the missing information or final step.","main_translations_es":["Completar el circuito","Cerrar el lazo","Finalizar el circuito"],"collocations":["close the loop on","close the loop with","close the loop in the process","close the loop for feedback"],"example_sentence":"To prevent a short circuit, we must close the loop before turning on the device.","example_es":"Para evitar el cortocircuito, debemos cerrar el circuito antes de encender el dispositivo.","example_en":"To prevent a short circuit, we must close the loop before turning on the device.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Mantener informado","english_text":"Keep posted","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"To keep someone informed about developments.","main_translations_es":["Mantener al tanto","Mantener al corriente","Mantener informado"],"collocations":["keep me posted","keep us posted","keep them posted"],"example_sentence":"Please keep the customers posted about the schedule changes.","example_es":"Por favor, mantén a los clientes informados sobre los cambios en el horario.","example_en":"Please keep the customers posted about the schedule changes.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Hilo de correo","english_text":"Email thread","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A series of related email messages that share the same subject line, showing the progression of a conversation.","main_translations_es":["Cadena de correo","Conversación de correo","Hilo de email"],"collocations":["follow the email thread","reply to the email thread","email thread history","email thread view"],"example_sentence":"I reviewed the email thread to find the information I needed.","example_es":"Revisé el hilo de correo para encontrar la información que necesitaba.","example_en":"I reviewed the email thread to find the information I needed.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Llamada breve","english_text":"Quick call","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"A brief telephone conversation.","main_translations_es":["Llamada corta","Llamada rápida","Llamada breve"],"collocations":["give me a quick call","quick call back","quick call to discuss","schedule a quick call"],"example_sentence":"I''ll make a quick call to confirm the time.","example_es":"Haré una llamada breve para confirmar la hora.","example_en":"I''ll make a quick call to confirm the time.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Reunión individual","english_text":"One-on-one meeting","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A private meeting between two individuals, often a manager and an employee, conducted face‑to‑face.","main_translations_es":["Entrevista individual","Reunión cara a cara","Reunión personal"],"collocations":["schedule a one-on-one meeting","have a one-on-one meeting","one-on-one meeting agenda","one-on-one meeting follow-up"],"example_sentence":"I have a one-on-one meeting with my supervisor tomorrow at ten.","example_es":"Tengo una reunión individual con mi supervisor mañana a las diez.","example_en":"I have a one-on-one meeting with my supervisor tomorrow at ten.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sesión de lluvia de ideas","english_text":"Brainstorming session","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A meeting where participants generate ideas and solutions through spontaneous discussion.","main_translations_es":["Sesión creativa","Reunión de ideas","Jornada de lluvia de ideas"],"collocations":["kick off the brainstorming session","schedule a brainstorming session","productive brainstorming session","brainstorming session agenda"],"example_sentence":"Tomorrow we will have a brainstorming session to improve the product.","example_es":"Mañana tendremos una sesión de lluvia de ideas para mejorar el producto.","example_en":"Tomorrow we will have a brainstorming session to improve the product.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Presentación","english_text":"Presentation","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A formal introduction or display of information, such as a talk, demonstration, or visual material.","main_translations_es":["Exposición","Introducción","Charla"],"collocations":["make a presentation","give a presentation","presentation slides","presentation skills"],"example_sentence":"The presentation of the project was very clear.","example_es":"La presentación del proyecto fue muy clara.","example_en":"The presentation of the project was very clear.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Diapositiva","english_text":"Slide","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A single page of a presentation, typically shown on a screen.","main_translations_es":["diapositiva","lámina","transparencia"],"collocations":["slide show","slide deck","slide transition","slide into"],"example_sentence":"The slide shows the results of the experiment.","example_es":"La diapositiva muestra los resultados del experimento.","example_en":"The slide shows the results of the experiment.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Propuesta","english_text":"Proposal","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A plan or suggestion put forward for consideration or discussion.","main_translations_es":["Propuesta","Oferta","Iniciativa"],"collocations":["proposal for","proposal to","proposal was accepted","proposal meeting"],"example_sentence":"The committee''s proposal was approved unanimously.","example_es":"La propuesta del comité fue aprobada por unanimidad.","example_en":"The committee''s proposal was approved unanimously.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Factura","english_text":"Invoice","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A document itemizing goods or services provided and requesting payment.","main_translations_es":["Factura","Recibo","Comprobante"],"collocations":["invoice number","invoice date","invoice amount","invoice processing"],"example_sentence":"I need you to send me the invoice before Friday.","example_es":"Necesito que me envíes la factura antes del viernes.","example_en":"I need you to send me the invoice before Friday.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Orden de compra","english_text":"Purchase order","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A document issued by a buyer to a seller specifying the items, quantities, and agreed prices for a purchase.","main_translations_es":["Pedido de compra","Orden de adquisición","Solicitud de compra"],"collocations":["issue a purchase order","purchase order number","receive a purchase order","purchase order form"],"example_sentence":"I need to send the purchase order to the supplier before Friday.","example_es":"Necesito enviar la orden de compra al proveedor antes del viernes.","example_en":"I need to send the purchase order to the supplier before Friday.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Reembolso","english_text":"Reimbursement","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A repayment of money that has been spent or lost, typically to cover incurred expenses.","main_translations_es":["devolución","reintegro","restitución"],"collocations":["reimbursement claim","reimbursement policy","reimbursement request","reimbursement form"],"example_sentence":"I requested the reimbursement for my purchase because the product was defective.","example_es":"Solicité el reembolso de mi compra porque el producto estaba defectuoso.","example_en":"I requested the reimbursement for my purchase because the product was defective.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Baja médica","english_text":"Sick leave","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A period of time when an employee is permitted to be absent from work due to illness.","main_translations_es":["incapacidad laboral","permiso médico","licencia por enfermedad"],"collocations":["take sick leave","apply for sick leave","on sick leave","sick leave policy"],"example_sentence":"After the surgery, he needed a sick leave of two weeks.","example_es":"Después de la operación, necesitó una baja médica de dos semanas.","example_en":"After the surgery, he needed a sick leave of two weeks.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Vacaciones","english_text":"Annual leave","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Paid time off from work that an employee is entitled to each year.","main_translations_es":["Descanso","Periodo vacacional","Tiempo libre"],"collocations":["take annual leave","annual leave entitlement","annual leave balance","annual leave request"],"example_sentence":"I am going to take my annual leave next week.","example_es":"Voy a tomar mis vacaciones la próxima semana.","example_en":"I am going to take my annual leave next week.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Permiso de ausencia","english_text":"Leave of absence","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A period of time when someone is permitted to be away from work or school.","main_translations_es":["Licencia de ausencia","Permiso de ausencia","Licencia por ausencia"],"collocations":["take a leave of absence","apply for a leave of absence","grant a leave of absence","request a leave of absence"],"example_sentence":"I requested a leave of absence to take care of my family.","example_es":"Solicité un permiso de ausencia para poder atender a mi familia.","example_en":"I requested a leave of absence to take care of my family.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Período de prueba","english_text":"Probation period","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A designated span of time during which an employee''s performance is evaluated before confirming permanent employment.","main_translations_es":["Periodo de prueba","Plazo de prueba","Tiempo de prueba"],"collocations":["serve a probation period","complete a probation period","during the probation period","after the probation period"],"example_sentence":"The new employee will start his probation period next week.","example_es":"El nuevo empleado comenzará su período de prueba la próxima semana.","example_en":"The new employee will start his probation period next week.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Objetivo trimestral","english_text":"Quarterly goal","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A target or objective set to be achieved within a three-month period.","main_translations_es":["Meta trimestral","Objetivo de tres meses","Propósito trimestral"],"collocations":["set a quarterly goal","achieve the quarterly goal","review the quarterly goal","track quarterly goals"],"example_sentence":"Our quarterly goal is to increase sales by 10%.","example_es":"Nuestro objetivo trimestral es aumentar las ventas en un 10 %.","example_en":"Our quarterly goal is to increase sales by 10%.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Indicador clave de rendimiento","english_text":"Key performance indicator","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A measurable value that shows how effectively an organization is achieving its key objectives.","main_translations_es":["Indicador clave de desempeño","Indicador de rendimiento clave","Indicador principal de rendimiento"],"collocations":["track key performance indicators","key performance indicator dashboard","key performance indicator metrics","key performance indicator framework"],"example_sentence":"The company''s key performance indicator shows a 15% improvement in productivity.","example_es":"El indicador clave de rendimiento de la empresa muestra una mejora del 15% en la productividad.","example_en":"The company''s key performance indicator shows a 15% improvement in productivity.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Resultado medible","english_text":"Measurable outcome","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"A result that can be quantified or assessed.","main_translations_es":["Resultado cuantificable","Resultado evaluable","Resultado medible"],"collocations":["achieve a measurable outcome","track measurable outcomes","set measurable outcomes","measure the outcome"],"example_sentence":"Measurable outcome is essential to evaluate the project''s success.","example_es":"Resultado medible es esencial para evaluar el éxito del proyecto.","example_en":"Measurable outcome is essential to evaluate the project''s success.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Crecimiento profesional","english_text":"Professional growth","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of developing skills, knowledge, and experience in one''s career.","main_translations_es":["Desarrollo profesional","Avance profesional","Progresión profesional"],"collocations":["professional growth opportunities","continuous professional growth","personal and professional growth","professional growth plan"],"example_sentence":"Professional growth depends on continuous training.","example_es":"El crecimiento profesional depende de la capacitación continua.","example_en":"Professional growth depends on continuous training.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Toma de decisiones","english_text":"Decision-making","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of identifying and choosing among alternatives.","main_translations_es":["Proceso de decisión","Toma de decisiones","Decisión"],"collocations":["decision-making process","decision-making skills","decision-making authority","decision-making style"],"example_sentence":"Decision-making is crucial in project management.","example_es":"La toma de decisiones es crucial en la gestión de proyectos.","example_en":"Decision-making is crucial in project management.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Autorizar","english_text":"Authorize","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give official permission or authority to someone to perform an action.","main_translations_es":["Permitir","Aprobar","Dar autorización"],"collocations":["authorize a transaction","authorize access","authorize a payment"],"example_sentence":"The manager must authorize the expense before it is made.","example_es":"El gerente debe autorizar el gasto antes de que se realice.","example_en":"The manager must authorize the expense before it is made.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Asignar recursos","english_text":"Allocate resources","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To distribute or assign resources to particular tasks or purposes.","main_translations_es":["Distribuir recursos","Destinar recursos","Repartir recursos"],"collocations":["allocate resources wisely","allocate resources efficiently","allocate resources to projects","allocate resources for development"],"example_sentence":"The manager decided to allocate resources to the research project.","example_es":"El gerente decidió asignar recursos al proyecto de investigación.","example_en":"The manager decided to allocate resources to the research project.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Mantener el rumbo","english_text":"Stay on track","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"To continue doing something in the correct direction or according to a plan.","main_translations_es":["Seguir el rumbo","Mantener la dirección","No perder el norte"],"collocations":["stay on track with your goals","stay on track during the meeting","stay on track and avoid setbacks"],"example_sentence":"To finish the project on time, we need to stay on track and not deviate.","example_es":"Para terminar el proyecto a tiempo, debemos mantener el rumbo y no desviarnos.","example_en":"To finish the project on time, we need to stay on track and not deviate.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Desviarse del plan","english_text":"Go off track","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To deviate from the intended plan or course.","main_translations_es":["Salir del plan","Apartarse del plan","Desviarse del objetivo"],"collocations":["go off track during a meeting","go off track with the project","go off track easily"],"example_sentence":"We must not go off track.","example_es":"No debemos desviarnos del plan.","example_en":"We must not go off track.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Necesita revisión","english_text":"Needs revision","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"Requires further review or correction.","main_translations_es":["Requiere revisión","Precisa revisión","Debe revisarse"],"collocations":["This document needs revision","Your essay needs revision","The policy needs revision"],"example_sentence":"The report needs revision before sending it.","example_es":"El informe necesita revisión antes de enviarlo.","example_en":"The report needs revision before sending it.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Urgente","english_text":"Urgent","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"requiring immediate attention or action","main_translations_es":["Apremiante","Inmediato","Prioritario"],"collocations":["urgent care","urgent matter","urgent request","urgent need"],"example_sentence":"I need you to send me the report as soon as possible; it''s urgent.","example_es":"Necesito que me envíes el informe lo antes posible, es urgente.","example_en":"I need you to send me the report as soon as possible; it''s urgent.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Alta prioridad","english_text":"High priority","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Something that is considered very important and should be dealt with before other matters.","main_translations_es":["Prioridad alta","Máxima prioridad","Prioridad máxima"],"collocations":["high priority task","high priority issue","high priority item","high priority list"],"example_sentence":"This project is of high priority for the company.","example_es":"Este proyecto es de alta prioridad para la empresa.","example_en":"This project is of high priority for the company.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Baja prioridad","english_text":"Low priority","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"Something that is considered less important or urgent than other items.","main_translations_es":["Prioridad baja","Prioridad reducida","Prioridad menor"],"collocations":["set to low priority","treated as low priority","low priority task","low priority issue"],"example_sentence":"This ticket has low priority, so we can address it later.","example_es":"Este ticket tiene baja prioridad, así que podemos atenderlo más tarde.","example_en":"This ticket has low priority, so we can address it later.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Punto de contacto","english_text":"Point of contact","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person or place that serves as the primary source of communication or information.","main_translations_es":["Persona de contacto","Contacto principal","Referente"],"collocations":["primary point of contact","main point of contact","single point of contact","designated point of contact"],"example_sentence":"For any questions, please contact Maria, who will be your point of contact.","example_es":"Para cualquier duda, por favor contacte a María, quien será su punto de contacto.","example_en":"For any questions, please contact Maria, who will be your point of contact.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Compartir pantalla","english_text":"Share the screen","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To display one''s computer screen to others, typically during a video call or presentation.","main_translations_es":["Compartir la pantalla","Mostrar la pantalla","Proyección de pantalla"],"collocations":["share the screen with the team","share the screen during the meeting","share the screen on Zoom","share the screen for a presentation"],"example_sentence":"I need to share the screen during the meeting.","example_es":"Necesito compartir pantalla durante la reunión.","example_en":"I need to share the screen during the meeting.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Silenciar el micrófono","english_text":"Mute the microphone","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To turn off or lower the microphone''s sound so it cannot be heard.","main_translations_es":["Desactivar el micrófono","Apagar el micrófono","Poner en silencio el micrófono"],"collocations":["Please mute the microphone","Remember to mute the microphone","He forgot to mute the microphone"],"example_sentence":"You can mute the microphone if you don''t want to be heard.","example_es":"Puedes silenciar el micrófono si no quieres que te escuchen.","example_en":"You can mute the microphone if you don''t want to be heard.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Conectarse a la reunión","english_text":"Join the meeting","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To connect to or participate in a scheduled meeting.","main_translations_es":["Unirse a la reunión","Entrar a la reunión","Conectar a la reunión"],"collocations":["join the meeting on time","join the meeting via Zoom","join the meeting early","join the meeting tomorrow"],"example_sentence":"I need to join the meeting at ten in the morning.","example_es":"Necesito conectarme a la reunión a las diez de la mañana.","example_en":"I need to join the meeting at ten in the morning.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Abandonar la reunión","english_text":"Leave the meeting","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To exit or depart from a meeting.","main_translations_es":["Salir de la reunión","Irse de la reunión","Dejar la reunión"],"collocations":["to leave the meeting early","to leave the meeting abruptly","to leave the meeting without notice"],"example_sentence":"I''m going to leave the meeting because it''s getting late.","example_es":"Voy a abandonar la reunión porque ya es tarde.","example_en":"I''m going to leave the meeting because it''s getting late.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Tomar nota","english_text":"Take notes","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To write down information for later reference.","main_translations_es":["Anotar","Hacer anotaciones","Apuntar"],"collocations":["take notes during the lecture","take notes on the meeting","take notes for later"],"example_sentence":"During the class, you should take notes of everything the teacher says.","example_es":"Durante la clase, debes tomar nota de todo lo que el profesor dice.","example_en":"During the class, you should take notes of everything the teacher says.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Hacer una demostración","english_text":"Give a demo","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To present a demonstration of something, typically showing how it works.","main_translations_es":["Realizar una demostración","Mostrar una demo","Presentar una demostración"],"collocations":["give a demo of the product","give a demo to the client","give a demo during the meeting"],"example_sentence":"I''m going to give a demo of the new software to the team.","example_es":"Voy a hacer una demostración del nuevo software para el equipo.","example_en":"I''m going to give a demo of the new software to the team.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Próximos pasos","english_text":"Next steps","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A set of actions or tasks that should be taken after the current point.","main_translations_es":["Pasos siguientes","Siguientes pasos","Próximas acciones"],"collocations":["next steps in the process","next steps for implementation","next steps after the meeting","next steps to take"],"example_sentence":"The next steps are to review the report and present the results.","example_es":"Los próximos pasos son revisar el informe y presentar los resultados.","example_en":"The next steps are to review the report and present the results.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Prórroga","english_text":"Extension","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A continuation or prolongation of something, especially a period of time.","main_translations_es":["prórroga","aplazamiento","extensión"],"collocations":["extension cord","extension deadline","extension of a loan","extension service"],"example_sentence":"The referee granted a five‑minute extension to the game.","example_es":"El árbitro concedió una prórroga de cinco minutos al partido.","example_en":"The referee granted a five‑minute extension to the game.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Solución alternativa","english_text":"Workaround","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A method for overcoming a problem or limitation in a system.","main_translations_es":["Alternativa","Solución provisional","Método alternativo"],"collocations":["find a workaround","temporary workaround","implement a workaround","workaround solution"],"example_sentence":"We implemented a workaround while the team fixes the bug.","example_es":"Implementamos una solución alternativa mientras el equipo corrige el error.","example_en":"We implemented a workaround while the team fixes the bug.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Bloqueador","english_text":"Blocker","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person or thing that prevents progress or blocks something.","main_translations_es":["Obstáculo","Inhibidor","Bloqueador"],"collocations":["ad blocker","traffic blocker","blocker issue","blocker task"],"example_sentence":"He installed an ad blocker to avoid intrusive ads.","example_es":"Instaló un bloqueador de anuncios para evitar la publicidad intrusiva.","example_en":"He installed an ad blocker to avoid intrusive ads.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Disponibilidad inmediata","english_text":"Immediate availability","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"The state of being ready for use right away.","main_translations_es":["Disponibilidad al instante","Disponibilidad sin demora","Disponibilidad inmediata"],"collocations":["subject to immediate availability","with immediate availability","immediate availability of"],"example_sentence":"I have immediate availability to start working.","example_es":"Tengo disponibilidad inmediata para comenzar a trabajar.","example_en":"I have immediate availability to start working.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Entorno de pruebas","english_text":"Test environment","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A setting or system used to conduct testing of software or processes.","main_translations_es":["Ambiente de pruebas","Entorno de test","Ambiente de test"],"collocations":["set up a test environment","test environment configuration","test environment variables","test environment setup"],"example_sentence":"The team set up the test environment before releasing the new version.","example_es":"El equipo configuró el entorno de pruebas antes de lanzar la nueva versión.","example_en":"The team set up the test environment before releasing the new version.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Entorno de producción","english_text":"Production environment","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The setting where software or a system is operated for real users, as opposed to testing or development.","main_translations_es":["Entorno de producción","Ambiente de producción","Entorno productivo"],"collocations":["deploy to production environment","production environment setup","production environment monitoring"],"example_sentence":"The software was deployed to the production environment after testing.","example_es":"El software se desplegó en el entorno de producción después de las pruebas.","example_en":"The software was deployed to the production environment after testing.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cadena de aprobación","english_text":"Approval chain","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A sequence of individuals or steps required to give approval for a decision or document.","main_translations_es":["cadena de autorización","flujo de aprobación","cadena de validación"],"collocations":["establish an approval chain","approval chain process","manage the approval chain","approval chain hierarchy"],"example_sentence":"For the project, we follow an approval chain before launching the product.","example_es":"Para el proyecto, seguimos una cadena de aprobación antes de lanzar el producto.","example_en":"For the project, we follow an approval chain before launching the product.","mnemonic_en":null}]'::jsonb) as x(
  spanish_text text, english_text text, section_name text, part_of_speech text, definition_en text,
  main_translations_es jsonb, collocations jsonb, example_sentence text, example_es text, example_en text, mnemonic_en text
)
where not exists (
  select 1 from public.cards c2
  where c2.deck_id = dk.id
    and lower(c2.spanish_text) = lower(x.spanish_text)
    and lower(c2.english_text) = lower(x.english_text)
);

-- english-academic-english (107 cards)
insert into public.decks (slug, title, description, language_from, language_to)
values ('english-academic-english', 'Academic English', 'Upper-intermediate and advanced academic vocabulary for essays, reports, presentations, and formal discussion.', 'es', 'en')
on conflict (slug) do nothing;

insert into public.cards (deck_id, spanish_text, english_text, is_enabled, generation_phase, generation_metadata, section_name, part_of_speech, definition_en, main_translations_es, collocations, example_sentence, example_es, example_en, mnemonic_en)
select dk.id, x.spanish_text, x.english_text, true, 'refined', '{}'::jsonb, x.section_name, x.part_of_speech, x.definition_en,
       coalesce(x.main_translations_es, '[]'::jsonb), coalesce(x.collocations, '[]'::jsonb), x.example_sentence, x.example_es, x.example_en, x.mnemonic_en
from (select id from public.decks where slug = 'english-academic-english') dk
cross join jsonb_to_recordset('[{"spanish_text":"Hipótesis","english_text":"Hypothesis","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A proposed explanation for a phenomenon that can be tested through observation or experiment.","main_translations_es":["Suposición","Conjetura","Teoría"],"collocations":["test the hypothesis","form a hypothesis","null hypothesis","working hypothesis"],"example_sentence":"My hypothesis is that the rise in temperature affects bird migration.","example_es":"Mi hipótesis es que el aumento de la temperatura afecta la migración de las aves.","example_en":"My hypothesis is that the rise in temperature affects bird migration.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Variable","english_text":"Variable","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A symbol or quantity that can change or take on different values.","main_translations_es":["Variable","Cambiante","Inestable"],"collocations":["variable cost","variable rate","variable speed","variable temperature"],"example_sentence":"The temperature is variable in this region.","example_es":"La temperatura es variable en esta región.","example_en":"The temperature is variable in this region.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Metodología","english_text":"Methodology","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A systematic set of methods and principles used in a particular field of study or practice.","main_translations_es":["Método","Procedimiento","Enfoque"],"collocations":["research methodology","methodology section","methodology of the study"],"example_sentence":"The methodology the researcher used ensured reliable results.","example_es":"La metodología que utilizó el investigador garantizó resultados fiables.","example_en":"The methodology the researcher used ensured reliable results.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Revisión bibliográfica","english_text":"Literature review","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A comprehensive summary and analysis of existing research and publications on a particular topic.","main_translations_es":["Revisión de la literatura","Estado del arte","Análisis bibliográfico"],"collocations":["conduct a literature review","comprehensive literature review","literature review section","literature review methodology"],"example_sentence":"For my thesis, I conducted an exhaustive literature review of recent studies.","example_es":"Para mi tesis, realicé una revisión bibliográfica exhaustiva de los estudios recientes.","example_en":"For my thesis, I conducted an exhaustive literature review of recent studies.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Revisión por pares","english_text":"Peer review","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A process in which experts evaluate each other''s work, such as academic articles, to ensure quality and validity.","main_translations_es":["Evaluación por pares","Revisión entre colegas","Revisión de pares"],"collocations":["peer review process","peer review article","peer review system","peer review committee"],"example_sentence":"Peer review is essential to ensure the quality of scientific articles.","example_es":"La revisión por pares es esencial para garantizar la calidad de los artículos científicos.","example_en":"Peer review is essential to ensure the quality of scientific articles.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Empírico","english_text":"Empirical","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Based on observation or experience rather than theory or pure logic.","main_translations_es":["basado en la experiencia","práctico","experimental"],"collocations":["empirical evidence","empirical data","empirical research","empirical study"],"example_sentence":"The empirical method relies on direct observation of phenomena.","example_es":"El método empírico se basa en la observación directa de los fenómenos.","example_en":"The empirical method relies on direct observation of phenomena.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cualitativo","english_text":"Qualitative","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"relating to the qualities or characteristics of something rather than its quantity","main_translations_es":["cualitativo","de carácter cualitativo","de naturaleza cualitativa"],"collocations":["qualitative analysis","qualitative research","qualitative data","qualitative methods"],"example_sentence":"The study used a qualitative approach to understand patients'' experiences.","example_es":"El estudio utilizó un enfoque cualitativo para comprender las experiencias de los pacientes.","example_en":"The study used a qualitative approach to understand patients'' experiences.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cuantitativo","english_text":"Quantitative","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Relating to, measuring, or expressed in terms of quantity.","main_translations_es":["de tipo cuantitativo","numérico","medible"],"collocations":["quantitative analysis","quantitative research","quantitative data","quantitative methods"],"example_sentence":"The quantitative analysis showed a 15% increase in sales.","example_es":"El análisis cuantitativo mostró un aumento del 15% en las ventas.","example_en":"The quantitative analysis showed a 15% increase in sales.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Tamaño de la muestra","english_text":"Sample size","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The number of observations or items included in a statistical sample.","main_translations_es":["Tamaño muestral","Número de muestra","Tamaño de la muestra"],"collocations":["determine the sample size","increase the sample size","sample size calculation","optimal sample size"],"example_sentence":"The sample size must be large enough to obtain reliable results.","example_es":"El tamaño de la muestra debe ser suficientemente grande para obtener resultados fiables.","example_en":"The sample size must be large enough to obtain reliable results.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Hallazgos","english_text":"Findings","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Results or conclusions drawn from an investigation or study.","main_translations_es":["Descubrimientos","Resultados","Conclusiones"],"collocations":["research findings","key findings","preliminary findings","significant findings"],"example_sentence":"The findings of the study suggest that diet affects cardiovascular health.","example_es":"Los hallazgos del estudio sugieren que la dieta afecta la salud cardiovascular.","example_en":"The findings of the study suggest that diet affects cardiovascular health.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Implicaciones","english_text":"Implications","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The possible results or effects that may follow from an action, decision, or event.","main_translations_es":["Consecuencias","Repercusiones","Efectos"],"collocations":["the implications of","far‑reaching implications","implications for","implications on"],"example_sentence":"The implications of his decision will be felt throughout the company.","example_es":"Las implicaciones de su decisión se sentirán en toda la empresa.","example_en":"The implications of his decision will be felt throughout the company.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Limitaciones","english_text":"Limitations","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Restrictions or constraints that limit what can be done or achieved.","main_translations_es":["Restricciones","Límites","Condiciones"],"collocations":["limitations of the study","legal limitations","technical limitations","limitations and constraints"],"example_sentence":"The limitations of the new software are evident in its performance.","example_es":"Las limitaciones del nuevo software son evidentes en su rendimiento.","example_en":"The limitations of the new software are evident in its performance.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Marco teórico","english_text":"Theoretical framework","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A set of concepts and theories that provides a basis for understanding and analyzing a particular research topic.","main_translations_es":["Marco teórico","Marco conceptual","Marco de referencia"],"collocations":["develop a theoretical framework","theoretical framework of the study","underlying theoretical framework","theoretical framework and methodology"],"example_sentence":"The theoretical framework of the study is based on contemporary sociological theories.","example_es":"El marco teórico del estudio se basa en teorías sociológicas contemporáneas.","example_en":"The theoretical framework of the study is based on contemporary sociological theories.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Investigación previa","english_text":"Previous research","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Research that has been conducted earlier on a given topic.","main_translations_es":["Estudio previo","Investigación preliminar","Revisión previa"],"collocations":["according to previous research","build on previous research","previous research has shown","previous research indicates"],"example_sentence":"Previous research suggests that the method is effective.","example_es":"La investigación previa sugiere que el método es efectivo.","example_en":"Previous research suggests that the method is effective.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cuerpo de evidencia","english_text":"Body of evidence","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"A collection of facts, testimony, or other information that together support a particular conclusion or argument.","main_translations_es":["Conjunto de pruebas","Cuerpo probatorio","Colección de evidencia"],"collocations":["a substantial body of evidence","the body of evidence suggests","the body of evidence points to","the body of evidence is compelling"],"example_sentence":"The body of evidence presented at the trial was sufficient to convict the defendant.","example_es":"El cuerpo de evidencia presentado en el juicio fue suficiente para condenar al acusado.","example_en":"The body of evidence presented at the trial was sufficient to convict the defendant.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Conjunto de datos","english_text":"Dataset","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A collection of data, typically organized for analysis or reference.","main_translations_es":["Conjunto de datos","Base de datos","Colección de datos"],"collocations":["large dataset","training dataset","public dataset","dataset analysis"],"example_sentence":"The dataset contains information about household energy consumption.","example_es":"El conjunto de datos contiene información sobre el consumo energético de los hogares.","example_en":"The dataset contains information about household energy consumption.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Interpretar","english_text":"Interpret","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To explain the meaning of something, or to understand and convey it in a particular way.","main_translations_es":["Interpretar","Entender","Descifrar"],"collocations":["interpret the data","interpret a text","interpret the results","interpret the meaning"],"example_sentence":"The translator must interpret the text accurately.","example_es":"El traductor debe interpretar el texto con precisión.","example_en":"The translator must interpret the text accurately.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Analizar","english_text":"Analyze","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To examine methodically by breaking something into its components and studying their relationships.","main_translations_es":["Examinar","Estudiar","Evaluar"],"collocations":["analyze data","analyze the results","analyze the situation","analyze trends"],"example_sentence":"Scientists must analyze the data before publishing their conclusions.","example_es":"Los científicos deben analizar los datos antes de publicar sus conclusiones.","example_en":"Scientists must analyze the data before publishing their conclusions.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sintetizar","english_text":"Synthesize","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To combine different ideas, information, or substances into a unified whole.","main_translations_es":["Resumir","Compilar","Integrar"],"collocations":["synthesize information","synthesize data","synthesize findings","synthesize ideas"],"example_sentence":"The chemist managed to synthesize a new molecule in the lab.","example_es":"El químico logró sintetizar una nueva molécula en el laboratorio.","example_en":"The chemist managed to synthesize a new molecule in the lab.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Evaluar","english_text":"Evaluate","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To assess or judge the value, quality, or significance of something.","main_translations_es":["Valorar","Calificar","Analizar"],"collocations":["evaluate the results","evaluate the performance","evaluate the data","evaluate the situation"],"example_sentence":"The committee must evaluate the experiment''s results before publishing the report.","example_es":"El comité debe evaluar los resultados del experimento antes de publicar el informe.","example_en":"The committee must evaluate the experiment''s results before publishing the report.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Criticar","english_text":"Critique","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A detailed analysis and assessment of something, especially a work of art, literature, or performance.","main_translations_es":["Reprochar","Censurar","Juzgar"],"collocations":["constructive critique","critical review","peer critique","artistic critique"],"example_sentence":"The critic decided to critique the new movie for its lack of originality.","example_es":"El crítico decidió criticar la nueva película por su falta de originalidad.","example_en":"The critic decided to critique the new movie for its lack of originality.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Argumentar","english_text":"Argue","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give reasons for or against something, often in a discussion or debate.","main_translations_es":["Discutir","Razonar","Debatir"],"collocations":["argue a point","argue with","argue about","argue that"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to know how to argue your ideas during the debate.","example_es":"Es importante saber argumentar tus ideas durante el debate.","example_en":"It''s important to know how to argue your ideas during the debate.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Demostrar","english_text":"Demonstrate","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To show or prove something clearly by giving evidence, examples, or a practical display.","main_translations_es":["Mostrar","Comprobar","Evidenciar"],"collocations":["demonstrate a point","demonstrate the ability","demonstrate commitment","demonstrate how"],"example_sentence":"The scientist managed to demonstrate his theory with the new experiments.","example_es":"El científico logró demostrar su teoría con los nuevos experimentos.","example_en":"The scientist managed to demonstrate his theory with the new experiments.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Ilustrar","english_text":"Illustrate","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to explain or make something clear by using examples, pictures, or diagrams","main_translations_es":["Dibujar","Representar","Mostrar"],"collocations":["illustrate a point","illustrate with examples","illustrate the concept","illustrate the differences"],"example_sentence":"The teacher used diagrams to illustrate the concept of kinetic energy.","example_es":"El profesor utilizó diagramas para ilustrar el concepto de energía cinética.","example_en":"The teacher used diagrams to illustrate the concept of kinetic energy.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Justificar","english_text":"Justify","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To provide reasons or arguments that show something is right or reasonable.","main_translations_es":["Explicar","Fundamentar","Razonar"],"collocations":["justify the decision","justify the cost","justify the means","justify the claim"],"example_sentence":"I need to justify my absence from the meeting with a medical note.","example_es":"Necesito justificar mi ausencia en la reunión con una nota médica.","example_en":"I need to justify my absence from the meeting with a medical note.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Respaldar","english_text":"Support","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give assistance, encouragement, or approval to someone or something.","main_translations_es":["Apoyar","Sustentar","Avalar"],"collocations":["provide support","support system","financial support","emotional support"],"example_sentence":"My family always supports me in my decisions.","example_es":"Mi familia siempre me respalda en mis decisiones.","example_en":"My family always supports me in my decisions.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Contradecir","english_text":"Contradict","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To assert the opposite of a statement or claim, thereby denying or opposing it.","main_translations_es":["oponerse","refutar","desmentir"],"collocations":["contradict the evidence","contradict each other","contradict the statement","contradict the findings"],"example_sentence":"You shouldn''t contradict your boss in public.","example_es":"No deberías contradecir a tu jefe en público.","example_en":"You shouldn''t contradict your boss in public.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cuestionar","english_text":"Question","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To ask about something in order to obtain information or to express doubt about it.","main_translations_es":["interrogar","dudar","poner en duda"],"collocations":["ask a question","raise a question","question the decision"],"example_sentence":"You shouldn''t question his motives without knowing the facts.","example_es":"No deberías cuestionar sus motivos sin conocer los hechos.","example_en":"You shouldn''t question his motives without knowing the facts.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Reformular","english_text":"Rephrase","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To express something again using different words, often to clarify or improve it.","main_translations_es":["Parafrasear","Reexpresar","Reformular"],"collocations":["rephrase the sentence","rephrase your question","rephrase for clarity"],"example_sentence":"Could you rephrase the question to make it clearer?","example_es":"¿Podrías reformular la pregunta para que sea más clara?","example_en":"Could you rephrase the question to make it clearer?","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Afirmar","english_text":"Claim","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To assert that something is true, typically without providing proof.","main_translations_es":["Declarar","Aseverar","Sostener"],"collocations":["make a claim","file a claim","claim responsibility","claim that"],"example_sentence":"The witness claimed that he saw the suspect at the scene.","example_es":"El testigo afirmó que vio al sospechoso en la escena.","example_en":"The witness claimed that he saw the suspect at the scene.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sugerir","english_text":"Suggest","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To propose an idea, plan, or course of action for consideration.","main_translations_es":["proponer","recomendar","aconsejar"],"collocations":["suggest a solution","suggest that","suggest an idea"],"example_sentence":"Could you suggest a good restaurant for dinner?","example_es":"¿Podrías sugerir un buen restaurante para cenar?","example_en":"Could you suggest a good restaurant for dinner?","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Señalar","english_text":"Indicate","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To point out or show something, making it known.","main_translations_es":["indicar","apuntar","marcar"],"collocations":["indicate that","indicate a preference","indicate the direction","indicate the results"],"example_sentence":"Please indicate the correct answer on the exam.","example_es":"Por favor, señale la respuesta correcta en el examen.","example_en":"Please indicate the correct answer on the exam.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Destacar","english_text":"Highlight","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To emphasize or make something stand out.","main_translations_es":["Resaltar","Sobresalir","Enfatizar"],"collocations":["highlight the main points","highlight a text","highlight a feature","highlight the issue"],"example_sentence":"I want to highlight the team''s achievements in the presentation.","example_es":"Quiero destacar los logros del equipo en la presentación.","example_en":"I want to highlight the team''s achievements in the presentation.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Enfatizar","english_text":"Emphasize","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give special importance or attention to something.","main_translations_es":["Resaltar","Destacar","Poner énfasis"],"collocations":["emphasize the importance","emphasize the need","emphasize that","emphasize the point"],"example_sentence":"The teacher wanted to emphasize the importance of punctuality.","example_es":"El profesor quiso enfatizar la importancia de la puntualidad.","example_en":"The teacher wanted to emphasize the importance of punctuality.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"En consecuencia","english_text":"Consequently","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"As a result; therefore.","main_translations_es":["Por lo tanto","Así que","De ese modo"],"collocations":["Consequently, the project was delayed.","Consequently, we decided to cancel the event.","Consequently, the results were inconclusive.","Consequently, sales increased dramatically."],"example_sentence":"Consequently, the project was cancelled.","example_es":"En consecuencia, el proyecto fue cancelado.","example_en":"Consequently, the project was cancelled.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sin embargo","english_text":"However","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"It introduces a contrast or exception to what has just been said.","main_translations_es":["no obstante","aun así","con todo"],"collocations":["however you like","however you want","however possible"],"example_sentence":"I wanted to go to the park; however, it started to rain.","example_es":"Quería ir al parque, sin embargo empezó a llover.","example_en":"I wanted to go to the park; however, it started to rain.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Además","english_text":"Furthermore","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"In addition; used to introduce an additional point.","main_translations_es":["También","Encima","Aparte"],"collocations":["Furthermore, ...","Furthermore, the study shows","Furthermore, we find","Furthermore, it is important"],"example_sentence":"Furthermore, the project will be completed before the deadline.","example_es":"Además, el proyecto será completado antes de la fecha límite.","example_en":"Furthermore, the project will be completed before the deadline.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Por el contrario","english_text":"Conversely","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"In a contrasting or opposite manner, used to introduce a statement that reverses the previous one.","main_translations_es":["En cambio","Al contrario","Por otro lado"],"collocations":["Conversely, the opposite is true","Conversely, if you increase the temperature, the pressure drops","Conversely, the results suggest a different trend"],"example_sentence":"He doesn''t like coffee; conversely, he prefers tea.","example_es":"No le gusta el café; por el contrario, prefiere el té.","example_en":"He doesn''t like coffee; conversely, he prefers tea.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Del mismo modo","english_text":"Similarly","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"In a similar way; in the same manner.","main_translations_es":["Igualmente","De la misma forma","De igual manera"],"collocations":["Similarly, ...","Similarly to","Similarly, the results show","Similarly, we can see"],"example_sentence":"Similarly, children must respect the rules.","example_es":"Del mismo modo, los niños deben respetar las reglas.","example_en":"Similarly, children must respect the rules.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No obstante","english_text":"Nonetheless","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"It means ''in spite of that'' or ''nevertheless''.","main_translations_es":["Sin embargo","A pesar de eso","Con todo"],"collocations":["Nonetheless, ...","Nonetheless, we must","Nonetheless, it is"],"example_sentence":"Nonetheless, he decided to continue with the project.","example_es":"No obstante, decidió continuar con el proyecto.","example_en":"Nonetheless, he decided to continue with the project.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Por lo tanto","english_text":"Therefore","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"As a result; for that reason.","main_translations_es":["Así que","Por consiguiente","En consecuencia"],"collocations":["therefore, we conclude","therefore, it follows","therefore, the results show"],"example_sentence":"He studied a lot for the exam; therefore, he got a good grade.","example_es":"Estudió mucho para el examen; por lo tanto, obtuvo una buena nota.","example_en":"He studied a lot for the exam; therefore, he got a good grade.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"En cambio","english_text":"In contrast","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to introduce a statement that differs from or opposes what has just been mentioned.","main_translations_es":["Por el contrario","A diferencia de","En contraste"],"collocations":["in contrast to","in contrast with","in contrast, however"],"example_sentence":"I prefer tea; she, in contrast, prefers coffee.","example_es":"Yo prefiero el té; ella, en cambio, prefiere el café.","example_en":"I prefer tea; she, in contrast, prefers coffee.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Por ejemplo","english_text":"For instance","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"phrase","definition_en":"Used to introduce an example.","main_translations_es":["Por ejemplo","A modo de ejemplo","Ejemplo"],"collocations":["for instance, ...","for instance, consider","for instance, such as"],"example_sentence":"For instance, if you study every day, you will improve your grades.","example_es":"Por ejemplo, si estudias todos los días, mejorarás tus notas.","example_en":"For instance, if you study every day, you will improve your grades.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Es decir","english_text":"That is to say","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to introduce a clarification or restatement of something previously said.","main_translations_es":["O sea","En otras palabras","Dicho de otro modo"],"collocations":["that is to say, the project is delayed","that is to say, in other words","that is to say, we need to act"],"example_sentence":"I didn''t like the movie; that is to say, I found it boring.","example_es":"No me gustó la película; es decir, la encontré aburrida.","example_en":"I didn''t like the movie; that is to say, I found it boring.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"A grandes rasgos","english_text":"Broadly speaking","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to introduce a general summary or overview of a topic.","main_translations_es":["En términos generales","En líneas generales","De manera general"],"collocations":["Broadly speaking, the results are positive.","Broadly speaking, we can conclude that...","Broadly speaking, the plan works.","Broadly speaking, it''s a good approach."],"example_sentence":"Broadly speaking, the project involves developing a mobile app for task management.","example_es":"A grandes rasgos, el proyecto consiste en desarrollar una aplicación móvil para la gestión de tareas.","example_en":"Broadly speaking, the project involves developing a mobile app for task management.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"En primer lugar","english_text":"In the first place","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to introduce the first reason or point in a discussion.","main_translations_es":["Primero","En primer término","Ante todo"],"collocations":["Why did you do that in the first place?","In the first place, we should consider the costs.","It wasn''t necessary in the first place."],"example_sentence":"In the first place, we must review the documents.","example_es":"En primer lugar, debemos revisar los documentos.","example_en":"In the first place, we must review the documents.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"En segundo lugar","english_text":"Secondly","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"Used to introduce the second item in a list or sequence of points.","main_translations_es":["En segundo término","En segundo punto","En segundo orden"],"collocations":["Firstly, ... Secondly, ...","Secondly, we need to...","Secondly, the results show..."],"example_sentence":"Secondly, we must consider the budget.","example_es":"En segundo lugar, debemos considerar el presupuesto.","example_en":"Secondly, we must consider the budget.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"En términos generales","english_text":"In general terms","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to indicate that something applies broadly or in a general sense.","main_translations_es":["En general","En términos generales","De forma general"],"collocations":["in general terms, ...","to put it in general terms","in general terms, the result is","in general terms, we can say"],"example_sentence":"In general terms, the project will be completed by the end of the year.","example_es":"En términos generales, el proyecto será completado a finales de año.","example_en":"In general terms, the project will be completed by the end of the year.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"En última instancia","english_text":"Ultimately","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"In the end, after all other considerations or events have taken place.","main_translations_es":["Al fin y al cabo","En definitiva","A fin de cuentas"],"collocations":["Ultimately, it comes down to","Ultimately, the decision rests with","Ultimately, we need to","Ultimately, the outcome depends on"],"example_sentence":"Ultimately, we will decide whether the project will go ahead.","example_es":"En última instancia, decidiremos si el proyecto sigue adelante.","example_en":"Ultimately, we will decide whether the project will go ahead.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cabe señalar que","english_text":"It should be noted that","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to introduce a statement that the speaker wants to emphasize or draw attention to.","main_translations_es":["Cabe destacar que","Hay que señalar que","Es importante señalar que"],"collocations":["It should be noted that...","It should be noted that the data...","It should be noted that this is..."],"example_sentence":"It should be noted that the report will be presented tomorrow.","example_es":"Cabe señalar que el informe será presentado mañana.","example_en":"It should be noted that the report will be presented tomorrow.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Se puede sostener que","english_text":"It can be argued that","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to introduce a statement that may be debated or supported with reasoning.","main_translations_es":["Se puede afirmar que","Se podría sostener que","Se puede decir que"],"collocations":["It can be argued that the data supports this","It can be argued that this is the case","It can be argued that there are alternatives","It can be argued that the policy is ineffective"],"example_sentence":"It can be argued that the economy will grow next year.","example_es":"Se puede sostener que la economía crecerá el próximo año.","example_en":"It can be argued that the economy will grow next year.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Parece evidente que","english_text":"It seems evident that","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to indicate that something appears clear or obvious.","main_translations_es":["Resulta evidente que","Es evidente que","Se ve evidente que"],"collocations":["It seems evident that...","It seems evident that the data show...","It seems evident that we need to act","It seems evident that this is the case"],"example_sentence":"It seems evident that the evidence supports his theory.","example_es":"Parece evidente que la evidencia apoya su teoría.","example_en":"It seems evident that the evidence supports his theory.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Está ampliamente aceptado","english_text":"It is widely accepted","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that something is generally approved or recognized by many people.","main_translations_es":["Se acepta ampliamente","Es de aceptación general","Goza de amplio reconocimiento"],"collocations":["widely accepted practice","widely accepted theory","widely accepted standard"],"example_sentence":"It is widely accepted that recycling helps the environment.","example_es":"Está ampliamente aceptado que el reciclaje ayuda al medio ambiente.","example_en":"It is widely accepted that recycling helps the environment.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Permanecer incierto","english_text":"Remain uncertain","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To stay in a state of uncertainty.","main_translations_es":["Seguir sin estar claro","Quedarse en duda","Mantenerse incierto"],"collocations":["remain uncertain about","remain uncertain whether","remain uncertain at this point"],"example_sentence":"The outcome of the trial will remain uncertain.","example_es":"El resultado del juicio seguirá permaneciendo incierto.","example_en":"The outcome of the trial will remain uncertain.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Tener en cuenta","english_text":"Take into consideration","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To consider something carefully when making a decision.","main_translations_es":["Considerar","Tener presente","Tomar en cuenta"],"collocations":["take into consideration the costs","take into consideration the risks","take into consideration the feedback","take into consideration the circumstances"],"example_sentence":"You should take into consideration the doctor''s recommendations before starting the treatment.","example_es":"Debes tener en cuenta las recomendaciones del médico antes de iniciar el tratamiento.","example_en":"You should take into consideration the doctor''s recommendations before starting the treatment.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sacar una conclusión","english_text":"Draw a conclusion","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"to form a judgment or inference based on evidence","main_translations_es":["Llegar a una conclusión","Concluir","Formular una conclusión"],"collocations":["draw a conclusion from the data","draw a conclusion about","draw a conclusion based on the evidence","draw a conclusion that"],"example_sentence":"After reviewing the data, we can draw a clear conclusion.","example_es":"Después de revisar los datos, podemos sacar una conclusión clara.","example_en":"After reviewing the data, we can draw a clear conclusion.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Llegar a una conclusión","english_text":"Reach a conclusion","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to arrive at a decision or judgment after considering the evidence","main_translations_es":["Sacar una conclusión","Concluir","Llegar a una decisión"],"collocations":["reach a conclusion about","reach a conclusion after","reach a conclusion that","reach a conclusion quickly"],"example_sentence":"After analyzing the data, we reached a conclusion.","example_es":"Después de analizar los datos, llegamos a una conclusión.","example_en":"After analyzing the data, we reached a conclusion.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"A modo de conclusión","english_text":"By way of conclusion","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to introduce a final statement or summary.","main_translations_es":["En conclusión","Para concluir","En síntesis"],"collocations":["By way of conclusion, we can see that...","By way of conclusion, the study suggests...","By way of conclusion, it is evident that...","By way of conclusion, I recommend..."],"example_sentence":"By way of conclusion, we can say that the project was a success.","example_es":"A modo de conclusión, podemos decir que el proyecto fue un éxito.","example_en":"By way of conclusion, we can say that the project was a success.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Tesis","english_text":"Thesis","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A written document presenting the author''s research and findings, typically submitted for an academic degree.","main_translations_es":["Trabajo de investigación","Disertación","Monografía"],"collocations":["thesis statement","doctoral thesis","master''s thesis","thesis defense"],"example_sentence":"I am working on my doctoral thesis.","example_es":"Estoy trabajando en mi tesis de doctorado.","example_en":"I am working on my doctoral thesis.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Antítesis","english_text":"Counterargument","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A statement or set of reasons presented in opposition to another argument.","main_translations_es":["Contraposición","Oposición","Contraste"],"collocations":["present a counterargument","raise a counterargument","offer a counterargument","counterargument to"],"example_sentence":"His statement was a counterargument to the proposed theory.","example_es":"Su argumento era la antítesis de la teoría propuesta.","example_en":"His statement was a counterargument to the proposed theory.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Postura","english_text":"Stance","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"a person''s attitude or position on a particular issue","main_translations_es":["Actitud","Posición","Postura"],"collocations":["take a stance","firm stance","political stance","stance on"],"example_sentence":"His stance on the change was very clear.","example_es":"Su postura frente al cambio fue muy clara.","example_en":"His stance on the change was very clear.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Razonamiento","english_text":"Reasoning","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The mental process of drawing conclusions or making inferences based on evidence or logical principles.","main_translations_es":["Lógica","Pensamiento","Análisis"],"collocations":["critical reasoning","logical reasoning","deductive reasoning","reasoning skills"],"example_sentence":"His reasoning was impeccable during the debate.","example_es":"Su razonamiento fue impecable durante el debate.","example_en":"His reasoning was impeccable during the debate.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Premisa","english_text":"Premise","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A statement or proposition that serves as a basis for reasoning or argument.","main_translations_es":["Supuesto","Postulado","Axioma"],"collocations":["on the premise that","basic premise","underlying premise","premise of the argument"],"example_sentence":"The premise of the argument is that all human beings seek happiness.","example_es":"La premisa del argumento es que todos los seres humanos buscan la felicidad.","example_en":"The premise of the argument is that all human beings seek happiness.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Inferencia","english_text":"Inference","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A conclusion drawn from evidence and reasoning.","main_translations_es":["Razonamiento","Deducción"],"collocations":["make an inference","draw an inference","inference based on evidence"],"example_sentence":"Based on the data, he made an inference about the future behavior of the market.","example_es":"A partir de los datos, hizo una inferencia sobre el comportamiento futuro del mercado.","example_en":"Based on the data, he made an inference about the future behavior of the market.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Validez","english_text":"Validity","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The quality of being logically sound or legally acceptable.","main_translations_es":["Validez","Legitimidad","Vigencia"],"collocations":["question the validity","prove the validity","validity period","validity of the claim"],"example_sentence":"The validity of the contract expired on December 31st.","example_es":"La validez del contrato expiró el 31 de diciembre.","example_en":"The validity of the contract expired on December 31st.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Fiabilidad","english_text":"Reliability","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The quality of being trustworthy or dependable.","main_translations_es":["Confiabilidad","Seguridad"],"collocations":["reliability of the system","high reliability","reliability engineering","reliability testing"],"example_sentence":"The reliability of this car is impressive.","example_es":"La fiabilidad de este coche es impresionante.","example_en":"The reliability of this car is impressive.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sesgo","english_text":"Bias","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A tendency to favor or prejudice a particular perspective, group, or outcome.","main_translations_es":["Prejuicio","Tendencia","Parcialidad"],"collocations":["bias towards","bias against","cognitive bias","implicit bias"],"example_sentence":"The bias of the survey made the results unrepresentative.","example_es":"El sesgo de la encuesta hizo que los resultados no fueran representativos.","example_en":"The bias of the survey made the results unrepresentative.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Objetividad","english_text":"Objectivity","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The quality of being objective, or the ability to consider facts without personal bias or emotion.","main_translations_es":["Imparcialidad","Neutralidad","Objetividad"],"collocations":["maintain objectivity","objectivity in reporting","objectivity and fairness","objectivity of the study"],"example_sentence":"The scientist must maintain objectivity when analyzing the data.","example_es":"El científico debe mantener la objetividad al analizar los datos.","example_en":"The scientist must maintain objectivity when analyzing the data.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Subjetividad","english_text":"Subjectivity","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The quality of being based on personal feelings, tastes, or opinions rather than objective facts.","main_translations_es":["Subjetividad","Perspectiva personal","Punto de vista subjetivo"],"collocations":["subjectivity of perception","subjectivity in art","subjectivity bias","subjectivity of experience"],"example_sentence":"The subjectivity of the author is reflected in every chapter of the book.","example_es":"La subjetividad del autor se refleja en cada capítulo del libro.","example_en":"The subjectivity of the author is reflected in every chapter of the book.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Correlación","english_text":"Correlation","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A statistical measure that describes the extent to which two variables change together.","main_translations_es":["Relación estadística","Correspondencia","Vínculo"],"collocations":["high correlation","strong correlation","positive correlation","negative correlation"],"example_sentence":"There is a strong correlation between sugar consumption and the incidence of diabetes.","example_es":"Existe una fuerte correlación entre el consumo de azúcar y la incidencia de diabetes.","example_en":"There is a strong correlation between sugar consumption and the incidence of diabetes.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Causalidad","english_text":"Causation","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The relationship in which one event or action causes another to occur.","main_translations_es":["Causa","Relación causal"],"collocations":["cause and effect","causation and correlation","prove causation"],"example_sentence":"The causation between smoking and lung cancer is well established.","example_es":"La causalidad entre fumar y el cáncer de pulmón está bien establecida.","example_en":"The causation between smoking and lung cancer is well established.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Distribución","english_text":"Distribution","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The act of giving out or spreading something, or the way in which something is shared or dispersed.","main_translations_es":["Distribución","Reparto"],"collocations":["distribution network","probability distribution","distribution channel","distribution system"],"example_sentence":"The distribution of the resources was carried out equitably.","example_es":"La distribución de los recursos se realizó de manera equitativa.","example_en":"The distribution of the resources was carried out equitably.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Desviación","english_text":"Deviation","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A departure from a standard, norm, or expected course.","main_translations_es":["Desviación"],"collocations":["standard deviation","deviation from the norm","maximum deviation","acceptable deviation"],"example_sentence":"The deviation from the road was minimal.","example_es":"La desviación del camino fue mínima.","example_en":"The deviation from the road was minimal.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Consistencia","english_text":"Consistency","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The quality of being consistent, or the ability to remain the same over time or across situations.","main_translations_es":["Coherencia","Uniformidad","Solidez"],"collocations":["consistency is key","maintain consistency","lack of consistency","consistency over time"],"example_sentence":"The consistency of the yogurt is perfect for breakfast.","example_es":"La consistencia del yogur es perfecta para el desayuno.","example_en":"The consistency of the yogurt is perfect for breakfast.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Precisión","english_text":"Accuracy","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The quality or state of being correct, exact, or precise.","main_translations_es":["Exactitud","Precisión","Fidelidad"],"collocations":["high accuracy","accuracy rate","accuracy of the measurement","accuracy level"],"example_sentence":"The accuracy of the Swiss watch is impressive.","example_es":"La precisión del reloj suizo es impresionante.","example_en":"The accuracy of the Swiss watch is impressive.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Relevancia","english_text":"Relevance","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The quality of being relevant or applicable to a particular matter.","main_translations_es":["Importancia","Pertinencia","Significancia"],"collocations":["of relevance","relevance to the issue","in terms of relevance","relevance in the context"],"example_sentence":"The relevance of scientific data is essential for making informed decisions.","example_es":"La relevancia de los datos científicos es fundamental para tomar decisiones informadas.","example_en":"The relevance of scientific data is essential for making informed decisions.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Pertinencia","english_text":"Appropriateness","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The quality of being suitable or fitting for a particular purpose, situation, or person.","main_translations_es":["Relevancia","Adecuación","Conveniencia"],"collocations":["appropriateness of the decision","assess the appropriateness","in terms of appropriateness","question of appropriateness"],"example_sentence":"The appropriateness of his remarks improved the group''s discussion.","example_es":"La pertinencia de sus comentarios mejoró la discusión del grupo.","example_en":"The appropriateness of his remarks improved the group''s discussion.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Muestra representativa","english_text":"Representative sample","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A subset of a population that accurately reflects the characteristics of the whole group.","main_translations_es":["Muestra típica","Muestra representativa","Muestra aleatoria representativa"],"collocations":["a representative sample of the population","representative sample size","representative sample data","representative sample study"],"example_sentence":"For the study, we took a representative sample of the population.","example_es":"Para el estudio, tomamos una muestra representativa de la población.","example_en":"For the study, we took a representative sample of the population.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Criterio de selección","english_text":"Selection criteria","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Selection criteria are the standards or requirements used to choose among alternatives.","main_translations_es":["Criterio de elección","Parámetro de selección","Criterio de escogencia"],"collocations":["meet the selection criteria","selection criteria for","establish selection criteria","selection criteria include"],"example_sentence":"The selection criteria for the scholarship program is academic performance.","example_es":"El criterio de selección para el programa de becas es el rendimiento académico.","example_en":"The selection criteria for the scholarship program is academic performance.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Recopilar datos","english_text":"Collect data","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To gather or obtain information, typically for analysis or record-keeping.","main_translations_es":["Recoger datos","Obtener datos","Compilar datos"],"collocations":["collect data from","collect data on","collect data for analysis","collect data efficiently"],"example_sentence":"The team needs to collect data before presenting the report.","example_es":"El equipo necesita recopilar datos antes de presentar el informe.","example_en":"The team needs to collect data before presenting the report.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Procesar datos","english_text":"Process data","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To manipulate or handle data in order to extract information or perform operations on it.","main_translations_es":["Tratar datos","Manejar datos","Analizar datos"],"collocations":["process data efficiently","process data in real time","process large datasets","process data securely"],"example_sentence":"We need to process data before generating the report.","example_es":"Necesitamos procesar datos antes de generar el informe.","example_en":"We need to process data before generating the report.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Respaldado por evidencia","english_text":"Evidence-based","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Based on or derived from evidence.","main_translations_es":["Basado en evidencia","Fundamentado en evidencia","Sustentado por evidencia"],"collocations":["evidence-based practice","evidence-based approach","evidence-based medicine","evidence-based policy"],"example_sentence":"The new treatment is evidence-based, relying on scientific data.","example_es":"El nuevo tratamiento está respaldado por evidencia científica.","example_en":"The new treatment is evidence-based, relying on scientific data.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sustancial","english_text":"Substantial","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Considerable in amount, size, or importance; significant.","main_translations_es":["significativo","considerable","importante"],"collocations":["substantial amount","substantial evidence","substantial increase","substantial impact"],"example_sentence":"The increase in investment was substantial this year.","example_es":"El aumento de la inversión fue sustancial este año.","example_en":"The increase in investment was substantial this year.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Marginal","english_text":"Marginal","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Existing or situated at the edge or margin, or being only barely sufficient.","main_translations_es":["periférico","secundario","de poca importancia"],"collocations":["marginal cost","marginal benefit","marginal increase","marginally"],"example_sentence":"The marginal increase in price will not affect most consumers.","example_es":"El aumento marginal del precio no afectará a la mayoría de los consumidores.","example_en":"The marginal increase in price will not affect most consumers.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Significativo","english_text":"Significant","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Important or notable enough to be worthy of attention.","main_translations_es":["Importante","Relevante","Notable"],"collocations":["significant impact","significant difference","significant role","significant amount"],"example_sentence":"This finding is significant for the research.","example_es":"Este hallazgo es significativo para la investigación.","example_en":"This finding is significant for the research.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Insignificante","english_text":"Negligible","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"so small or unimportant that it is not worth considering","main_translations_es":["Irrelevante","Trivial","Mínimo"],"collocations":["negligible amount","negligible impact","negligible risk","negligible difference"],"example_sentence":"The impact of that mistake is negligible on the final result.","example_es":"El impacto de ese error es insignificante en el resultado final.","example_en":"The impact of that mistake is negligible on the final result.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Rigurosidad","english_text":"Rigor","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"strictness or exactness in standards, procedures, or analysis","main_translations_es":["rigor","exigencia","meticulosidad"],"collocations":["academic rigor","rigor of the test","rigor in methodology","rigor and precision"],"example_sentence":"The rigor of the scientific method ensures reliable results.","example_es":"La rigurosidad del método científico garantiza resultados confiables.","example_en":"The rigor of the scientific method ensures reliable results.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Coherencia","english_text":"Coherence","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The quality of being logical, consistent, and forming a unified whole.","main_translations_es":["Consistencia","Lógica","Congruencia"],"collocations":["lack of coherence","maintain coherence","coherence theory","coherence in writing"],"example_sentence":"The coherence of the argument made everyone accept it.","example_es":"La coherencia del argumento hizo que todos lo aceptaran.","example_en":"The coherence of the argument made everyone accept it.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Claridad","english_text":"Clarity","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The quality of being clear, easily understood, or transparent.","main_translations_es":["Nitidez","Lucidez","Transparencia"],"collocations":["crystal clear","gain clarity","lack of clarity","clear as day"],"example_sentence":"The clarity of the lake''s water was impressive.","example_es":"La claridad del agua del lago era impresionante.","example_en":"The clarity of the lake''s water was impressive.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Concisión","english_text":"Conciseness","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The quality of being brief and to the point in speech or writing.","main_translations_es":["Brevedad","Precisión","Sucintez"],"collocations":["value of conciseness","conciseness is key","in the interest of conciseness","conciseness and clarity"],"example_sentence":"Conciseness is essential when drafting brief reports.","example_es":"La concisión es esencial al redactar informes breves.","example_en":"Conciseness is essential when drafting brief reports.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Ampliar","english_text":"Elaborate on","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give more detail or expand upon something.","main_translations_es":["Extender","Desarrollar","Expandir"],"collocations":["elaborate on the details","elaborate on the plan","elaborate on his statement"],"example_sentence":"Could you elaborate on your explanation of the process?","example_es":"¿Podrías ampliar tu explicación sobre el proceso?","example_en":"Could you elaborate on your explanation of the process?","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Resumir","english_text":"Summarize","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give a brief statement of the main points of something.","main_translations_es":["Sintetizar","Abreviar","Compendiar"],"collocations":["summarize the main points","summarize the findings","summarize the report","summarize briefly"],"example_sentence":"Please summarize the article in three sentences.","example_es":"Por favor, resume el artículo en tres frases.","example_en":"Please summarize the article in three sentences.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Parafrasear","english_text":"Paraphrase","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A restatement of a text or passage using different words, especially to achieve greater clarity.","main_translations_es":["Reformular","Expresar con otras palabras","Decir de otra manera"],"collocations":["to paraphrase the text","in other words","to paraphrase the author","as a paraphrase"],"example_sentence":"Can you paraphrase what I said to make it clearer?","example_es":"¿Puedes parafrasear lo que dije para que sea más claro?","example_en":"Can you paraphrase what I said to make it clearer?","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Citar","english_text":"Cite","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To quote or refer to a source as evidence or support.","main_translations_es":["Citar","Mencionar","Referenciar"],"collocations":["cite a source","cite evidence","cite references","cite in APA style"],"example_sentence":"The article cites several experts on climate change.","example_es":"El artículo cita a varios expertos sobre el cambio climático.","example_en":"The article cites several experts on climate change.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Referenciar","english_text":"Reference","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A source of information that is cited or consulted.","main_translations_es":["Citar","Mencionar","Aludir"],"collocations":["reference letter","reference point","make reference to","for reference"],"example_sentence":"It is important to reference all sources in your research paper.","example_es":"Es importante referenciar todas las fuentes en tu trabajo de investigación.","example_en":"It is important to reference all sources in your research paper.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Notas a pie de página","english_text":"Footnotes","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Notes placed at the bottom of a page that give additional information or citations.","main_translations_es":["Notas al pie","Notas de pie de página","Referencias al pie"],"collocations":["in the footnotes","footnotes section","footnotes and endnotes","footnotes reference"],"example_sentence":"The footnotes explain the technical terms of the article.","example_es":"Las notas a pie de página explican los términos técnicos del artículo.","example_en":"The footnotes explain the technical terms of the article.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Apéndice","english_text":"Appendix","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A supplementary section at the end of a book or document, or a small organ attached to the large intestine.","main_translations_es":["Anexo","Suplemento","Apéndice"],"collocations":["in the appendix","appendix A","see the appendix","appendix section"],"example_sentence":"The appendix of the book contains additional information about the history.","example_es":"El apéndice del libro contiene información adicional sobre la historia.","example_en":"The appendix of the book contains additional information about the history.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Resumen ejecutivo","english_text":"Executive summary","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A brief overview of a document''s main points, usually placed at the beginning.","main_translations_es":["Síntesis ejecutiva","Informe ejecutivo","Resumen de gestión"],"collocations":["prepare an executive summary","include an executive summary","the executive summary outlines","executive summary section"],"example_sentence":"The executive summary of the report highlights the main findings.","example_es":"El resumen ejecutivo del informe destaca los principales hallazgos.","example_en":"The executive summary of the report highlights the main findings.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Pregunta de investigación","english_text":"Research question","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A question that guides the focus and direction of a research study.","main_translations_es":["Cuestión de investigación","Pregunta de estudio","Interrogante de investigación"],"collocations":["formulate a research question","address the research question","answer the research question","research question formulation"],"example_sentence":"The research question of my thesis is how climate change affects biodiversity.","example_es":"La pregunta de investigación de mi tesis es cómo afecta el cambio climático a la biodiversidad.","example_en":"The research question of my thesis is how climate change affects biodiversity.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Ámbito de estudio","english_text":"Scope of the study","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"The range or extent of topics covered by the study.","main_translations_es":["Campo de estudio","Área de estudio","Rama de estudio"],"collocations":["the scope of the study includes","within the scope of the study","the scope of the study was limited","scope of the study determines"],"example_sentence":"The scope of the study is molecular biology.","example_es":"El ámbito de estudio de la investigación es la biología molecular.","example_en":"The scope of the study is molecular biology.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Línea de investigación","english_text":"Research line","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A specific area or focus within a broader field of study or investigation.","main_translations_es":["Área de investigación","Campo de investigación","Tema de investigación"],"collocations":["establish a research line","follow a research line","new research line","research line in biology"],"example_sentence":"My research line focuses on artificial intelligence.","example_es":"Mi línea de investigación se centra en la inteligencia artificial.","example_en":"My research line focuses on artificial intelligence.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Marco conceptual","english_text":"Conceptual framework","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A set of ideas and concepts that provides a structure for understanding or analyzing something.","main_translations_es":["Marco teórico","Estructura conceptual","Esquema conceptual"],"collocations":["within the conceptual framework","conceptual framework of","conceptual framework for","under the conceptual framework"],"example_sentence":"The researcher presented a new conceptual framework to understand urban migration.","example_es":"El investigador presentó un nuevo marco conceptual para entender la migración urbana.","example_en":"The researcher presented a new conceptual framework to understand urban migration.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Vacío de investigación","english_text":"Research gap","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A research gap is an area or topic that has not yet been studied or is insufficiently explored in existing literature.","main_translations_es":["laguna de investigación","hueco de investigación","brecha de investigación"],"collocations":["identify a research gap","address the research gap","fill the research gap","research gap analysis"],"example_sentence":"The study identifies a research gap in the relationship between diet and mental health.","example_es":"El estudio identifica un vacío de investigación en la relación entre la dieta y la salud mental.","example_en":"The study identifies a research gap in the relationship between diet and mental health.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Hallazgo clave","english_text":"Key finding","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A significant or important result discovered in a study or investigation.","main_translations_es":["Descubrimiento importante","Resultado principal","Conclusión esencial"],"collocations":["key finding of the study","key finding suggests","key finding highlights","key finding reveals"],"example_sentence":"The key finding of the study was the relationship between diet and cardiovascular health.","example_es":"El hallazgo clave del estudio fue la relación entre la dieta y la salud cardiovascular.","example_en":"The key finding of the study was the relationship between diet and cardiovascular health.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Trabajo seminal","english_text":"Seminal work","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A highly influential piece of research or writing that forms the basis for later developments.","main_translations_es":["Obra seminal","Estudio pionero","Trabajo fundamental"],"collocations":["seminal work on","seminal work in","seminal work that","seminal work has"],"example_sentence":"This article is a seminal work in the field of evolutionary biology.","example_es":"Este artículo es un trabajo seminal en el campo de la biología evolutiva.","example_en":"This article is a seminal work in the field of evolutionary biology.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Contribución original","english_text":"Original contribution","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A contribution that is new, unique, or created for the first time.","main_translations_es":["Aporte original","Contribución inicial","Aportación original"],"collocations":["make an original contribution","original contribution to the field","significant original contribution","original contribution was recognized"],"example_sentence":"His original contribution to the project was essential.","example_es":"Su contribución original al proyecto fue fundamental.","example_en":"His original contribution to the project was essential.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Líneas futuras","english_text":"Further avenues","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"Additional possible paths or options for exploration.","main_translations_es":["Nuevas vías","Posibles caminos","Opciones futuras"],"collocations":["explore further avenues","open further avenues","pursue further avenues"],"example_sentence":"We will explore further avenues to improve the project.","example_es":"Exploraremos nuevas líneas futuras para mejorar el proyecto.","example_en":"We will explore further avenues to improve the project.","mnemonic_en":null}]'::jsonb) as x(
  spanish_text text, english_text text, section_name text, part_of_speech text, definition_en text,
  main_translations_es jsonb, collocations jsonb, example_sentence text, example_es text, example_en text, mnemonic_en text
)
where not exists (
  select 1 from public.cards c2
  where c2.deck_id = dk.id
    and lower(c2.spanish_text) = lower(x.spanish_text)
    and lower(c2.english_text) = lower(x.english_text)
);

-- english-news-and-society (104 cards)
insert into public.decks (slug, title, description, language_from, language_to)
values ('english-news-and-society', 'News and Society', 'Advanced vocabulary for current affairs, social issues, media, technology, and global events.', 'es', 'en')
on conflict (slug) do nothing;

insert into public.cards (deck_id, spanish_text, english_text, is_enabled, generation_phase, generation_metadata, section_name, part_of_speech, definition_en, main_translations_es, collocations, example_sentence, example_es, example_en, mnemonic_en)
select dk.id, x.spanish_text, x.english_text, true, 'refined', '{}'::jsonb, x.section_name, x.part_of_speech, x.definition_en,
       coalesce(x.main_translations_es, '[]'::jsonb), coalesce(x.collocations, '[]'::jsonb), x.example_sentence, x.example_es, x.example_en, x.mnemonic_en
from (select id from public.decks where slug = 'english-news-and-society') dk
cross join jsonb_to_recordset('[{"spanish_text":"Titular","english_text":"Headline","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A headline is a brief, attention‑grabbing title that appears at the top of a news article or other written piece.","main_translations_es":["encabezado","título","cabecera"],"collocations":["headline news","catchy headline","headline story","make headlines"],"example_sentence":"The headline in the newspaper announced the team''s victory.","example_es":"El titular del periódico anunciaba la victoria del equipo.","example_en":"The headline in the newspaper announced the team''s victory.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cobertura mediática","english_text":"Media coverage","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The reporting of an event or topic by various media outlets.","main_translations_es":["Cobertura de prensa","Cobertura informativa","Cobertura periodística"],"collocations":["extensive media coverage","media coverage of the event","receive media coverage","limited media coverage"],"example_sentence":"The media coverage of the accident was extensive and continuous.","example_es":"La cobertura mediática del accidente fue extensa y constante.","example_en":"The media coverage of the accident was extensive and continuous.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Artículo de fondo","english_text":"Feature article","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A feature article is a detailed, in‑depth newspaper or magazine story that explores a topic more comprehensively than a news report.","main_translations_es":["Artículo de fondo","Reportaje de fondo","Artículo extenso"],"collocations":["write a feature article","publish a feature article","feature article series"],"example_sentence":"I read a feature article about the climate crisis in the newspaper.","example_es":"Leí un artículo de fondo sobre la crisis climática en el periódico.","example_en":"I read a feature article about the climate crisis in the newspaper.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Editorial","english_text":"Editorial","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"An article expressing the opinion of the editor or the publication.","main_translations_es":["artículo de opinión","publicación","opinión"],"collocations":["editorial board","editorial policy","editorial staff","editorial decision"],"example_sentence":"I read the editorial in the newspaper about the climate crisis.","example_es":"Leí la editorial del periódico sobre la crisis climática.","example_en":"I read the editorial in the newspaper about the climate crisis.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Fuente fiable","english_text":"Reliable source","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A source that can be trusted to provide accurate and trustworthy information.","main_translations_es":["Fuente confiable","Fuente segura","Fuente fidedigna"],"collocations":["according to reliable sources","a reliable source of information","from a reliable source","reliable source of news"],"example_sentence":"This article is a reliable source for studying history.","example_es":"Este artículo es una fuente fiable para estudiar la historia.","example_en":"This article is a reliable source for studying history.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Desinformación","english_text":"Misinformation","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"False or inaccurate information that is spread deliberately or unintentionally.","main_translations_es":["Información errónea","Noticias falsas","Información falsa"],"collocations":["spread misinformation","combat misinformation","misinformation campaign","misinformation about"],"example_sentence":"Misinformation about the vaccine is causing fear.","example_es":"La desinformación sobre la vacuna está generando miedo.","example_en":"Misinformation about the vaccine is causing fear.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Información falsa","english_text":"False information","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Information that is incorrect or misleading.","main_translations_es":["Datos falsos","Información errónea","Noticias falsas"],"collocations":["spread false information","contain false information","correct false information"],"example_sentence":"Don''t believe everything you read online; much of that information is false.","example_es":"No creas todo lo que lees en internet; mucha de esa información es falsa.","example_en":"Don''t believe everything you read online; much of that information is false.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Noticia de última hora","english_text":"Breaking news","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Urgent or newly received news that is reported immediately.","main_translations_es":["Última hora","Noticias de última hora","Últimas noticias"],"collocations":["breaking news alert","breaking news story","breaking news coverage","breaking news update"],"example_sentence":"Breaking news! The president has announced his resignation.","example_es":"¡Noticia de última hora! El presidente ha anunciado su renuncia.","example_en":"Breaking news! The president has announced his resignation.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cobertura en directo","english_text":"Live coverage","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"Live coverage is the real-time reporting or broadcasting of an event as it happens.","main_translations_es":["Cobertura en vivo","Transmisión en directo","Cobertura en tiempo real"],"collocations":["live coverage of the event","live coverage on TV","live coverage updates","live coverage broadcast"],"example_sentence":"The live coverage of the concert will be streamed on our website.","example_es":"La cobertura en directo del concierto se transmitirá en nuestro sitio web.","example_en":"The live coverage of the concert will be streamed on our website.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Actualización","english_text":"Update","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A change that adds new information or improves something to make it current.","main_translations_es":["Actualización","Puesta al día","Renovación"],"collocations":["software update","latest update","update the record","update your status"],"example_sentence":"The update of the software improved the device''s performance.","example_es":"La actualización del software mejoró el rendimiento del dispositivo.","example_en":"The update of the software improved the device''s performance.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Encuesta de opinión","english_text":"Opinion poll","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A survey that asks people for their views on a particular topic.","main_translations_es":["Encuesta de opinión","Sondeo de opinión","Encuesta de percepción"],"collocations":["conduct an opinion poll","opinion poll results","national opinion poll","opinion poll survey"],"example_sentence":"The opinion poll showed that the majority supports the measure.","example_es":"La encuesta de opinión mostró que la mayoría apoya la medida.","example_en":"The opinion poll showed that the majority supports the measure.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Participación electoral","english_text":"Voter turnout","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The percentage or number of eligible voters who actually cast a ballot in an election.","main_translations_es":["Participación en las elecciones","Tasa de participación","Participación de los votantes"],"collocations":["low voter turnout","increase voter turnout","voter turnout rates","boost voter turnout"],"example_sentence":"Voter turnout in the last election was 70%.","example_es":"La participación electoral en las últimas elecciones fue del 70%.","example_en":"Voter turnout in the last election was 70%.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Campaña electoral","english_text":"Election campaign","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A coordinated effort by a candidate or political party to win votes in an upcoming election.","main_translations_es":["Campaña electoral","Campaña de elecciones","Campaña política"],"collocations":["run an election campaign","launch an election campaign","election campaign strategy","election campaign finance"],"example_sentence":"The election campaign began last week and the debates are already being heard.","example_es":"La campaña electoral comenzó la semana pasada y ya se están escuchando los debates.","example_en":"The election campaign began last week and the debates are already being heard.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Debate público","english_text":"Public debate","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A public debate is an open discussion where participants exchange differing views on a topic in front of an audience.","main_translations_es":["Foro público","Discusión pública","Debate abierto"],"collocations":["public debate on","open public debate","national public debate"],"example_sentence":"The public debate on climate change attracted thousands of viewers.","example_es":"El debate público sobre el cambio climático atrajo a miles de espectadores.","example_en":"The public debate on climate change attracted thousands of viewers.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Polarización","english_text":"Polarization","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of dividing something into opposing groups or of aligning electric charges in opposite directions.","main_translations_es":["Polarización","División polar","Polarización política"],"collocations":["political polarization","cultural polarization","polarization of opinions","polarization effect"],"example_sentence":"Political polarization in the country has increased in recent years.","example_es":"La polarización política en el país ha aumentado en los últimos años.","example_en":"Political polarization in the country has increased in recent years.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Populismo","english_text":"Populism","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A political approach that seeks to appeal to ordinary people who feel their concerns are ignored by established elites.","main_translations_es":["populismo","movimiento populista","corriente populista"],"collocations":["rise of populism","populist rhetoric","populist movements","anti‑establishment populism"],"example_sentence":"Populism has gained ground in several Latin American countries.","example_es":"El populismo ha ganado terreno en varios países de América Latina.","example_en":"Populism has gained ground in several Latin American countries.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Gobernanza","english_text":"Governance","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The act or system of governing, or the way an organization or society is managed and controlled.","main_translations_es":["Gestión","Administración","Dirección"],"collocations":["corporate governance","good governance","governance structure","governance framework"],"example_sentence":"The governance of the company is based on transparency and employee participation.","example_es":"La gobernanza de la empresa se basa en la transparencia y la participación de los empleados.","example_en":"The governance of the company is based on transparency and employee participation.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Transparencia","english_text":"Transparency","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The quality of being clear, open, or easily understood, or the condition of allowing light to pass through so that objects behind can be seen.","main_translations_es":["Claridad","Limpidez","Visibilidad"],"collocations":["transparency in government","financial transparency","transparency and accountability","transparency report"],"example_sentence":"Government transparency is essential for citizens'' trust.","example_es":"La transparencia del gobierno es esencial para la confianza de los ciudadanos.","example_en":"Government transparency is essential for citizens'' trust.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Rendición de cuentas","english_text":"Accountability","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The obligation to accept responsibility for one''s actions and decisions.","main_translations_es":["Responsabilidad","Justificación","Transparencia"],"collocations":["accountability measures","accountability framework","accountability for actions"],"example_sentence":"Accountability is essential for transparency in government.","example_es":"La rendición de cuentas es fundamental para la transparencia en el gobierno.","example_en":"Accountability is essential for transparency in government.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Corrupción","english_text":"Corruption","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Dishonest or fraudulent conduct by those in power, often involving bribery or the misuse of authority for personal gain.","main_translations_es":["Corrupción","Deshonestidad","Mala conducta"],"collocations":["corruption scandal","corruption charges","fight against corruption","corruption in politics"],"example_sentence":"Corruption in the government has decreased thanks to the new laws.","example_es":"La corrupción en el gobierno ha disminuido gracias a las nuevas leyes.","example_en":"Corruption in the government has decreased thanks to the new laws.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Desigualdad","english_text":"Inequality","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A condition of being unequal, especially in status, rights, or opportunities.","main_translations_es":["Desigualdad","Desigualdad social","Desigualdad económica"],"collocations":["income inequality","gender inequality","social inequality","racial inequality"],"example_sentence":"Salary inequality between men and women remains a serious problem.","example_es":"La desigualdad salarial entre hombres y mujeres sigue siendo un problema grave.","example_en":"Salary inequality between men and women remains a serious problem.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Movilidad social","english_text":"Social mobility","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The movement of individuals or groups within or between social classes in a society.","main_translations_es":["Movilidad social","Ascenso social","Movilidad de clase"],"collocations":["intergenerational social mobility","enhance social mobility","promote social mobility"],"example_sentence":"Social mobility is a key indicator of equal opportunity in a society.","example_es":"La movilidad social es un indicador clave de la igualdad de oportunidades en una sociedad.","example_en":"Social mobility is a key indicator of equal opportunity in a society.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Costo de vida","english_text":"Cost of living","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The amount of money required to cover basic expenses such as housing, food, taxes, and healthcare in a specific location.","main_translations_es":["Costo de vida"],"collocations":["cost of living index","cost of living adjustment","cost of living expenses","cost of living in"],"example_sentence":"The cost of living in Madrid is very high.","example_es":"El costo de vida en Madrid es muy alto.","example_en":"The cost of living in Madrid is very high.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Inflación","english_text":"Inflation","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A general increase in prices and a corresponding decline in the purchasing power of money.","main_translations_es":["Alza de precios","Aumento de precios","Crecimiento de precios"],"collocations":["inflation rate","inflationary pressure","inflation-adjusted","inflation targeting"],"example_sentence":"Inflation has increased the cost of food.","example_es":"La inflación ha aumentado el costo de los alimentos.","example_en":"Inflation has increased the cost of food.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Recesión","english_text":"Recession","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A period of economic decline marked by reduced trade, production, and rising unemployment.","main_translations_es":["Depresión económica","Contracción económica","Crisis económica"],"collocations":["recession fears","deep recession","recession hit","recessionary pressures"],"example_sentence":"The recession has caused an increase in unemployment in the country.","example_es":"La recesión ha provocado un aumento del desempleo en el país.","example_en":"The recession has caused an increase in unemployment in the country.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Recuperación económica","english_text":"Economic recovery","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A period when an economy regains growth and improves after a downturn.","main_translations_es":["Reactivación económica","Recuperación de la economía","Rebote económico"],"collocations":["spur economic recovery","support economic recovery","accelerate economic recovery"],"example_sentence":"The country''s economic recovery has been faster than expected.","example_es":"La recuperación económica del país ha sido más rápida de lo esperado.","example_en":"The country''s economic recovery has been faster than expected.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Mercado laboral","english_text":"Labor market","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The supply of workers and the demand for jobs in an economy, encompassing employment conditions and opportunities.","main_translations_es":["mercado de trabajo","mercado de empleo","mercado laboral"],"collocations":["tight labor market","labor market conditions","labor market trends","labor market analysis"],"example_sentence":"The labor market is experiencing a high demand for technology professionals.","example_es":"El mercado laboral está experimentando una alta demanda de profesionales de tecnología.","example_en":"The labor market is experiencing a high demand for technology professionals.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Crisis habitacional","english_text":"Housing crisis","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A situation in which the supply of affordable housing is insufficient to meet demand, causing widespread difficulty in obtaining suitable homes.","main_translations_es":["Crisis de la vivienda","Escasez de vivienda","Problema de vivienda"],"collocations":["address the housing crisis","housing crisis is worsening","impact of the housing crisis","solve the housing crisis"],"example_sentence":"The housing crisis is forcing many families to seek shelter in temporary homes.","example_es":"La crisis habitacional está obligando a muchas familias a buscar refugio en viviendas temporales.","example_en":"The housing crisis is forcing many families to seek shelter in temporary homes.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sin techo","english_text":"Homeless","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person who lacks a permanent residence or home.","main_translations_es":["Sin hogar","Desamparado","Persona sin techo"],"collocations":["homeless shelter","homeless population","homeless crisis","homeless youth"],"example_sentence":"After the fire, he was left homeless and had to find shelter.","example_es":"Después del incendio, quedó sin techo y tuvo que buscar refugio.","example_en":"After the fire, he was left homeless and had to find shelter.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Atención sanitaria","english_text":"Healthcare","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The organized provision of medical services to maintain or improve people''s health.","main_translations_es":["Cuidado de la salud","Servicios de salud","Asistencia sanitaria"],"collocations":["healthcare system","healthcare provider","affordable healthcare","healthcare industry"],"example_sentence":"Access to healthcare is a fundamental right.","example_es":"El acceso a la atención sanitaria es un derecho fundamental.","example_en":"Access to healthcare is a fundamental right.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Salud mental","english_text":"Mental health","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A state of psychological well‑being that enables a person to handle daily stresses, work productively, and contribute to society.","main_translations_es":["Bienestar mental","Salud psicológica","Salud de la mente"],"collocations":["mental health care","mental health issues","mental health awareness","mental health services"],"example_sentence":"Mental health is as important as physical health.","example_es":"La salud mental es tan importante como la salud física.","example_en":"Mental health is as important as physical health.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Bienestar","english_text":"Well-being","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A state of being comfortable, healthy, or happy.","main_translations_es":["Salud","Plenitud","Bienestar"],"collocations":["mental well-being","physical well-being","overall well-being","well-being of the community"],"example_sentence":"The exercise program improves the participants'' well-being.","example_es":"El programa de ejercicios mejora el bienestar de los participantes.","example_en":"The exercise program improves the participants'' well-being.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":