amente.","example_en":"The algorithm found the information quickly.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Inteligencia artificial","english_text":"Artificial intelligence","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Artificial intelligence is the branch of computer science that develops systems capable of performing tasks that normally require human intelligence.","main_translations_es":["Inteligencia artificial","IA","Inteligencia de máquinas"],"collocations":["artificial intelligence technology","artificial intelligence applications","artificial intelligence research"],"example_sentence":"Artificial intelligence is transforming the medical industry.","example_es":"La inteligencia artificial está transformando la industria médica.","example_en":"Artificial intelligence is transforming the medical industry.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Automatización","english_text":"Automation","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The use of technology or machines to perform tasks without human intervention.","main_translations_es":["Automatización","Robotización","Mecanización"],"collocations":["automation technology","automation process","automation system","automation industry"],"example_sentence":"Automation of manufacturing processes has increased efficiency.","example_es":"La automatización de los procesos de fabricación ha aumentado la eficiencia.","example_en":"Automation of manufacturing processes has increased efficiency.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Desinformación algorítmica","english_text":"Algorithmic misinformation","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"False or misleading information that is generated, spread, or amplified by algorithms.","main_translations_es":["Desinformación generada por algoritmos","Información errónea algorítmica"],"collocations":["combat algorithmic misinformation","address algorithmic misinformation","algorithmic misinformation campaigns","spread of algorithmic misinformation"],"example_sentence":"Algorithmic misinformation spreads quickly on social media.","example_es":"La desinformación algorítmica se propaga rápidamente en las redes sociales.","example_en":"Algorithmic misinformation spreads quickly on social media.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cambio climático","english_text":"Climate change","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A long-term alteration in Earth''s average weather patterns, primarily caused by human activities that increase greenhouse gases.","main_translations_es":["Calentamiento global","Alteración climática"],"collocations":["climate change mitigation","climate change adaptation","address climate change"],"example_sentence":"Climate change is affecting the glaciers.","example_es":"El cambio climático está afectando a los glaciares.","example_en":"Climate change is affecting the glaciers.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Calentamiento global","english_text":"Global warming","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A long-term rise in Earth''s average atmospheric temperature caused primarily by human activities that increase greenhouse gas concentrations.","main_translations_es":["Calentamiento del planeta","Calentamiento climático"],"collocations":["combat global warming","effects of global warming","global warming mitigation","global warming is a serious issue"],"example_sentence":"Global warming is causing extreme weather events.","example_es":"El calentamiento global está provocando fenómenos climáticos extremos.","example_en":"Global warming is causing extreme weather events.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Emisiones","english_text":"Emissions","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Substances, especially gases or particles, released into the atmosphere, typically as a result of industrial processes or combustion.","main_translations_es":["Descargas","Vertidos","Emanaciones"],"collocations":["greenhouse gas emissions","carbon emissions","emissions standards","emissions testing"],"example_sentence":"The CO₂ emissions from the factory have increased this year.","example_es":"Las emisiones de CO₂ de la fábrica han aumentado este año.","example_en":"The CO₂ emissions from the factory have increased this year.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Huella de carbono","english_text":"Carbon footprint","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The total amount of greenhouse gases emitted directly or indirectly by a person, organization, event, or product.","main_translations_es":["Huella de carbono","Impacto de carbono","Emisión de CO₂"],"collocations":["reduce your carbon footprint","measure your carbon footprint","carbon footprint calculator","carbon footprint assessment"],"example_sentence":"Reducing our carbon footprint is essential to combat climate change.","example_es":"Reducir nuestra huella de carbono es esencial para combatir el cambio climático.","example_en":"Reducing our carbon footprint is essential to combat climate change.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Energía renovable","english_text":"Renewable energy","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Energy obtained from naturally replenished sources such as sunlight, wind, rain, tides, waves, and geothermal heat.","main_translations_es":["Energía limpia","Energía sostenible","Energía verde"],"collocations":["renewable energy sources","renewable energy sector","renewable energy projects","renewable energy investment"],"example_sentence":"Renewable energy reduces dependence on fossil fuels.","example_es":"La energía renovable reduce la dependencia de los combustibles fósiles.","example_en":"Renewable energy reduces dependence on fossil fuels.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Combustibles fósiles","english_text":"Fossil fuels","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Natural resources such as coal, oil, and natural gas formed from ancient organic matter and used as energy sources.","main_translations_es":["Combustibles no renovables","Energías fósiles","Recursos fósiles"],"collocations":["fossil fuel consumption","fossil fuel emissions","fossil fuel industry","fossil fuel dependence"],"example_sentence":"Fossil fuels are the main source of energy in the world.","example_es":"Los combustibles fósiles son la principal fuente de energía en el mundo.","example_en":"Fossil fuels are the main source of energy in the world.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sequía","english_text":"Drought","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A prolonged period of abnormally low rainfall that results in a shortage of water.","main_translations_es":["Escasez de agua","Falta de lluvia","Sequía prolongada"],"collocations":["drought conditions","drought relief","drought-resistant","drought-stricken"],"example_sentence":"The drought has reduced the corn harvest this year.","example_es":"La sequía ha reducido la cosecha de maíz este año.","example_en":"The drought has reduced the corn harvest this year.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Inundación","english_text":"Flood","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A large amount of water that covers land which is normally dry.","main_translations_es":["Desbordamiento","Aluvión","Inundación"],"collocations":["flood the market","flood of complaints","flood damage","flood plain"],"example_sentence":"The flood destroyed several houses in the town.","example_es":"La inundación destruyó varias casas en el pueblo.","example_en":"The flood destroyed several houses in the town.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Ola de calor","english_text":"Heatwave","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A prolonged period of excessively hot weather.","main_translations_es":["ola de calor","ola de calor intensa","ola de calor extremo"],"collocations":["heatwave warning","record-breaking heatwave","heatwave conditions","heatwave season"],"example_sentence":"This week there was a heatwave that reached 40 degrees.","example_es":"Esta semana hubo una ola de calor que alcanzó los 40 grados.","example_en":"This week there was a heatwave that reached 40 degrees.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Conservación","english_text":"Conservation","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The protection, preservation, or careful management of natural resources and the environment.","main_translations_es":["Preservación","Protección","Cuidado"],"collocations":["wildlife conservation","conservation efforts","conservation area","conservationist"],"example_sentence":"The conservation of forests is essential to combat climate change.","example_es":"La conservación de los bosques es esencial para combatir el cambio climático.","example_en":"The conservation of forests is essential to combat climate change.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Biodiversidad","english_text":"Biodiversity","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The variety of living organisms and their ecological interactions within a given area or across the planet.","main_translations_es":["Diversidad biológica","Variedad de especies","Riqueza biológica"],"collocations":["biodiversity loss","biodiversity conservation","biodiversity hotspot","biodiversity crisis"],"example_sentence":"Biodiversity is essential for the balance of the ecosystem.","example_es":"La biodiversidad es esencial para el equilibrio del ecosistema.","example_en":"Biodiversity is essential for the balance of the ecosystem.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Deforestación","english_text":"Deforestation","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The removal or clearing of trees and forested land, typically for human use such as agriculture or development.","main_translations_es":["Desforestación","Pérdida de bosques","Talado de bosques"],"collocations":["deforestation rates","deforestation and climate change","combat deforestation","reduce deforestation"],"example_sentence":"Deforestation is causing habitat loss in the Amazon.","example_es":"La deforestación está provocando la pérdida de hábitats en la Amazonía.","example_en":"Deforestation is causing habitat loss in the Amazon.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Contaminación","english_text":"Pollution","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Pollution is the introduction of harmful substances or energy into the environment.","main_translations_es":["Polución","Contaminación ambiental","Contaminación del aire"],"collocations":["air pollution","water pollution","pollution control","pollution levels"],"example_sentence":"Air pollution is worsening the health of the population.","example_es":"La contaminación del aire está empeorando la salud de la población.","example_en":"Air pollution is worsening the health of the population.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Desperdicio","english_text":"Waste","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Waste is material, resources, or energy that is discarded, unused, or considered useless.","main_translations_es":["Desperdicio","Derroche","Pérdida"],"collocations":["waste of time","waste management","waste disposal","waste water"],"example_sentence":"Food waste is a serious problem.","example_es":"El desperdicio de alimentos es un problema grave.","example_en":"Food waste is a serious problem.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Reciclaje","english_text":"Recycling","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of collecting and converting waste materials into new, usable products.","main_translations_es":["Reciclado","Reciclaje de residuos","Gestión de reciclaje"],"collocations":["recycling program","recycling bin","recycling center","recycling industry"],"example_sentence":"Recycling helps protect the environment.","example_es":"El reciclaje ayuda a proteger el medio ambiente.","example_en":"Recycling helps protect the environment.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Economía circular","english_text":"Circular economy","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"An economic system that aims to minimize waste and maximize resource use by reusing, repairing, refurbishing, and recycling materials and products.","main_translations_es":["Economía circular","Modelo de economía circular","Sistema de economía circular"],"collocations":["circular economy model","circular economy principles","circular economy approach","circular economy initiatives"],"example_sentence":"The company has adopted the circular economy to reduce its waste.","example_es":"La empresa ha adoptado la economía circular para reducir sus residuos.","example_en":"The company has adopted the circular economy to reduce its waste.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Seguridad alimentaria","english_text":"Food security","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Food security is the condition in which all people have reliable access to sufficient, safe, and nutritious food.","main_translations_es":["Seguridad alimentaria","Seguridad en la alimentación","Garantía alimentaria"],"collocations":["food security policy","food security challenges","global food security","food security and nutrition"],"example_sentence":"Food security is essential for sustainable development.","example_es":"La seguridad alimentaria es esencial para el desarrollo sostenible.","example_en":"Food security is essential for sustainable development.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Escasez de agua","english_text":"Water scarcity","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A condition in which there is insufficient available water to meet the needs of a region or population.","main_translations_es":["Falta de agua","Déficit hídrico","Escasez hídrica"],"collocations":["address water scarcity","water scarcity crisis","combat water scarcity","water scarcity issues"],"example_sentence":"Water scarcity is affecting millions of people worldwide.","example_es":"La escasez de agua está afectando a millones de personas en todo el mundo.","example_en":"Water scarcity is affecting millions of people worldwide.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cadena de suministro","english_text":"Supply chain","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A network of organizations, activities, and resources that moves a product or service from supplier to customer.","main_translations_es":["Red de suministro","Cadena logística","Sistema de suministro"],"collocations":["supply chain management","global supply chain","supply chain disruption","supply chain network"],"example_sentence":"The company is optimizing its supply chain to reduce costs.","example_es":"La empresa está optimizando su cadena de suministro para reducir costos.","example_en":"The company is optimizing its supply chain to reduce costs.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Interrupción","english_text":"Disruption","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A disturbance or interruption that prevents something from continuing smoothly.","main_translations_es":["Corte","Parada","Suspensión"],"collocations":["cause disruption","disruption of services","major disruption","disruption in the market"],"example_sentence":"The disruption of the power supply left the city without electricity.","example_es":"La interrupción del suministro eléctrico dejó a la ciudad sin luz.","example_en":"The disruption of the power supply left the city without electricity.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Escalada","english_text":"Escalation","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A rapid increase or intensification, especially of a conflict, problem, or situation.","main_translations_es":["Subida","Ascenso","Trepar"],"collocations":["escalation of conflict","price escalation","rapid escalation","escalation clause"],"example_sentence":"The escalation of the conflict surprised everyone.","example_es":"La escalada del conflicto sorprendió a todos.","example_en":"The escalation of the conflict surprised everyone.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Alto el fuego","english_text":"Ceasefire","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A temporary suspension of fighting between opposing sides.","main_translations_es":["Cese del fuego","Alto al fuego","Alto al combate"],"collocations":["call for a ceasefire","agree to a ceasefire","observe a ceasefire","hold a ceasefire"],"example_sentence":"Ceasefire, before more people get hurt.","example_es":"Alto el fuego, antes de que más personas resulten heridas.","example_en":"Ceasefire, before more people get hurt.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sanción","english_text":"Sanction","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A penalty imposed for violating a law, rule, or regulation.","main_translations_es":["Castigo","Multa","Penalización"],"collocations":["impose sanctions","economic sanctions","sanctioned by the UN","sanction a law"],"example_sentence":"The committee decided to impose a sanction of ten thousand euros on the club for violating the rules.","example_es":"El comité decidió imponer una sanción de diez mil euros al club por incumplir las normas.","example_en":"The committee decided to impose a sanction of ten thousand euros on the club for violating the rules.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Ayuda humanitaria","english_text":"Humanitarian aid","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Assistance given to people in need, especially during crises or disasters, to alleviate suffering and protect life and health.","main_translations_es":["Asistencia humanitaria","Socorro humanitario","Apoyo humanitario"],"collocations":["provide humanitarian aid","humanitarian aid efforts","humanitarian aid organization","humanitarian aid funding"],"example_sentence":"Humanitarian aid arrived in the area affected by the earthquake.","example_es":"La ayuda humanitaria llegó a la zona afectada por el terremoto.","example_en":"Humanitarian aid arrived in the area affected by the earthquake.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Desplazamiento forzado","english_text":"Forced displacement","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The involuntary movement of people from their homes or habitual residence, usually caused by conflict, persecution, or natural disasters.","main_translations_es":["Desplazamiento forzado","Desplazamiento involuntario","Desplazamiento obligado"],"collocations":["forced displacement crisis","forced displacement of populations","address forced displacement","prevent forced displacement"],"example_sentence":"The forced displacement of thousands of families has created a humanitarian crisis.","example_es":"El desplazamiento forzado de miles de familias ha creado una crisis humanitaria.","example_en":"The forced displacement of thousands of families has created a humanitarian crisis.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Derechos humanos","english_text":"Human rights","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Fundamental rights and freedoms that belong to every person simply because they are human.","main_translations_es":["Derechos fundamentales","Derechos civiles","Derechos de la persona"],"collocations":["human rights violations","human rights activist","human rights law","human rights organization"],"example_sentence":"Human rights must be respected worldwide.","example_es":"Los derechos humanos deben ser respetados en todo el mundo.","example_en":"Human rights must be respected worldwide.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Libertad de expresión","english_text":"Freedom of speech","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The right to express one''s opinions publicly without censorship or restraint.","main_translations_es":["Libertad de expresión","Derecho a la libre expresión","Libertad de opinión"],"collocations":["freedom of speech is essential","protect freedom of speech","advocate for freedom of speech","freedom of speech rights"],"example_sentence":"Freedom of speech is a fundamental right in a democracy.","example_es":"La libertad de expresión es un derecho fundamental en una democracia.","example_en":"Freedom of speech is a fundamental right in a democracy.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Estado de derecho","english_text":"Rule of law","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The principle that all individuals and institutions, including the government, are bound by and accountable to publicly known laws.","main_translations_es":["Estado de la ley","ordenamiento jurídico","régimen de derecho"],"collocations":["uphold the rule of law","rule of law principles","rule of law framework","rule of law and democracy"],"example_sentence":"In a rule of law system, all citizens are subject to the same legislation.","example_es":"En un Estado de derecho, todos los ciudadanos están sujetos a la misma legislación.","example_en":"In a rule of law system, all citizens are subject to the same legislation.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Reforma","english_text":"Reform","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A change made to improve a system, institution, or practice.","main_translations_es":["Modificación","Cambio","Reajuste"],"collocations":["tax reform","education reform","healthcare reform"],"example_sentence":"The reform of the education system will be approved next month.","example_es":"La reforma del sistema educativo será aprobada el próximo mes.","example_en":"The reform of the education system will be approved next month.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Protesta","english_text":"Protest","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"An expression of objection or disapproval, often manifested in a public demonstration.","main_translations_es":["manifestación","marcha","rebelión"],"collocations":["peaceful protest","protest march","protest against","protest rally"],"example_sentence":"The students organized a protest against the school policy.","example_es":"Los estudiantes organizaron una protesta contra la política escolar.","example_en":"The students organized a protest against the school policy.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Manifestación","english_text":"Demonstration","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A public protest or a presentation that shows how something works.","main_translations_es":["Protesta","Exhibición","Muestra"],"collocations":["public demonstration","demonstration of skill","scientific demonstration"],"example_sentence":"The demonstration against the labor reform attracted thousands of people.","example_es":"La manifestación contra la reforma laboral atrajo a miles de personas.","example_en":"The demonstration against the labor reform attracted thousands of people.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Activismo","english_text":"Activism","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Activism is the practice of organized efforts to promote or oppose social, political, or environmental change.","main_translations_es":["Activismo","Activismo social","Activismo político"],"collocations":["grassroots activism","environmental activism","political activism","social activism"],"example_sentence":"Youth activism has driven significant changes in environmental policy.","example_es":"El activismo juvenil ha impulsado cambios significativos en la política ambiental.","example_en":"Youth activism has driven significant changes in environmental policy.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Movilización","english_text":"Mobilization","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The act of assembling and preparing troops or resources for active service.","main_translations_es":["Movilización","Despliegue","Activación"],"collocations":["mass mobilization","resource mobilization","mobilization effort","mobilization plan"],"example_sentence":"The mobilization of resources was key to the project''s success.","example_es":"La movilización de los recursos fue clave para el éxito del proyecto.","example_en":"The mobilization of resources was key to the project''s success.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Conciencia pública","english_text":"Public awareness","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the state of being informed or conscious about a particular issue among the general public","main_translations_es":["conciencia colectiva","conciencia social","conciencia ciudadana"],"collocations":["raise public awareness","public awareness campaign","increase public awareness","public awareness of"],"example_sentence":"The campaign raised public awareness about climate change.","example_es":"La campaña aumentó la conciencia pública sobre el cambio climático.","example_en":"The campaign raised public awareness about climate change.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Narrativa","english_text":"Narrative","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A spoken or written account of connected events; a story.","main_translations_es":["Relato","Historia","Crónica"],"collocations":["narrative structure","narrative voice","narrative arc","narrative perspective"],"example_sentence":"The narrative of the novel captures the essence of the era.","example_es":"La narrativa de la novela captura la esencia de la época.","example_en":"The narrative of the novel captures the essence of the era.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sesgo mediático","english_text":"Media bias","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A tendency of journalists or news outlets to present information in a way that favors a particular perspective or agenda.","main_translations_es":["Parcialidad mediática","Sesgo de los medios","Tendencia mediática"],"collocations":["media bias affects public opinion","combat media bias","perceived media bias","media bias in reporting"],"example_sentence":"Media bias affects the way we perceive the news.","example_es":"El sesgo mediático afecta la forma en que percibimos las noticias.","example_en":"Media bias affects the way we perceive the news.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Verificación de hechos","english_text":"Fact-checking","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of verifying the accuracy of information or claims.","main_translations_es":["Chequeo de datos","Contraste de hechos","Comprobación de hechos"],"collocations":["fact-checking process","fact-checking organization","fact-checking tools","fact-checking report"],"example_sentence":"Fact-checking is essential to combat misinformation.","example_es":"La verificación de hechos es esencial para combatir la desinformación.","example_en":"Fact-checking is essential to combat misinformation.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Difundirse","english_text":"Spread rapidly","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To become widely known or distributed quickly.","main_translations_es":["propagarse","extenderse","diseminarse"],"collocations":["spread like wildfire","spread quickly","spread fast","spread at a rapid pace"],"example_sentence":"The rumor spread rapidly throughout the neighborhood.","example_es":"El rumor se difundió rápidamente por todo el vecindario.","example_en":"The rumor spread rapidly throughout the neighborhood.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Volverse viral","english_text":"Go viral","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"to become widely circulated on the internet, especially through rapid sharing.","main_translations_es":["Hacerse viral","Convertirse en viral","Tornar viral"],"collocations":["go viral on social media","go viral overnight","go viral quickly","go viral instantly"],"example_sentence":"The video went viral within hours.","example_es":"El video se volvió viral en cuestión de horas.","example_en":"The video went viral within hours.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Repercusiones","english_text":"Repercussions","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Unintended or indirect consequences of an action or event, often negative.","main_translations_es":["Consecuencias","Efectos","Resultados"],"collocations":["face the repercussions","have repercussions","repercussions of","suffer the repercussions"],"example_sentence":"The repercussions of the decision will be felt for years.","example_es":"Las repercusiones de la decisión se sentirán durante años.","example_en":"The repercussions of the decision will be felt for years.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Consecuencia imprevista","english_text":"Unintended consequence","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"An outcome that was not intended or expected.","main_translations_es":["Resultado inesperado","Efecto inesperado","Repercusiones no previstas"],"collocations":["as an unintended consequence","the unintended consequence","unintended consequence of","unintended consequence for"],"example_sentence":"The unintended consequence of his policy was an unexpected rise in inflation.","example_es":"La consecuencia imprevista de su política fue un aumento inesperado de la inflación.","example_en":"The unintended consequence of his policy was an unexpected rise in inflation.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Resiliencia","english_text":"Resilience","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The ability to recover quickly from difficulties or to adapt in the face of adversity.","main_translations_es":["Capacidad de recuperación","Fortaleza mental","Elasticidad"],"collocations":["building resilience","resilience in the face of adversity","show resilience","resilience training"],"example_sentence":"The community''s resilience allowed it to recover quickly after the earthquake.","example_es":"La resiliencia de la comunidad le permitió recuperarse rápidamente después del terremoto.","example_en":"The community''s resilience allowed it to recover quickly after the earthquake.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Capacidad de adaptación","english_text":"Adaptability","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The ability to adjust to new conditions or changes.","main_translations_es":["Flexibilidad","Capacidad de ajuste","Aptitud para adaptarse"],"collocations":["adaptability is key","high adaptability","demonstrate adaptability","adaptability skills"],"example_sentence":"His adaptability allowed him to overcome the changes at work.","example_es":"Su capacidad de adaptación le permitió superar los cambios en el trabajo.","example_en":"His adaptability allowed him to overcome the changes at work.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Interdependencia","english_text":"Interdependence","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the mutual reliance between two or more entities, where each depends on the others.","main_translations_es":["Mutua dependencia","Dependencia recíproca","Interrelación"],"collocations":["mutual interdependence","economic interdependence","global interdependence","interdependence theory"],"example_sentence":"The interdependence among Latin American countries is reflected in their trade agreements.","example_es":"La interdependencia entre los países latinoamericanos se refleja en sus acuerdos comerciales.","example_en":"The interdependence among Latin American countries is reflected in their trade agreements.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Consenso científico","english_text":"Scientific consensus","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"General agreement among scientists about a particular scientific finding or theory.","main_translations_es":["acuerdo científico","consenso de la comunidad científica","posicionamiento científico"],"collocations":["reach a scientific consensus","scientific consensus on climate change","widely accepted scientific consensus","the scientific consensus is that"],"example_sentence":"The scientific consensus indicates that climate change is primarily caused by human activity.","example_es":"El consenso científico indica que el cambio climático es causado principalmente por la actividad humana.","example_en":"The scientific consensus indicates that climate change is primarily caused by human activity.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Debate ético","english_text":"Ethical debate","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A discussion that examines moral principles and values.","main_translations_es":["Discusión ética","Debate moral","Diálogo ético"],"collocations":["engage in an ethical debate","participate in an ethical debate","ethical debate on climate change","ethical debate surrounding AI"],"example_sentence":"The ethical debate about genetic editing is very controversial.","example_es":"El debate ético sobre la edición genética es muy controvertido.","example_en":"The ethical debate about genetic editing is very controversial.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Brecha generacional","english_text":"Generation gap","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A difference in attitudes, values, and experiences between people of different generations.","main_translations_es":["brecha generacional","diferencia generacional","distancia generacional"],"collocations":["bridge the generation gap","close the generation gap","widen the generation gap","generation gap issues"],"example_sentence":"The generation gap between young people and their parents is evident in their use of technology.","example_es":"La brecha generacional entre los jóvenes y sus padres se hace evidente en el uso de la tecnología.","example_en":"The generation gap between young people and their parents is evident in their use of technology.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Presión social","english_text":"Social pressure","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The influence exerted by a group or society on an individual''s behavior or decisions.","main_translations_es":["presión social","presión de grupo","presión colectiva"],"collocations":["under social pressure","succumb to social pressure","resist social pressure","social pressure to conform"],"example_sentence":"Social pressure led him to quit his job.","example_es":"La presión social lo llevó a dejar su trabajo.","example_en":"Social pressure led him to quit his job.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cohesión social","english_text":"Social cohesion","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The bonds, shared values, and sense of belonging that hold members of a society together.","main_translations_es":["Cooperación social","Solidaridad social","Integración social"],"collocations":["promote social cohesion","strengthen social cohesion","enhance social cohesion","social cohesion initiatives"],"example_sentence":"Social cohesion is essential for the community''s development.","example_es":"La cohesión social es fundamental para el desarrollo de la comunidad.","example_en":"Social cohesion is essential for the community''s development.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sentimiento de pertenencia","english_text":"Sense of belonging","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A feeling of being accepted and valued as part of a group or community.","main_translations_es":["Sentido de pertenencia","Sensación de pertenencia","Pertenencia"],"collocations":["foster a sense of belonging","enhance the sense of belonging","create a sense of belonging","sense of belonging"],"example_sentence":"The sense of belonging he feels in his community motivates him to participate actively.","example_es":"El sentimiento de pertenencia que experimenta en su comunidad lo motiva a participar activamente.","example_en":"The sense of belonging he feels in his community motivates him to participate actively.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Marginalización","english_text":"Marginalization","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of treating a person or group as insignificant or peripheral.","main_translations_es":["Exclusión","Segregación","Marginación"],"collocations":["social marginalization","economic marginalization","cultural marginalization","political marginalization"],"example_sentence":"The marginalization of rural communities hinders their access to basic services.","example_es":"La marginalización de las comunidades rurales dificulta su acceso a servicios básicos.","example_en":"The marginalization of rural communities hinders their access to basic services.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Empoderamiento","english_text":"Empowerment","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of giving someone authority, confidence, or power to act or make decisions.","main_translations_es":["Capacitación","Fortalecimiento","Autonomía"],"collocations":["women''s empowerment","employee empowerment","community empowerment","empowerment program"],"example_sentence":"The empowerment of women is essential for sustainable development.","example_es":"El empoderamiento de las mujeres es fundamental para el desarrollo sostenible.","example_en":"The empowerment of women is essential for sustainable development.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Justicia climática","english_text":"Climate justice","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Climate justice is the principle of ensuring fair and equitable treatment of all people in the distribution of climate change impacts and responsibilities.","main_translations_es":["Equidad climática","Justicia ambiental del clima"],"collocations":["climate justice movement","climate justice framework","climate justice initiatives"],"example_sentence":"Climate justice demands that rich countries cut their emissions to protect the most vulnerable.","example_es":"La justicia climática exige que los países ricos reduzcan sus emisiones para proteger a los más vulnerables.","example_en":"Climate justice demands that rich countries cut their emissions to protect the most vulnerable.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Justicia social","english_text":"Social justice","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A principle of fairness that seeks equitable distribution of resources, rights, and opportunities within a society.","main_translations_es":["Justicia social","Equidad social","Igualdad social"],"collocations":["social justice movement","social justice issues","social justice advocacy","social justice initiatives"],"example_sentence":"The movement fights for social justice in the community.","example_es":"El movimiento lucha por la justicia social en la comunidad.","example_en":"The movement fights for social justice in the community.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Responsabilidad compartida","english_text":"Shared responsibility","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A situation in which two or more parties are jointly accountable for an outcome.","main_translations_es":["Responsabilidad conjunta","Responsabilidad mutua","Responsabilidad colectiva"],"collocations":["shared responsibility for","shared responsibility between","shared responsibility model","shared responsibility approach"],"example_sentence":"Shared responsibility between parents and teachers is essential for the student''s success.","example_es":"La responsabilidad compartida entre los padres y los maestros es esencial para el éxito del estudiante.","example_en":"Shared responsibility between parents and teachers is essential for the student''s success.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Tema candente","english_text":"Hot-button issue","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A controversial or emotionally charged topic that provokes strong opinions.","main_translations_es":["Asunto polémico","Cuestión delicada","Tema controvertido"],"collocations":["raise a hot‑button issue","address a hot‑button issue","hot‑button issue in politics"],"example_sentence":"Climate change has become a hot‑button issue in international politics.","example_es":"El cambio climático se ha convertido en un tema candente en la política internacional.","example_en":"Climate change has become a hot‑button issue in international politics.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Amplia repercusión","english_text":"Far-reaching impact","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"A significant or extensive effect or influence.","main_translations_es":["Gran repercusión","Amplio alcance","Extensa influencia"],"collocations":["has a far‑reaching impact","far‑reaching impact on society","with far‑reaching impact","far‑reaching impact on the economy"],"example_sentence":"The new law will have a far-reaching impact on the country''s economy.","example_es":"La nueva ley tendrá una amplia repercusión en la economía del país.","example_en":"The new law will have a far-reaching impact on the country''s economy.","mnemonic_en":null}]'::jsonb) as x(
  spanish_text text, english_text text, section_name text, part_of_speech text, definition_en text,
  main_translations_es jsonb, collocations jsonb, example_sentence text, example_es text, example_en text, mnemonic_en text
)
where not exists (
  select 1 from public.cards c2
  where c2.deck_id = dk.id
    and lower(c2.spanish_text) = lower(x.spanish_text)
    and lower(c2.english_text) = lower(x.english_text)
);

-- english-advanced-phrasal-verbs (110 cards)
insert into public.decks (slug, title, description, language_from, language_to)
values ('english-advanced-phrasal-verbs', 'Advanced Phrasal Verbs', 'A large deck of phrasal verbs and common advanced uses to improve fluency and natural expression.', 'es', 'en')
on conflict (slug) do nothing;

insert into public.cards (deck_id, spanish_text, english_text, is_enabled, generation_phase, generation_metadata, section_name, part_of_speech, definition_en, main_translations_es, collocations, example_sentence, example_es, example_en, mnemonic_en)
select dk.id, x.spanish_text, x.english_text, true, 'refined', '{}'::jsonb, x.section_name, x.part_of_speech, x.definition_en,
       coalesce(x.main_translations_es, '[]'::jsonb), coalesce(x.collocations, '[]'::jsonb), x.example_sentence, x.example_es, x.example_en, x.mnemonic_en
from (select id from public.decks where slug = 'english-advanced-phrasal-verbs') dk
cross join jsonb_to_recordset('[{"spanish_text":"Mencionar","english_text":"Bring up","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to mention or raise a topic for discussion","main_translations_es":["Citar","Aludir","Referir"],"collocations":["bring up a topic","bring up an issue","bring up a child","bring up the subject"],"example_sentence":"During the meeting, Juan brought up the budget issue.","example_es":"Durante la reunión, Juan mencionó el problema del presupuesto.","example_en":"During the meeting, Juan brought up the budget issue.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Llevar a cabo","english_text":"Carry out","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to perform or execute a task or plan","main_translations_es":["realizar","ejecutar","desarrollar"],"collocations":["carry out a plan","carry out an experiment","carry out the investigation","carry out duties"],"example_sentence":"The committee decided to carry out the investigation next week.","example_es":"El comité decidió llevar a cabo la investigación la próxima semana.","example_en":"The committee decided to carry out the investigation next week.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Encontrarse con","english_text":"Come across","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to find or meet something or someone by chance","main_translations_es":["Toparse con","Tropezar con","Dar con"],"collocations":["come across as","come across something","come across unexpectedly"],"example_sentence":"I came across an old friend at the market.","example_es":"Me encontré con un viejo amigo en el mercado.","example_en":"I came across an old friend at the market.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Idear","english_text":"Come up with","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To think of or produce an idea, plan, or solution.","main_translations_es":["concebir","inventar","elaborar"],"collocations":["come up with an idea","come up with a solution","come up with a plan","come up with a name"],"example_sentence":"We need to come up with a solution before the day ends.","example_es":"Necesitamos idear una solución antes de que termine el día.","example_en":"We need to come up with a solution before the day ends.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Reducir","english_text":"Cut down on","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to reduce the amount or frequency of something","main_translations_es":["Disminuir","Recortar","Ajustar"],"collocations":["cut down on sugar","cut down on expenses","cut down on smoking"],"example_sentence":"I need to cut down on sugar consumption.","example_es":"Necesito reducir el consumo de azúcar.","example_en":"I need to cut down on sugar consumption.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Eliminar","english_text":"Do away with","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To eliminate or get rid of something.","main_translations_es":["Borrar","Suprimir","Quitar"],"collocations":["do away with poverty","do away with the old system","do away with unnecessary rules"],"example_sentence":"The government decided to do away with import taxes.","example_es":"El gobierno decidió eliminar los impuestos a la importación.","example_en":"The government decided to do away with import taxes.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Resolver","english_text":"Figure out","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To understand or solve something by thinking about it.","main_translations_es":["Resolver","Solucionar","Despejar"],"collocations":["figure out the problem","figure out how","figure out why","figure out the solution"],"example_sentence":"I need to figure out this problem before the meeting.","example_es":"Necesito resolver este problema antes de la reunión.","example_en":"I need to figure out this problem before the meeting.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Rellenar","english_text":"Fill in","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To complete something by adding missing information.","main_translations_es":["Completar","Llenar","Ingresar"],"collocations":["fill in the blanks","fill in the form","fill in the details"],"example_sentence":"Please fill in the form before the deadline.","example_es":"Por favor, rellena el formulario antes de la fecha límite.","example_en":"Please fill in the form before the deadline.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cumplir hasta el final","english_text":"Follow through","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To continue an action or task until it is completed.","main_translations_es":["Cumplir hasta el final","Llevar a cabo","Ver hasta el final"],"collocations":["follow through on","follow through with","see it through","carry out"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to follow through with the projects we start.","example_es":"Es importante cumplir hasta el final con los proyectos que iniciamos.","example_en":"It''s important to follow through with the projects we start.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Transmitir","english_text":"Get across","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To communicate or convey an idea, feeling, or message so that it is understood.","main_translations_es":["Comunicar","Transmitir","Pasar"],"collocations":["get the point across","get the message across","make sure it gets across"],"example_sentence":"The teacher managed to get the idea across clearly.","example_es":"El profesor logró transmitir la idea de manera clara.","example_en":"The teacher managed to get the idea across clearly.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Salirse con la suya","english_text":"Get away with","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To succeed in doing something that is disapproved of or illegal without being punished.","main_translations_es":["Salir impune","Escapar sin castigo","Quedarse con la razón"],"collocations":["get away with murder","get away with cheating","can''t get away with that","get away with it"],"example_sentence":"Juan tried to rob the store, but the police caught him before he could get away with it.","example_es":"Juan intentó robar la tienda, pero la policía lo atrapó antes de que pudiera salirse con la suya.","example_en":"Juan tried to rob the store, but the police caught him before he could get away with it.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Arreglárselas","english_text":"Get by","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to manage to survive or cope with a situation, often with limited resources.","main_translations_es":["Apañarse","Sobrevivir","Librarse"],"collocations":["get by on a salary","get by with difficulty","just get by","get by in life"],"example_sentence":"With so little money, I have to get by.","example_es":"Con tan poco dinero, tengo que arreglármelas.","example_en":"With so little money, I have to get by.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Superar","english_text":"Get over","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To recover from or move beyond something, such as an illness, difficulty, or emotional upset.","main_translations_es":["Vencer","Sobrepasar","Sobreponerse"],"collocations":["get over it","get over a cold","get over the loss","get over the hurdle"],"example_sentence":"I had to get over my fear of flying.","example_es":"Tuve que superar mi miedo a volar.","example_en":"I had to get over my fear of flying.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Ceder","english_text":"Give in","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to surrender or yield to someone or something","main_translations_es":["rendirse","ceder","conceder"],"collocations":["give in to pressure","give in to temptation","give in easily","give in finally"],"example_sentence":"After a long argument, he decided to give in to his demands.","example_es":"Después de mucho discutir, decidió ceder a sus demandas.","example_en":"After a long argument, he decided to give in to his demands.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Rendirse","english_text":"Give up","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To stop trying to achieve something or to surrender.","main_translations_es":["darse por vencido","ceder","abandonar"],"collocations":["give up smoking","give up on","give up the habit","give up the fight"],"example_sentence":"I won''t give up so easily.","example_es":"No voy a rendirme tan fácilmente.","example_en":"I won''t give up so easily.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Repasar","english_text":"Go over","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To examine or review something carefully.","main_translations_es":["Revisar","Estudiar","Repasar"],"collocations":["go over the details","go over the plan","go over the results","go over the material"],"example_sentence":"I will go over my notes before the exam.","example_es":"Voy a repasar mis notas antes del examen.","example_en":"I will go over my notes before the exam.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Crecer","english_text":"Grow up","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to develop from a child into an adult","main_translations_es":["Desarrollarse","Madurar","Aumentar"],"collocations":["grow up fast","grow up to be","grow up with","grow up in"],"example_sentence":"Children should grow up in a safe environment.","example_es":"Los niños deben crecer en un ambiente seguro.","example_en":"Children should grow up in a safe environment.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Entregar","english_text":"Hand in","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to submit something, such as a document or assignment, to the appropriate authority.","main_translations_es":["entregar","presentar","someter"],"collocations":["hand in your assignment","hand in a report","hand in the paperwork","hand in a resignation"],"example_sentence":"I have to hand in the report before five.","example_es":"Tengo que entregar el informe antes de las cinco.","example_en":"I have to hand in the report before five.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Reprimirse","english_text":"Hold back","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To restrain or keep something from progressing or being expressed.","main_translations_es":["contenerse","restringirse","autocontrolarse"],"collocations":["hold back tears","hold back the crowd","hold back emotions","hold back the tide"],"example_sentence":"You shouldn''t hold back and say what you feel.","example_es":"No deberías reprimirte y decir lo que sientes.","example_en":"You shouldn''t hold back and say what you feel.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Mantener el ritmo","english_text":"Keep up with","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To stay at the same level or pace as someone or something.","main_translations_es":["Seguir el ritmo","Mantener el paso","No quedarse atrás"],"collocations":["keep up with the latest trends","keep up with the news","keep up with your studies","keep up with the schedule"],"example_sentence":"It''s hard to keep up with the pace of the dance class.","example_es":"Es difícil mantener el ritmo de la clase de baile.","example_en":"It''s hard to keep up with the pace of the dance class.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Decepcionar","english_text":"Let down","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To disappoint someone or fail to meet their expectations.","main_translations_es":["Desilusionar","Desencantar"],"collocations":["let someone down","let down the team","let down the guard"],"example_sentence":"He didn''t want to let down his parents with his poor grades.","example_es":"No quería decepcionar a sus padres con sus malas notas.","example_en":"He didn''t want to let down his parents with his poor grades.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cuidar de","english_text":"Look after","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to take care of someone or something","main_translations_es":["cuidar","velar por","tener cuidado de"],"collocations":["look after the children","look after yourself","look after the house"],"example_sentence":"I have to look after my little brother while my parents are away.","example_es":"Tengo que cuidar de mi hermano pequeño mientras mis padres están fuera.","example_en":"I have to look after my little brother while my parents are away.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Investigar","english_text":"Look into","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to examine or investigate something in order to learn more about it","main_translations_es":["Indagar","Examinar","Investigar"],"collocations":["look into the matter","look into the issue","look into the problem","look into it"],"example_sentence":"I will look into the origin of the problem.","example_es":"Voy a investigar el origen del problema.","example_en":"I will look into the origin of the problem.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Admirar","english_text":"Look up to","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to regard someone with admiration and respect","main_translations_es":["Estimar","Respetar","Venerar"],"collocations":["look up to someone","look up to his father","look up to role models","look up to as an inspiration"],"example_sentence":"I have always looked up to my grandfather for his wisdom.","example_es":"Siempre he admirado a mi abuelo por su sabiduría.","example_en":"I have always looked up to my grandfather for his wisdom.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Compensar","english_text":"Make up for","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To compensate for something; to offset or counterbalance it.","main_translations_es":["Resarcir","Reparar","Compensar"],"collocations":["make up for lost time","make up for a mistake","make up for the damage","make up for the loss"],"example_sentence":"The raise makes up for the extra time he worked.","example_es":"El aumento de sueldo compensa el tiempo extra que trabajó.","example_en":"The raise makes up for the extra time he worked.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Seguir adelante","english_text":"Move on","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to continue or proceed to the next thing, especially after a difficulty or interruption","main_translations_es":["Continuar","Seguir","Avanzar"],"collocations":["move on to","move on from","move on with","move on quickly"],"example_sentence":"After the breakup, she decided to move on with her life.","example_es":"Después de la ruptura, decidió seguir adelante con su vida.","example_en":"After the breakup, she decided to move on with her life.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Señalar","english_text":"Point out","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To draw attention to something.","main_translations_es":["indicar","mostrar","apuntar"],"collocations":["point out the mistake","point out that","point out the differences","point out the importance"],"example_sentence":"The teacher pointed out the mistakes on the exam.","example_es":"El profesor señaló los errores en el examen.","example_en":"The teacher pointed out the mistakes on the exam.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Posponer","english_text":"Put off","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To delay or postpone something.","main_translations_es":["Aplazar","Postergar","Diferir"],"collocations":["put off the meeting","put off until later","put off doing something"],"example_sentence":"I will put off the meeting until tomorrow.","example_es":"Voy a posponer la reunión hasta mañana.","example_en":"I will put off the meeting until tomorrow.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Soportar","english_text":"Put up with","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to tolerate or endure something or someone","main_translations_es":["aguantar","tolerar","soportar"],"collocations":["put up with the noise","can''t put up with his attitude","put up with the heat"],"example_sentence":"I can''t put up with the constant noise.","example_es":"No puedo soportar el ruido constante.","example_en":"I can''t put up with the constant noise.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Descartar","english_text":"Rule out","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To eliminate or exclude something as a possibility.","main_translations_es":["Excluir","Eliminar","Desestimar"],"collocations":["rule out the possibility","rule out a diagnosis","rule out any chance","rule out the hypothesis"],"example_sentence":"Doctors must rule out other causes before confirming the diagnosis.","example_es":"Los médicos deben descartar otras causas antes de confirmar el diagnóstico.","example_en":"Doctors must rule out other causes before confirming the diagnosis.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Toparse con","english_text":"Run into","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To meet or encounter someone or something unexpectedly.","main_translations_es":["Encontrarse con","Tropezar con","Chocar con"],"collocations":["run into trouble","run into an old friend","run into a problem","run into obstacles"],"example_sentence":"I ran into my old friend at the supermarket.","example_es":"Me topé con mi viejo amigo en el supermercado.","example_en":"I ran into my old friend at the supermarket.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Reservar","english_text":"Set aside","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To reserve something for later use or a specific purpose.","main_translations_es":["Apartar","Guardar","Hacer una reserva"],"collocations":["set aside money","set aside time","set aside differences","set aside for later"],"example_sentence":"I will set aside time to study.","example_es":"Voy a reservar tiempo para estudiar.","example_en":"I will set aside time to study.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Montar","english_text":"Set up","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to arrange or establish something, such as equipment, a system, or an event.","main_translations_es":["Instalar","Armar","Configurar"],"collocations":["set up a meeting","set up the equipment","set up shop","set up a system"],"example_sentence":"Let''s set up the tent before it starts raining.","example_es":"Vamos a montar la carpa antes de que empiece a llover.","example_en":"Let''s set up the tent before it starts raining.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Aclarar","english_text":"Sort out","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To organize, resolve, or clarify something.","main_translations_es":["Explicar","Despejar","Precisar"],"collocations":["sort out the problem","sort out the details","sort out the mess","sort out the paperwork"],"example_sentence":"I need to sort out the project details before the meeting.","example_es":"Necesito aclarar los detalles del proyecto antes de la reunión.","example_en":"I need to sort out the project details before the meeting.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Hablar con firmeza","english_text":"Speak up","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To speak louder or more assertively, especially to express an opinion.","main_translations_es":["hablar con autoridad","expresarse con firmeza","hablar con seguridad"],"collocations":["speak up for yourself","speak up against injustice","speak up in meetings"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to speak up when defending human rights.","example_es":"Es importante hablar con firmeza cuando se defienden los derechos humanos.","example_en":"It''s important to speak up when defending human rights.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Dimitir","english_text":"Step down","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To resign from a position or office.","main_translations_es":["Renunciar","Abandonar el cargo","Dejar el puesto"],"collocations":["step down from","step down as","step down voluntarily","step down after"],"example_sentence":"The president announced that he will step down after the scandal.","example_es":"El presidente anunció que va a dimitir después del escándalo.","example_en":"The president announced that he will step down after the scandal.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Parecerse a","english_text":"Take after","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to resemble or be similar to someone, especially a family member","main_translations_es":["Asemejarse a","Se parecer a","Tener el parecido de"],"collocations":["take after his father","take after his mother","take after his brother","take after the family"],"example_sentence":"María takes after her mother.","example_es":"María se parece a su madre.","example_en":"María takes after her mother.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Asumir","english_text":"Take on","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To accept responsibility for something or to assume a task or role.","main_translations_es":["Aceptar","Encargar","Adoptar"],"collocations":["take on a challenge","take on responsibilities","take on a new role","take on board"],"example_sentence":"He decided to take on the responsibility of the project.","example_es":"Decidió asumir la responsabilidad del proyecto.","example_en":"He decided to take on the responsibility of the project.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Tomar el control","english_text":"Take over","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to assume control or responsibility for something","main_translations_es":["Asumir el control","Hacerse cargo","Dominar"],"collocations":["take over the company","take over the reins","take over from","take over the project"],"example_sentence":"The new CEO decided to take over the company.","example_es":"El nuevo CEO decidió tomar el control de la empresa.","example_en":"The new CEO decided to take over the company.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Pensarlo detenidamente","english_text":"Think over","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to consider something carefully","main_translations_es":["Reflexionar sobre ello","Considerarlo con cuidado","Meditar al respecto"],"collocations":["think it over","think over the proposal","think over the decision","think over the options"],"example_sentence":"Before making a decision, it''s important to think it over.","example_es":"Antes de tomar una decisión, es importante pensarlo detenidamente.","example_en":"Before making a decision, it''s important to think it over.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Rechazar","english_text":"Turn down","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To reject or refuse something.","main_translations_es":["Rehusar","Negar","Declinar"],"collocations":["turn down the volume","turn down the offer","turn down a request","turn down the lights"],"example_sentence":"He decided to turn down the job offer.","example_es":"Decidió rechazar la oferta de trabajo.","example_en":"He decided to turn down the job offer.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Resultar","english_text":"Turn out","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to have a particular result or outcome","main_translations_es":["acabar","salir","concluir"],"collocations":["turn out to be","turn out well","turn out for the best","turn out the lights"],"example_sentence":"The exam turned out to be easier than I expected.","example_es":"El examen resultó más fácil de lo que esperaba.","example_en":"The exam turned out to be easier than I expected.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Salirse bien","english_text":"Work out","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to succeed or have a favorable outcome","main_translations_es":["Salir bien","Resultar bien","Ir bien"],"collocations":["work out at the gym","work out the details","work out a solution","work out a plan"],"example_sentence":"In the end, everything worked out.","example_es":"Al final, todo se salió bien.","example_en":"In the end, everything worked out.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Retirarse","english_text":"Back out","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to withdraw from an agreement, plan, or commitment","main_translations_es":["Echarse atrás","Desistir","Recuarse"],"collocations":["back out of a deal","back out of a commitment","back out at the last minute"],"example_sentence":"He decided to back out of the project before it was too late.","example_es":"Decidió retirarse del proyecto antes de que fuera demasiado tarde.","example_en":"He decided to back out of the project before it was too late.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Romper con","english_text":"Break off","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb (phrasal verb)","definition_en":"To end a relationship with someone.","main_translations_es":["Terminar con","Poner fin a","Separarse de"],"collocations":["break off a relationship","break off negotiations","break off a conversation","break off the engagement"],"example_sentence":"He decided to break off his relationship with his girlfriend after three years.","example_es":"Decidió romper con su novia después de tres años.","example_en":"He decided to break off his relationship with his girlfriend after three years.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Abrirse paso","english_text":"Break through","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"phrasal verb","definition_en":"To succeed in overcoming an obstacle or to make a way forward.","main_translations_es":["Abrir camino","Hacer hueco","Forzar la entrada"],"collocations":["break through the barrier","break through the market","break through to the audience","break through the noise"],"example_sentence":"The pioneers had to break through the jungle.","example_es":"Los pioneros tuvieron que abrirse paso en la selva.","example_en":"The pioneers had to break through the jungle.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Interrumpir","english_text":"Cut in","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To interrupt someone while they are speaking.","main_translations_es":["interrumpir","intervenir","intercalar"],"collocations":["cut in line","cut in on","cut in the conversation","cut in while"],"example_sentence":"You shouldn''t cut in when someone is speaking.","example_es":"No deberías interrumpir cuando alguien está hablando.","example_en":"You shouldn''t cut in when someone is speaking.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Agotar","english_text":"Use up","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To consume something completely until none remains.","main_translations_es":["exhaustar","consumir","desgastar"],"collocations":["use up the resources","use up all the water","use up your time","use up the budget"],"example_sentence":"The fire managed to use up all the water supply in the area.","example_es":"El incendio logró agotar todo el suministro de agua de la zona.","example_en":"The fire managed to use up all the water supply in the area.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Terminar en","english_text":"End up","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to finally reach a particular place, condition, or result, often unexpectedly","main_translations_es":["acabar en","quedar en","finalizar en"],"collocations":["end up with","end up doing","end up in","end up somewhere"],"example_sentence":"If you don''t study, you could end up on the street.","example_es":"Si no estudias, podrías terminar en la calle.","example_en":"If you don''t study, you could end up on the street.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Dar con","english_text":"Find out","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To discover or learn something.","main_translations_es":["Encontrar","Toparse con","Descubrir"],"collocations":["find out the truth","find out more","find out what happened"],"example_sentence":"After searching for hours, I finally found out the solution to the problem.","example_es":"Después de buscar durante horas, finalmente di con la solución al problema.","example_en":"After searching for hours, I finally found out the solution to the problem.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Irse apagando","english_text":"Fade away","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To gradually disappear or lose intensity.","main_translations_es":["Desvanecerse","Ir perdiendo intensidad","Desaparecer poco a poco"],"collocations":["fade away slowly","fade away over time","fade away into the distance","fade away completely"],"example_sentence":"Over time, the lantern''s light began to fade away.","example_es":"Con el tiempo, la luz del farol se fue apagando.","example_en":"Over time, the lantern''s light began to fade away.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Aplastar","english_text":"Crack down on","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to take strict or severe measures against something or someone","main_translations_es":["machacar","triturar","aplastar"],"collocations":["crack down on crime","crack down on corruption","crack down on tax evasion","crack down on illegal immigration"],"example_sentence":"The government decided to crack down on tax evasion.","example_es":"El gobierno decidió aplastar la evasión fiscal.","example_en":"The government decided to crack down on tax evasion.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Rechazar de plano","english_text":"Brush off","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb (phrasal verb)","definition_en":"To dismiss or reject something or someone in a casual or indifferent manner.","main_translations_es":["Desestimar","Descartar","Rechazar rotundamente"],"collocations":["brush off criticism","brush off a comment","brush off the suggestion"],"example_sentence":"When they proposed the idea to him, he brushed it off.","example_es":"Cuando le propusieron la idea, la rechazó de plano.","example_en":"When they proposed the idea to him, he brushed it off.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Acompañar","english_text":"Go along with","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to agree with or support something or someone","main_translations_es":["acompañar","ir con","seguir"],"collocations":["go along with the plan","go along with the decision","go along with the idea","go along with the crowd"],"example_sentence":"He decided to go along with his brother on the hike.","example_es":"Decidió acompañar a su hermano en la caminata.","example_en":"He decided to go along with his brother on the hike.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Tolerar","english_text":"Put up with","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to tolerate or endure something or someone","main_translations_es":["soportar","aguantar","sufrir"],"collocations":["can''t put up with","put up with the noise","put up with his behavior"],"example_sentence":"I can''t put up with the constant construction noise.","example_es":"No puedo tolerar el ruido constante de la construcción.","example_en":"I can''t put up with the constant construction noise.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Intervenir","english_text":"Step in","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To intervene or become involved in a situation.","main_translations_es":["Intervenir","Interceder","Meterse"],"collocations":["step in to help","step in and take over","step in at the last minute","step in for someone"],"example_sentence":"The doctor had to step in quickly to save the patient.","example_es":"El médico tuvo que intervenir rápidamente para salvar al paciente.","example_en":"The doctor had to step in quickly to save the patient.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Retirarse gradualmente","english_text":"Phase out","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To gradually stop using or providing something.","main_translations_es":["Eliminar gradualmente","Descontinuar","Ir reduciendo"],"collocations":["phase out the program","phase out subsidies","phase out gradually","phase out over time"],"example_sentence":"The company decided to phase out its mobile phone market.","example_es":"La empresa decidió retirarse gradualmente del mercado de teléfonos móviles.","example_en":"The company decided to phase out its mobile phone market.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Introducir gradualmente","english_text":"Phase in","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To introduce something gradually or in stages.","main_translations_es":["Implementar de forma gradual","Ir incorporando poco a poco","Introducir paulatinamente"],"collocations":["phase in gradually","phase in over time","phase in the new system","phase in the changes"],"example_sentence":"The company decided to phase in the new software to avoid problems.","example_es":"La empresa decidió introducir gradualmente el nuevo software para evitar problemas.","example_en":"The company decided to phase in the new software to avoid problems.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Fallar","english_text":"Break down","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to cause something to collapse, fail, or separate into its component parts.","main_translations_es":["Equivocarse","Fallarse","Desacertar"],"collocations":["break down the problem","break down into steps","break down barriers","break down in tears"],"example_sentence":"The car started to break down and stopped in the middle of the road.","example_es":"El coche empezó a fallar y se detuvo en medio de la carretera.","example_en":"The car started to break down and stopped in the middle of the road.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Separarse","english_text":"Break up","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To end a romantic relationship.","main_translations_es":["Divorciarse","Romper","Terminar"],"collocations":["break up with","break up a fight","break up the band","break up the meeting"],"example_sentence":"After five years together, they decided to break up.","example_es":"Después de cinco años de relación, decidieron separarse.","example_en":"After five years together, they decided to break up.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Calmarse","english_text":"Calm down","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to become or cause someone to become less agitated or upset","main_translations_es":["tranquilizarse","relajarse"],"collocations":["Calm down and think","Calm down, please","Calm down, it''s not a big deal"],"example_sentence":"After the argument, John decided to calm down and take a deep breath.","example_es":"Después de la discusión, Juan decidió calmarse y respirar profundamente.","example_en":"After the argument, John decided to calm down and take a deep breath.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Cancelar","english_text":"Call off","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To cancel or stop something that was planned.","main_translations_es":["Cancelar","Anular","Suspender"],"collocations":["call off the meeting","call off the search","call off the wedding","call off the strike"],"example_sentence":"We decided to call off the party.","example_es":"Decidimos cancelar la fiesta.","example_en":"We decided to call off the party.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Seguir adelante con","english_text":"Carry on","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to continue doing something","main_translations_es":["Continuar con","Proseguir con","Avanzar con"],"collocations":["carry on with","carry on doing","carry on as usual","carry on regardless"],"example_sentence":"He decided to carry on with the project despite the obstacles.","example_es":"Decidió seguir adelante con el proyecto a pesar de los obstáculos.","example_en":"He decided to carry on with the project despite the obstacles.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Alcanzar","english_text":"Catch up","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to reach the same level or position as someone or something after falling behind","main_translations_es":["Lograr","Conseguir","Ponerse al día"],"collocations":["catch up on","catch up with","catch up to","catch up later"],"example_sentence":"I need to catch up with my classmates so I don''t fall behind.","example_es":"Necesito alcanzar a mis compañeros de clase para no quedarme atrás.","example_en":"I need to catch up with my classmates so I don''t fall behind.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Comprobar","english_text":"Check out","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to examine or look at something, or to borrow it from a library","main_translations_es":["verificar","confirmar","corroborar"],"collocations":["check out the new store","check out a book","check out of a hotel","check out the website"],"example_sentence":"I will check out the train schedule before leaving.","example_es":"Voy a comprobar el horario del tren antes de salir.","example_en":"I will check out the train schedule before leaving.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Contar con","english_text":"Count on","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to rely on someone or something","main_translations_es":["Depender de","Confiar en","Apoyarse en"],"collocations":["count on me","count on someone","count on it","you can count on"],"example_sentence":"You can count on my help to finish the project.","example_es":"Puedes contar con mi ayuda para terminar el proyecto.","example_en":"You can count on my help to finish the project.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Interrumpir abruptamente","english_text":"Cut off","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To stop or interrupt something abruptly.","main_translations_es":["Cortar de golpe","Interrumpir bruscamente","Cortar abruptamente"],"collocations":["cut off the power","cut off communication","cut off at the source","cut off from"],"example_sentence":"The host decided to cut off the interview abruptly when the guest became nervous.","example_es":"El presentador decidió interrumpir abruptamente la entrevista cuando el invitado se puso nervioso.","example_en":"The host decided to cut off the interview abruptly when the guest became nervous.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Lidiar con","english_text":"Deal with","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To address, manage, or handle a problem, situation, or person.","main_translations_es":["Enfrentarse a","Tratar con","Abordar"],"collocations":["deal with a problem","deal with customers","deal with the situation","deal with stress"],"example_sentence":"I have to deal with many problems at work.","example_es":"Tengo que lidiar con muchos problemas en el trabajo.","example_en":"I have to deal with many problems at work.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Acabar con","english_text":"Do without","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To manage or survive without something.","main_translations_es":["Eliminar","Poner fin a","Deshacerse de"],"collocations":["can''t do without","do without sugar","do without help"],"example_sentence":"I''m going to do without sugar.","example_es":"Voy a acabar con el azúcar.","example_en":"I''m going to do without sugar.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Abandonar","english_text":"Drop out","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To quit a school, program, or activity before completing it.","main_translations_es":["Dejar","Renunciar","Desistir"],"collocations":["drop out of school","drop out of college","drop out of the race"],"example_sentence":"He decided to drop out of college after the first semester.","example_es":"Decidió abandonar la universidad después del primer semestre.","example_en":"He decided to drop out of college after the first semester.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Comerse todo","english_text":"Eat up","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to consume something completely, especially to finish eating it","main_translations_es":["comer todo","devorarlo todo","tragarse todo"],"collocations":["eat up the leftovers","eat up the competition","eat up the information"],"example_sentence":"I''m going to eat up the whole cake.","example_es":"Voy a comerme todo el pastel.","example_en":"I''m going to eat up the whole cake.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Explicar","english_text":"Explain away","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To dismiss or rationalize something as unimportant or untrue by offering an explanation that reduces its significance.","main_translations_es":["Aclarar","Desglosar","Ilustrar"],"collocations":["explain away the mistake","explain away the scandal","can''t explain away the evidence","explain away the problem"],"example_sentence":"He tried to explain away his mistake as if it were nothing.","example_es":"Trató de explicar su error como si no fuera gran cosa.","example_en":"He tried to explain away his mistake as if it were nothing.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Llenarse","english_text":"Fill up","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To cause something to become full or to become full oneself.","main_translations_es":["llenarse","completarse","colmarse"],"collocations":["fill up the tank","fill up on food","fill up the glass","fill up quickly"],"example_sentence":"The glass filled up with water.","example_es":"El vaso se llenó de agua.","example_en":"The glass filled up with water.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Encajar","english_text":"Fit in","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to be accepted as part of a group or environment","main_translations_es":["Ajustar","Adaptarse","Encajar"],"collocations":["fit in with","fit in at","fit in nicely"],"example_sentence":"I had a hard time fitting in with the new work team.","example_es":"Me costó mucho encajar en el nuevo equipo de trabajo.","example_en":"I had a hard time fitting in with the new work team.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Seguir adelante a pesar de","english_text":"Get on with","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb (phrasal verb)","definition_en":"to continue doing something despite obstacles or difficulties","main_translations_es":["Continuar a pesar de","Seguir adelante pese a","Prosseguir a pesar de"],"collocations":["get on with it","get on with your life","get on with the work","get on with the project"],"example_sentence":"We must get on with the project despite the setbacks.","example_es":"Debemos seguir adelante a pesar de los contratiempos.","example_en":"We must get on with the project despite the setbacks.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Bajarse de","english_text":"Get off","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To descend from or leave a vehicle, platform, or other surface.","main_translations_es":["Descender de","Salir de","Desmontarse de"],"collocations":["get off the bus","get off work","get off my back","get off the ground"],"example_sentence":"I got off the bus just in time.","example_es":"Me bajé del autobús justo a tiempo.","example_en":"I got off the bus just in time.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Subirse a","english_text":"Get on","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To board or mount something, such as a vehicle or animal.","main_translations_es":["Montarse en","Subir a","Entrar en"],"collocations":["get on the bus","get on board","get on with","get on the train"],"example_sentence":"I''m going to get on the bus before it leaves.","example_es":"Voy a subirme al autobús antes de que salga.","example_en":"I''m going to get on the bus before it leaves.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Volver","english_text":"Go back","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To return to a previous place or condition.","main_translations_es":["Regresar","Retornar","Volver atrás"],"collocations":["go back to the drawing board","go back home","go back in time"],"example_sentence":"I need to go back home before the storm.","example_es":"Necesito volver a casa antes de la tormenta.","example_en":"I need to go back home before the storm.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Salir","english_text":"Go out","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To leave a place and go outside.","main_translations_es":["Ir afuera","Salir de casa","Ir fuera"],"collocations":["go out for dinner","go out with friends","go out on a date"],"example_sentence":"We are going to go out after dinner.","example_es":"Vamos a salir después de la cena.","example_en":"We are going to go out after dinner.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Acelerarse","english_text":"Hurry up","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"A command telling someone to act more quickly.","main_translations_es":["Apurarse","Darse prisa","Acelerar"],"collocations":["Hurry up and wait","Hurry up, we''re late","Hurry up already"],"example_sentence":"You have to hurry up if you don''t want to miss the train.","example_es":"Debes acelerarte si no quieres perder el tren.","example_en":"You have to hurry up if you don''t want to miss the train.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Posponer hasta más tarde","english_text":"Hold off","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To delay or postpone something.","main_translations_es":["Aplazar","Dejar para después","Postergar"],"collocations":["hold off on","hold off until","hold off for a while"],"example_sentence":"We decided to hold off the meeting until later.","example_es":"Decidimos posponer la reunión hasta más tarde.","example_en":"We decided to hold off the meeting until later.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Permanecer despierto","english_text":"Keep up","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To continue doing something or maintain a certain level or pace.","main_translations_es":["Mantenerse despierto","No dormirse","Estar despierto"],"collocations":["keep up with","keep up the pace","keep up the good work","keep up the momentum"],"example_sentence":"I need to keep up to finish the project.","example_es":"Necesito permanecer despierto para terminar el proyecto.","example_en":"I need to keep up to finish the project.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Irse sin pagar","english_text":"Make off","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb (phrasal verb)","definition_en":"To leave hurriedly, especially after stealing something.","main_translations_es":["Escaparse sin pagar","Huir sin pagar","Irse sin abonar"],"collocations":["make off with","make off after","make off quickly"],"example_sentence":"The customers decided to make off without paying the restaurant bill.","example_es":"Los clientes decidieron irse sin pagar la cuenta del restaurante.","example_en":"The customers decided to make off without paying the restaurant bill.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Inventar","english_text":"Make up","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To create something false or fictitious, such as a story, excuse, or invention.","main_translations_es":["Crear","Fabricar","Idear"],"collocations":["make up a story","make up the bed","make up for","make up with"],"example_sentence":"She decided to make up an excuse to be late.","example_es":"Ella decidió inventar una excusa para llegar tarde.","example_en":"She decided to make up an excuse to be late.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Pasar por encima de","english_text":"Move past","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To go beyond or ignore something.","main_translations_es":["Superar","Dejar atrás","Pasar más allá de"],"collocations":["move past the obstacle","move past the issue","move past the pain","move past the past"],"example_sentence":"You can''t move past the rules of the game.","example_es":"No puedes pasar por encima de las reglas del juego.","example_en":"You can''t move past the rules of the game.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Mencionar casualmente","english_text":"Pass on","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to give or transmit something to someone else","main_translations_es":["Mencionar de pasada","Aludir casualmente","Hacer una mención casual"],"collocations":["pass on the message","pass on the information","pass on a tradition","pass on to the next generation"],"example_sentence":"He passed on that the meeting had been cancelled.","example_es":"Mencionó casualmente que la reunión se había cancelado.","example_en":"He passed on that the meeting had been cancelled.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Recoger","english_text":"Pick up","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To lift something from a surface or to collect it.","main_translations_es":["Alcanzar","Levantar","Recoger"],"collocations":["pick up the phone","pick up where you left off","pick up the tab","pick up a habit"],"example_sentence":"I will pick up the package from the office.","example_es":"Voy a recoger el paquete de la oficina.","example_en":"I will pick up the package from the office.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Señalar con precisión","english_text":"Pin down","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To identify or locate something precisely, often by determining its exact nature or details.","main_translations_es":["Precisar","Detallar con exactitud","Ubicar con precisión"],"collocations":["pin down the details","pin down the location","pin down the meaning","pin down the cause"],"example_sentence":"The detective managed to pin down the location of the body.","example_es":"El detective logró señalar con precisión la ubicación del cuerpo.","example_en":"The detective managed to pin down the location of the body.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Presentar formalmente","english_text":"Put forward","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to propose or suggest something for consideration","main_translations_es":["exponer formalmente","proponer formalmente","someter formalmente"],"collocations":["put forward a proposal","put forward an idea","put forward a suggestion","put forward a theory"],"example_sentence":"The lawyer put forward the evidence to the jury.","example_es":"El abogado presentó formalmente la evidencia al jurado.","example_en":"The lawyer put forward the evidence to the jury.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Encender","english_text":"Put on","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To dress oneself in something, or to cause something to be worn.","main_translations_es":["prender","activar","encender"],"collocations":["put on a coat","put on makeup","put on a show","put on weight"],"example_sentence":"I''m going to put on the heating because it''s cold.","example_es":"Voy a encender la calefacción porque hace frío.","example_en":"I''m going to put on the heating because it''s cold.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Apagar","english_text":"Put out","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To extinguish a fire, light, or similar source.","main_translations_es":["Extinguir","Desactivar","Cerrar"],"collocations":["put out a fire","put out the lights","put out a cigarette","put out a call"],"example_sentence":"Put out the candle before you leave.","example_es":"Apaga la vela antes de irte.","example_en":"Put out the candle before you leave.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Expulsar","english_text":"Throw out","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To discard or eject something.","main_translations_es":["Echar","Despedir","Eliminar"],"collocations":["throw out the trash","throw out a suggestion","throw out the window"],"example_sentence":"The guard had to throw out the thief from the building.","example_es":"El guardia tuvo que expulsar al ladrón del edificio.","example_en":"The guard had to throw out the thief from the building.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Resurgir","english_text":"Crop up","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb (phrasal)","definition_en":"to appear or occur unexpectedly","main_translations_es":["Aparecer","Reaparecer","Surgir de nuevo"],"collocations":["issues crop up","questions crop up","problems crop up","new ideas crop up"],"example_sentence":"Old problems can crop up after years.","example_es":"Los problemas antiguos pueden resurgir después de años.","example_en":"Old problems can crop up after years.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Darse cuenta de","english_text":"Cotton on","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to become aware of something","main_translations_es":["darse cuenta","percatarse de","notar"],"collocations":["cotton on to","cotton on quickly","cotton on to the fact","cotton on over time"],"example_sentence":"I cottoned on that I had left the door open.","example_es":"Me di cuenta de que había dejado la puerta abierta.","example_en":"I cottoned on that I had left the door open.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Enfrentarse a","english_text":"Face up to","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to confront or deal with something directly, especially a problem or difficulty.","main_translations_es":["Encarar","Hacerse cargo de","Confrontar"],"collocations":["face up to the reality","face up to the facts","face up to the consequences","face up to the problem"],"example_sentence":"I have to face up to my fears.","example_es":"Tengo que enfrentarme a mis miedos.","example_en":"I have to face up to my fears.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Tomar apuntes","english_text":"Jot down","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to write something quickly, especially brief notes.","main_translations_es":["Anotar","Escribir notas","Apuntar"],"collocations":["jot down notes","jot down a reminder","jot down ideas"],"example_sentence":"During the class, I like to jot down notes so I don''t forget anything.","example_es":"Durante la clase, me gusta tomar apuntes para no olvidar nada.","example_en":"During the class, I like to jot down notes so I don''t forget anything.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Reducirse a","english_text":"Boil down to","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To simplify something to its essential point or main idea.","main_translations_es":["Limitarse a","Resumirse a","Condensarse en"],"collocations":["It all boils down to","The problem boils down to","Everything boils down to","In the end, it boils down to"],"example_sentence":"The whole problem boils down to a matter of trust.","example_es":"Todo el problema se reduce a una cuestión de confianza.","example_en":"The whole problem boils down to a matter of trust.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Salir con una idea","english_text":"Dream up","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To imagine or invent something, especially an idea or plan.","main_translations_es":["Idear","Proponer una idea","Concebir una idea"],"collocations":["dream up a plan","dream up a story","dream up an excuse"],"example_sentence":"The scientist dreamed up a brilliant idea to solve the problem.","example_es":"El científico salió con una idea brillante para resolver el problema.","example_en":"The scientist dreamed up a brilliant idea to solve the problem.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Renunciar a","english_text":"Walk away from","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"phrasal verb","definition_en":"to leave or abandon something or someone","main_translations_es":["Abandonar","Dejar","Desistir de"],"collocations":["walk away from the problem","walk away from a relationship","walk away from danger"],"example_sentence":"He decided to walk away from his job after ten years.","example_es":"Decidió renunciar a su trabajo después de diez años.","example_en":"He decided to walk away from his job after ten years.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Asentarse","english_text":"Settle down","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to become comfortable and stable in a place or situation, often by establishing a residence or routine","main_translations_es":["instalarse","establecerse","posarse"],"collocations":["settle down and relax","settle down in a new city","settle down with a partner"],"example_sentence":"After moving to the new city, he decided to settle down in a small apartment near the park.","example_es":"Después de mudarse a la nueva ciudad, decidió asentarse en un pequeño apartamento cerca del parque.","example_en":"After moving to the new city, he decided to settle down in a small apartment near the park.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Derivar de","english_text":"Stem from","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to originate or develop from something","main_translations_es":["Proceder de","Originarse en","Derivarse de"],"collocations":["stem from a problem","stem from the fact that","stem from years of experience","stem from underlying causes"],"example_sentence":"The problem stems from poor communication.","example_es":"El problema deriva de una mala comunicación.","example_en":"The problem stems from poor communication.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Asumir el mando","english_text":"Step up","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to assume a higher level of responsibility or authority","main_translations_es":["Tomar el control","Asumir la dirección","Encabezar"],"collocations":["step up to the plate","step up your game","step up and take charge","step up the pace"],"example_sentence":"When the captain fell ill, he had to step up and take command of the ship.","example_es":"Cuando el capitán cayó enfermo, tuvo que asumir el mando del barco.","example_en":"When the captain fell ill, he had to step up and take command of the ship.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Suprimir gradualmente","english_text":"Weed out","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To gradually remove or eliminate unwanted or undesirable items or people.","main_translations_es":["Eliminar poco a poco","Deshacerse gradualmente","Ir eliminando"],"collocations":["weed out the weak","weed out candidates","weed out problems","weed out unnecessary items"],"example_sentence":"The company decided to weed out unnecessary positions.","example_es":"La empresa decidió suprimir gradualmente los puestos de trabajo innecesarios.","example_en":"The company decided to weed out unnecessary positions.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Desmenuzar","english_text":"Break down into","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"to separate something into smaller parts or components","main_translations_es":["desmenuzar","desglosar","descomponer"],"collocations":["break down into pieces","break down into steps","break down into components","break down into categories"],"example_sentence":"Break down the information into smaller parts to understand it better.","example_es":"Desmenuzar la información en partes más pequeñas ayuda a comprenderla mejor.","example_en":"Break down the information into smaller parts to understand it better.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Superar con esfuerzo","english_text":"Pull through","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to survive or recover from a difficult situation","main_translations_es":["Salir adelante con esfuerzo","Superar con dificultad","Lograrlo con esfuerzo"],"collocations":["pull through a crisis","pull through the tough times","pull through with help"],"example_sentence":"With a lot of effort, we managed to pull through the economic crisis.","example_es":"Con mucho trabajo, logramos superar con esfuerzo la crisis económica.","example_en":"With a lot of effort, we managed to pull through the economic crisis.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No presentarse","english_text":"Back out of","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to withdraw from a commitment or fail to follow through with a plan","main_translations_es":["ausentarse","no acudir","no comparecer"],"collocations":["back out of a deal","back out of a commitment","back out of an agreement","back out of a promise"],"example_sentence":"I backed out of the meeting because I was feeling sick.","example_es":"No me presenté a la reunión porque me sentía enfermo.","example_en":"I backed out of the meeting because I was feeling sick.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Tachar","english_text":"Cross out","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To draw a line through text or a mark to indicate it should be deleted or ignored.","main_translations_es":["rayar","borrar","tachar"],"collocations":["cross out a mistake","cross out the word","cross out the line","cross out the name"],"example_sentence":"Please cross out the mistakes in the document.","example_es":"Por favor, tachar los errores en el documento.","example_en":"Please cross out the mistakes in the document.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Ir acompañado de","english_text":"Go together with","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"to accompany someone or something","main_translations_es":["Ir con","Ir acompañado de","Ir en compañía de"],"collocations":["go together with friends","go together with a purpose","go together with the team","go together with the plan"],"example_sentence":"I go together with my dog to the park.","example_es":"Voy al parque acompañado de mi perro.","example_en":"I go together with my dog to the park.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Recaer en","english_text":"Fall back on","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to rely again on something or someone for support or help","main_translations_es":["caer de nuevo en","volver a incurrir en","incurrir de nuevo en"],"collocations":["fall back on savings","fall back on experience","fall back on a plan","fall back on your instincts"],"example_sentence":"When I don''t know what to do, I always fall back on my old habits.","example_es":"Cuando no sé qué hacer, siempre recaigo en mis viejos hábitos.","example_en":"When I don''t know what to do, I always fall back on my old habits.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Insistir en","english_text":"Press ahead with","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To continue doing something with determination despite obstacles.","main_translations_es":["Persistir en","Mantenerse firme en","Continuar con"],"collocations":["press ahead with the plan","press ahead with the project","press ahead with reforms","press ahead with negotiations"],"example_sentence":"He pressed ahead with finishing the project on time.","example_es":"Insistió en terminar el proyecto a tiempo.","example_en":"He pressed ahead with finishing the project on time.","mnemonic_en":null}]'::jsonb) as x(
  spanish_text text, english_text text, section_name text, part_of_speech text, definition_en text,
  main_translations_es jsonb, collocations jsonb, example_sentence text, example_es text, example_en text, mnemonic_en text
)
where not exists (
  select 1 from public.cards c2
  where c2.deck_id = dk.id
    and lower(c2.spanish_text) = lower(x.spanish_text)
    and lower(c2.english_text) = lower(x.english_text)
);

-- english-discussion-and-debate (105 cards)
insert into public.decks (slug, title, description, language_from, language_to)
values ('english-discussion-and-debate', 'Discussion and Debate', 'Expressions for giving opinions, agreeing, disagreeing, clarifying, and structuring advanced spoken English.', 'es', 'en')
on conflict (slug) do nothing;

insert into public.cards (deck_id, spanish_text, english_text, is_enabled, generation_phase, generation_metadata, section_name, part_of_speech, definition_en, main_translations_es, collocations, example_sentence, example_es, example_en, mnemonic_en)
select dk.id, x.spanish_text, x.english_text, true, 'refined', '{}'::jsonb, x.section_name, x.part_of_speech, x.definition_en,
       coalesce(x.main_translations_es, '[]'::jsonb), coalesce(x.collocations, '[]'::jsonb), x.example_sentence, x.example_es, x.example_en, x.mnemonic_en
from (select id from public.decks where slug = 'english-discussion-and-debate') dk
cross join jsonb_to_recordset('[{"spanish_text":"Estoy totalmente de acuerdo","english_text":"I completely agree","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating total agreement with something.","main_translations_es":["Estoy completamente de acuerdo","Coincido plenamente","Estoy totalmente de acuerdo"],"collocations":["I completely agree with you","I completely agree that","I completely agree, indeed"],"example_sentence":"I completely agree with your proposal.","example_es":"Estoy totalmente de acuerdo con tu propuesta.","example_en":"I completely agree with your proposal.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Estoy de acuerdo hasta cierto punto","english_text":"I agree to some extent","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"To express partial agreement with something.","main_translations_es":["Estoy de acuerdo en parte","Estoy parcialmente de acuerdo","Coincido hasta cierto punto"],"collocations":["I agree to some extent with you","I agree to some extent, however","I agree to some extent on that point"],"example_sentence":"I agree to some extent with what you say.","example_es":"Estoy de acuerdo hasta cierto punto con lo que dices.","example_en":"I agree to some extent with what you say.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No lo veo así","english_text":"I do not see it that way","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that the speaker does not share that perspective.","main_translations_es":["No lo percibo de esa manera","No lo entiendo así","No lo concibo así"],"collocations":["I do not see it that way, but...","I do not see it that way at all","I do not see it that way, however"],"example_sentence":"I don''t see it that way, but I understand your point.","example_es":"No lo veo así, pero entiendo tu punto.","example_en":"I don''t see it that way, but I understand your point.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No estoy del todo convencido","english_text":"I am not entirely convinced","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that someone is not fully persuaded.","main_translations_es":["No estoy completamente convencido","No me convence del todo","No estoy totalmente seguro"],"collocations":["I am not entirely convinced that…","I''m not entirely convinced by…","We are not entirely convinced about…"],"example_sentence":"I am not entirely convinced that this is the best solution.","example_es":"No estoy del todo convencido de que esa sea la mejor solución.","example_en":"I am not entirely convinced that this is the best solution.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Discrepo","english_text":"I beg to differ","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite way of saying that you disagree.","main_translations_es":["No estoy de acuerdo","Me opongo","Diferir"],"collocations":["I beg to differ, but...","I beg to differ with you","I beg to differ on that point"],"example_sentence":"I beg to differ with his opinion on the matter.","example_es":"Discrepo con su opinión sobre el tema.","example_en":"I beg to differ with his opinion on the matter.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Eso no refleja toda la realidad","english_text":"That does not tell the whole story","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means that something fails to convey the complete truth or full situation.","main_translations_es":["Eso no muestra toda la realidad","Eso no cuenta toda la historia","Eso no refleja todo el panorama"],"collocations":["The numbers do not tell the whole story","One example does not tell the whole story","Statistics often do not tell the whole story","A single incident does not tell the whole story"],"example_sentence":"That does not tell the whole story about the situation.","example_es":"Eso no refleja toda la realidad de la situación.","example_en":"That does not tell the whole story about the situation.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Desde mi punto de vista","english_text":"From my perspective","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to indicate that something is being considered according to one''s own point of view.","main_translations_es":["A mi parecer","En mi opinión","Según mi punto de vista"],"collocations":["From my perspective, ...","From my perspective, the situation is clear","From my perspective, we should proceed","From my perspective, the results are promising"],"example_sentence":"From my perspective, education should be free for everyone.","example_es":"Desde mi punto de vista, la educación debería ser gratuita para todos.","example_en":"From my perspective, education should be free for everyone.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Tal como yo lo veo","english_text":"As I see it","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to introduce one''s personal opinion or perspective.","main_translations_es":["Tal como lo percibo","Según mi punto de vista","A mi modo de ver"],"collocations":["as I see it, ...","as I see it, the problem is","as I see it, we should","as I see it, that''s the case"],"example_sentence":"As I see it, the situation is unsustainable.","example_es":"Tal como yo lo veo, la situación es insostenible.","example_en":"As I see it, the situation is unsustainable.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Por lo que entiendo","english_text":"As far as I understand","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"idiomatic expression","definition_en":"It indicates that the speaker is stating something based on their current understanding.","main_translations_es":["Según entiendo","Hasta donde entiendo","En lo que entiendo"],"collocations":["as far as I understand it","as far as I understand, ...","as far as I understand the situation","as far as I understand from the report"],"example_sentence":"As far as I understand, the project will be completed on time.","example_es":"Por lo que entiendo, el proyecto se completará a tiempo.","example_en":"As far as I understand, the project will be completed on time.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Hasta donde sé","english_text":"As far as I know","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means that the speaker is stating something based on their current knowledge, but may not be certain.","main_translations_es":["Hasta donde tengo entendido","Según lo que sé","Según mi conocimiento"],"collocations":["as far as I know, it''s true","as far as I know, there are no issues","as far as I know, that''s the case"],"example_sentence":"As far as I know, the meeting will be tomorrow at ten.","example_es":"Hasta donde sé, la reunión será mañana a las diez.","example_en":"As far as I know, the meeting will be tomorrow at ten.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Dicho esto","english_text":"That said","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to introduce a statement that qualifies or contrasts with what was previously said.","main_translations_es":["Con eso dicho","Eso dicho","Dicho lo anterior"],"collocations":["That said, we should proceed","That said, it''s not guaranteed","That said, I think","That said, the results are inconclusive"],"example_sentence":"That said, I think we should proceed with the original plan.","example_es":"Dicho esto, creo que deberíamos continuar con el plan original.","example_en":"That said, I think we should proceed with the original plan.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Al mismo tiempo","english_text":"At the same time","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Indicates that two or more events occur simultaneously.","main_translations_es":["Simultáneamente","A la vez","En simultáneo"],"collocations":["at the same time as","at the same time, however","at the same time, too"],"example_sentence":"At the same time, we decided to go to the beach and visit my grandparents.","example_es":"Al mismo tiempo, decidimos viajar a la playa y visitar a mis abuelos.","example_en":"At the same time, we decided to go to the beach and visit my grandparents.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sin restarle importancia","english_text":"Without downplaying","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"phrase","definition_en":"In a way that does not diminish or lessen the importance of something.","main_translations_es":["Sin minimizar","Sin restar importancia","Sin restarle relevancia"],"collocations":["without downplaying the risks","without downplaying the importance","without downplaying the facts","without downplaying the situation"],"example_sentence":"Without downplaying the minor issues, we must focus on the main solution.","example_es":"Sin restarle importancia a los problemas menores, debemos enfocarnos en la solución principal.","example_en":"Without downplaying the minor issues, we must focus on the main solution.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"En otras palabras","english_text":"In other words","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to restate something in a different way.","main_translations_es":["En otras palabras","Dicho de otra forma"],"collocations":["in other words, ...","to put it another way","that is"],"example_sentence":"In other words, the project is delayed.","example_es":"En otras palabras, el proyecto está retrasado.","example_en":"In other words, the project is delayed.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Dicho de otro modo","english_text":"Put differently","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to introduce a restatement of something in other words.","main_translations_es":["En otras palabras","De otra forma","Dicho de otra manera"],"collocations":["Put differently, ...","To put it differently","Put differently, however"],"example_sentence":"Put differently, the situation is unsustainable.","example_es":"Dicho de otro modo, la situación es insostenible.","example_en":"Put differently, the situation is unsustainable.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Para ser más preciso","english_text":"To be more precise","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to introduce a more exact statement or clarification.","main_translations_es":["Para ser más exacto","Con mayor precisión","En términos más precisos"],"collocations":["To be more precise, ...","To be more precise, the answer is ...","To be more precise, we should note that ..."],"example_sentence":"To be more precise, the project will be completed in three months.","example_es":"Para ser más preciso, el proyecto se completará en tres meses.","example_en":"To be more precise, the project will be completed in three months.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Permíteme reformularlo","english_text":"Let me rephrase that","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite way of saying that you will restate something using different words.","main_translations_es":["Déjame reformularlo","Permíteme decirlo de otra manera","Voy a expresarlo de nuevo"],"collocations":["Let me rephrase that for clarity","Let me rephrase that in simpler terms","Let me rephrase that to be sure","Let me rephrase that another way"],"example_sentence":"Let me rephrase that to make it clearer.","example_es":"Permíteme reformularlo para que sea más claro.","example_en":"Let me rephrase that to make it clearer.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Lo que intento decir es","english_text":"What I am trying to say is","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to introduce or clarify what the speaker intends to convey.","main_translations_es":["Lo que quiero decir es","Lo que pretendo decir es","Lo que intento expresar es"],"collocations":["What I am trying to say is that...","What I am trying to say is, in short,...","What I am trying to say is, basically,..."],"example_sentence":"What I am trying to say is that we need more time.","example_es":"Lo que intento decir es que necesitamos más tiempo.","example_en":"What I am trying to say is that we need more time.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Si lo analizamos","english_text":"If we break it down","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to introduce a detailed analysis or explanation of something.","main_translations_es":["Si lo desglosamos","Si lo examinamos","Si lo estudiamos"],"collocations":["If we break it down further","If we break it down step by step","If we break it down, we can see","If we break it down, the problem becomes clear"],"example_sentence":"If we break it down carefully, we will find the cause of the problem.","example_es":"Si lo analizamos detenidamente, encontraremos la causa del problema.","example_en":"If we break it down carefully, we will find the cause of the problem.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Ese es un buen punto","english_text":"That is a fair point","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement acknowledging that someone has made a valid or reasonable argument.","main_translations_es":["Eso es un punto válido","Ese es un buen argumento","Tienes un buen punto"],"collocations":["That''s a fair point, but...","Well, that''s a fair point.","I have to admit that''s a fair point.","You make a fair point."],"example_sentence":"That is a fair point, we should consider it before deciding.","example_es":"Ese es un buen punto, deberíamos considerarlo antes de decidir.","example_en":"That is a fair point, we should consider it before deciding.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Eso merece atención","english_text":"That is worth considering","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means something deserves attention or consideration.","main_translations_es":["Eso merece atención","Eso vale la pena","Eso merece ser considerado"],"collocations":["worth considering","worth a second look","worth taking into account"],"example_sentence":"That is worth considering, so we should review it.","example_es":"Eso merece atención, así que deberíamos revisarlo.","example_en":"That is worth considering, so we should review it.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No había pensado en eso","english_text":"I had not thought of that","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that one had not considered something before.","main_translations_es":["No lo había considerado","No lo había pensado","No se me había ocurrido"],"collocations":["I had not thought of that before","I had not thought of that possibility","I had not thought of that angle"],"example_sentence":"I hadn''t thought of that before you told me.","example_es":"No había pensado en eso antes de que me lo dijeras.","example_en":"I hadn''t thought of that before you told me.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sin embargo","english_text":"Having said that","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to introduce a statement that contrasts with or qualifies what was previously said.","main_translations_es":["No obstante","Aun así","Con todo"],"collocations":["Having said that, I think we should proceed.","Having said that, we need to consider the costs.","Having said that, it''s not a guarantee.","Having said that, let''s move on."],"example_sentence":"Having said that, the project was cancelled.","example_es":"Sin embargo, el proyecto fue cancelado.","example_en":"Having said that, the project was cancelled.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Aun así","english_text":"Even so","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"conjunctive adverb","definition_en":"Used to introduce a statement that contrasts with or qualifies what has just been said.","main_translations_es":["Sin embargo","No obstante","Aun así"],"collocations":["even so","even so, however","even so, nevertheless"],"example_sentence":"Even so, he decided to go to the concert despite the rain.","example_es":"Aun así, decidió ir al concierto a pesar de la lluvia.","example_en":"Even so, he decided to go to the concert despite the rain.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Pese a ello","english_text":"Despite that","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to indicate that something is true in spite of a previously mentioned fact.","main_translations_es":["Aun así","Sin embargo","No obstante"],"collocations":["Despite that, ...","Despite that, he continued","Despite that, the results were positive"],"example_sentence":"Despite that, he decided to continue with the project.","example_es":"Pese a ello, decidió continuar con el proyecto.","example_en":"Despite that, he decided to continue with the project.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No necesariamente","english_text":"Not necessarily","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to indicate that something is not always the case or not required.","main_translations_es":["No tiene que ser","No es obligatorio","No necesariamente"],"collocations":["not necessarily true","not necessarily the case","not necessarily required","not necessarily a problem"],"example_sentence":"You don''t necessarily have to work on weekends.","example_es":"No necesariamente tienes que trabajar los fines de semana.","example_en":"You don''t necessarily have to work on weekends.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No se sigue de eso","english_text":"That does not necessarily follow","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that a conclusion cannot be assumed from the given premise.","main_translations_es":["No se deduce de eso","No se infiere de eso","No se concluye a partir de eso"],"collocations":["does not necessarily follow","necessarily follow from","does not follow logically","does not necessarily follow that"],"example_sentence":"Just because you won the lottery, that does not necessarily follow that you''ll be happy.","example_es":"Solo porque ganaste la lotería, no se sigue de eso que serás feliz.","example_en":"Just because you won the lottery, that does not necessarily follow that you''ll be happy.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Eso depende","english_text":"That depends","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It indicates that the outcome or answer varies depending on certain conditions.","main_translations_es":["Depende","Depende de eso","Eso depende de"],"collocations":["That depends on…","It depends on the situation","That depends on the context","It depends"],"example_sentence":"That depends on the time you arrive.","example_es":"Eso depende de la hora en que llegues.","example_en":"That depends on the time you arrive.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Depende del contexto","english_text":"It depends on the context","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that the meaning or outcome varies according to the situation.","main_translations_es":["Depende de la situación","Según el contexto","Varía según el contexto"],"collocations":["It depends on the context","That depends on the context","It all depends on the context"],"example_sentence":"It depends on the context, but it is usually used in formal situations.","example_es":"Depende del contexto, pero generalmente se usa en situaciones formales.","example_en":"It depends on the context, but it is usually used in formal situations.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No es tan simple","english_text":"It is not that straightforward","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means that something is not as simple or clear as it might seem.","main_translations_es":["No es tan sencillo","No es tan fácil","No es tan claro"],"collocations":["It is not that straightforward to explain","It is not that straightforward to solve","It is not that straightforward in practice","It is not that straightforward for beginners"],"example_sentence":"It''s not that simple to solve this problem.","example_es":"No es tan simple resolver este problema.","example_en":"It''s not that simple to solve this problem.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Es una simplificación excesiva","english_text":"That is an oversimplification","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A statement that reduces a complex issue to overly simple terms.","main_translations_es":["Es una simplificación exagerada","Es una simplificación demasiado simple","Es una simplificación desmedida"],"collocations":["That''s an oversimplification of the issue","It''s an oversimplification of the problem","Such a view is an oversimplification","Calling it an oversimplification"],"example_sentence":"Saying that the problem will be solved in a week is an oversimplification.","example_es":"Decir que el problema se resolverá en una semana es una simplificación excesiva.","example_en":"Saying that the problem will be solved in a week is an oversimplification.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Podría interpretarse de otra manera","english_text":"It could be interpreted differently","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means that something may be understood in another way.","main_translations_es":["Podría entenderse de otra forma","Se podría interpretar de otra manera","Podría leerse de modo distinto"],"collocations":["This statement could be interpreted differently","The results could be interpreted differently","Such a comment could be interpreted differently","These findings could be interpreted differently"],"example_sentence":"It could be interpreted differently if we consider the context.","example_es":"Podría interpretarse de otra manera si consideramos el contexto.","example_en":"It could be interpreted differently if we consider the context.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Hay margen para debatir","english_text":"There is room for debate","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means that a topic can be discussed and different opinions are possible.","main_translations_es":["Hay espacio para debatir","Se puede debatir","Existe margen para debatir"],"collocations":["There is room for debate on this issue","It leaves room for debate","This point is open to debate","The matter remains open to debate"],"example_sentence":"In the meeting, there is room for debate about the proposed changes.","example_es":"En la reunión, hay margen para debatir los cambios propuestos.","example_en":"In the meeting, there is room for debate about the proposed changes.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Eso sigue siendo discutible","english_text":"That remains debatable","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means that the matter is still open to debate.","main_translations_es":["Eso sigue siendo debatible","Eso continúa siendo discutible","Eso aún es objeto de debate"],"collocations":["The issue remains debatable","His claim remains debatable","The outcome remains debatable"],"example_sentence":"Even after all this time, that remains debatable.","example_es":"Aunque ya pasó mucho tiempo, eso sigue siendo discutible.","example_en":"Even after all this time, that remains debatable.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Es una cuestión compleja","english_text":"It is a complex issue","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement that something is complicated or difficult.","main_translations_es":["Es un tema complejo","Se trata de un asunto complicado","Es una cuestión complicada"],"collocations":["a complex issue","address a complex issue","tackle a complex issue","the complex issue"],"example_sentence":"It is a complex issue.","example_es":"Es una cuestión compleja.","example_en":"It is a complex issue.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No hay una respuesta única","english_text":"There is no one-size-fits-all answer","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means that no single solution works for every situation.","main_translations_es":["No existe una única respuesta","No hay una solución única","No hay una respuesta universal"],"collocations":["There is no one-size-fits-all answer, so we must adapt","Because there is no one-size-fits-all answer, each case is different","There is no one-size-fits-all answer; tailor your strategy accordingly"],"example_sentence":"There is no one-size-fits-all answer to this problem.","example_es":"No hay una respuesta única a este problema.","example_en":"There is no one-size-fits-all answer to this problem.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Estoy a favor","english_text":"I am in favor of","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to state that you support or agree with something.","main_translations_es":["Apoyo","Estoy a favor de","Me inclino por"],"collocations":["I am in favor of the proposal","I am in favor of this plan","I am in favor of change"],"example_sentence":"I am in favor of the proposed law.","example_es":"Estoy a favor de la propuesta de ley.","example_en":"I am in favor of the proposed law.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Estoy en contra","english_text":"I am opposed to","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"It means that I am against something.","main_translations_es":["Me opongo a","Estoy en desacuerdo con","No estoy a favor de"],"collocations":["I am opposed to the new policy","I am opposed to violence","I am opposed to that idea"],"example_sentence":"I am opposed to the government''s decision.","example_es":"Estoy en contra de la decisión del gobierno.","example_en":"I am opposed to the government''s decision.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Valoro tu punto","english_text":"I appreciate your point","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite way of saying that you understand and value someone''s argument or opinion.","main_translations_es":["Aprecio tu punto","Valoro tu argumento","Reconozco tu punto"],"collocations":["I appreciate your point, but...","I appreciate your point of view","I really appreciate your point","I appreciate your point and will consider it"],"example_sentence":"I appreciate your point, but I think there''s another perspective.","example_es":"Valoro tu punto, pero creo que hay otra perspectiva.","example_en":"I appreciate your point, but I think there''s another perspective.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Entiendo de dónde vienes","english_text":"I see where you are coming from","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means that you understand someone''s perspective or reasoning.","main_translations_es":["Comprendo de dónde vienes","Entiendo tu punto de vista","Sé de dónde vienes"],"collocations":["I see where you''re coming from","I get your point","I understand your perspective","I see your point"],"example_sentence":"I see where you are coming from, so I will support your decision.","example_es":"Entiendo de dónde vienes, así que apoyaré tu decisión.","example_en":"I see where you are coming from, so I will support your decision.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Eso tiene sentido","english_text":"That makes sense","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to say that something is logical or understandable.","main_translations_es":["Tiene sentido","Eso tiene lógica","Eso tiene razón"],"collocations":["makes sense of","makes sense to","makes sense now","it makes sense"],"example_sentence":"That makes sense, so I''ll follow the plan.","example_es":"Eso tiene sentido, así que seguiré el plan.","example_en":"That makes sense, so I''ll follow the plan.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No estoy seguro de que eso sea exacto","english_text":"I am not sure that is accurate","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement expressing uncertainty about the accuracy of something.","main_translations_es":["No estoy seguro de que sea exacto","No tengo la certeza de que eso sea exacto","Dudo que eso sea exacto"],"collocations":["I''m not sure that''s accurate","I''m not sure if that''s accurate","I''m not sure about the accuracy"],"example_sentence":"I''m not sure that is accurate, but I think it''s close.","example_es":"No estoy seguro de que eso sea exacto, pero creo que está cerca.","example_en":"I''m not sure that is accurate, but I think it''s close.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Eso no parece convincente","english_text":"That does not sound convincing","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means that something is not perceived as believable or persuasive.","main_translations_es":["Eso no suena convincente","Eso no parece creíble","Eso no resulta convincente"],"collocations":["does not sound convincing","sounds unconvincing","fails to convince","lacks credibility"],"example_sentence":"That does not sound convincing, so I don''t believe it.","example_es":"Eso no parece convincente, así que no lo creo.","example_en":"That does not sound convincing, so I don''t believe it.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Me cuesta aceptar esa idea","english_text":"I struggle to accept that idea","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"To have difficulty accepting that idea.","main_translations_es":["Me cuesta aceptar esa idea","Me resulta difícil aceptar esa idea","Tengo problemas para aceptar esa idea"],"collocations":["I struggle to accept that idea","It''s hard to accept that idea","I find it difficult to accept that idea","I can''t seem to accept that idea"],"example_sentence":"I struggle to accept that idea, but I know it''s important.","example_es":"Me cuesta aceptar esa idea, pero sé que es importante.","example_en":"I struggle to accept that idea, but I know it''s important.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Podrías tener razón","english_text":"You may be right","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite way of saying that someone could be correct.","main_translations_es":["Quizás tengas razón","Puede que tengas razón","Tal vez tengas razón"],"collocations":["You may be right about that","You may be right, after all","You may be right, I guess"],"example_sentence":"You may be right, but I still want to try.","example_es":"Podrías tener razón, pero aún así quiero intentarlo.","example_en":"You may be right, but I still want to try.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Hay algo de verdad en eso","english_text":"There is some truth in that","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means that the statement contains a certain amount of truth.","main_translations_es":["Hay algo de verdad en eso","Hay algo de verdad en lo que dices","Hay algo de verdad en esa afirmación"],"collocations":["There''s some truth in that.","There''s some truth to that.","There''s some truth in what you said.","There''s some truth behind that claim."],"example_sentence":"There is some truth in that, although not everything is accurate.","example_es":"Hay algo de verdad en eso, aunque no todo es exacto.","example_en":"There is some truth in that, although not everything is accurate.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No descartaría esa posibilidad","english_text":"I would not rule that out","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that something is still considered possible.","main_translations_es":["No excluiría esa posibilidad","No descartaría esa opción","No lo descartaría"],"collocations":["I would not rule out the possibility","I would not rule out that option","I would not rule out a chance","I would not rule out the idea"],"example_sentence":"I would not rule that out, even though I''m still uncertain.","example_es":"No descartaría esa posibilidad, aunque todavía tengo dudas.","example_en":"I would not rule that out, even though I''m still uncertain.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Vale la pena analizarlo","english_text":"It is worth examining","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Something that should be looked at because it may be valuable or important.","main_translations_es":["Merece ser analizado","Vale la pena revisarlo","Conviene examinarlo"],"collocations":["It is worth examining further","It is worth examining the data","It is worth examining the evidence"],"example_sentence":"It is worth examining it before making a decision.","example_es":"Vale la pena analizarlo antes de tomar una decisión.","example_en":"It is worth examining it before making a decision.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No deberíamos apresurarnos","english_text":"We should not jump to conclusions","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means we ought not to form opinions before having all the facts.","main_translations_es":["No deberíamos precipitarse","No debemos apresurarnos","No hay que ir deprisa"],"collocations":["don''t jump to conclusions","avoid jumping to conclusions","stop jumping to conclusions"],"example_sentence":"We should not jump to conclusions before analyzing all the data.","example_es":"No deberíamos apresurarnos a sacar conclusiones sin analizar todos los datos.","example_en":"We should not jump to conclusions before analyzing all the data.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Conviene matizar","english_text":"We need to qualify that","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"To add a clarification or nuance to a statement.","main_translations_es":["Es conveniente matizar","Resulta necesario matizar","Conviene aclarar"],"collocations":["to qualify that statement","to qualify that claim","to qualify that point","to qualify that observation"],"example_sentence":"We need to qualify that the report does not include all the relevant data.","example_es":"Conviene matizar que el informe no incluye todos los datos relevantes.","example_en":"We need to qualify that the report does not include all the relevant data.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Eso requiere evidencia","english_text":"That requires evidence","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It states that something needs proof or supporting evidence.","main_translations_es":["Eso necesita pruebas","Eso demanda evidencia","Eso requiere pruebas"],"collocations":["requires evidence","requires solid evidence","requires concrete evidence","requires supporting evidence"],"example_sentence":"That requires evidence before making a decision.","example_es":"Eso requiere evidencia antes de tomar una decisión.","example_en":"That requires evidence before making a decision.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"¿En qué te basas?","english_text":"What are you basing that on?","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A question asking for the basis or justification of something.","main_translations_es":["¿En qué te basas?","¿Sobre qué te apoyas?","¿Qué fundamento tiene?"],"collocations":["basing decisions on","basing your argument on","basing the plan on"],"example_sentence":"What are you basing that on when you say the project will fail?","example_es":"¿En qué te basas para decir que el proyecto fracasará?","example_en":"What are you basing that on when you say the project will fail?","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"¿Podrías desarrollar esa idea?","english_text":"Could you elaborate on that?","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A polite request for more detail about something previously mentioned.","main_translations_es":["¿Podrías ampliar esa idea?","¿Podrías profundizar en esa idea?","¿Podrías detallar esa idea?"],"collocations":["Could you elaborate on that, please?","Could you elaborate on that a bit more?","Could you elaborate on that further?"],"example_sentence":"Could you elaborate on that?","example_es":"¿Podrías desarrollar esa idea?","example_en":"Could you elaborate on that?","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"¿Podrías dar un ejemplo?","english_text":"Could you give an example?","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A polite request asking someone to provide an example.","main_translations_es":["¿Puedes dar un ejemplo?","¿Me podrías dar un ejemplo?","¿Podrías proporcionar un ejemplo?"],"collocations":["Could you give an example of that?","Could you give an example, please?","Could you give an example to illustrate?"],"example_sentence":"Could you give an example of how to use this word?","example_es":"¿Podrías dar un ejemplo de cómo se usa esta palabra?","example_en":"Could you give an example of how to use this word?","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"¿Qué quieres decir exactamente?","english_text":"What exactly do you mean?","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"question","definition_en":"A request for clarification about the precise meaning of something.","main_translations_es":["¿Qué quieres decir con eso?","¿A qué te refieres exactamente?","¿Qué significa exactamente?"],"collocations":["What exactly do you mean by that?","I’m not sure what exactly you mean.","Could you explain what exactly you mean?","Tell me what exactly you mean."],"example_sentence":"When he explained his plan, I asked, \"What exactly do you mean?\"","example_es":"Cuando me explicó su plan, le pregunté: ¿Qué quieres decir exactamente?","example_en":"When he explained his plan, I asked, \"What exactly do you mean?\"","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Aclaremos un punto","english_text":"Let us clarify one point","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite phrase used to introduce an explanation of a specific matter.","main_translations_es":["Aclararemos un punto","Aclarar un punto","Vamos a aclarar un punto"],"collocations":["let us clarify","clarify one point","to clarify a point","let me clarify"],"example_sentence":"Let''s clarify one point before we continue.","example_es":"Aclaremos un punto antes de continuar.","example_en":"Let''s clarify one point before we continue.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Quiero dejar algo claro","english_text":"I want to make something clear","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement used to indicate that the speaker intends to clarify a point.","main_translations_es":["Quiero aclarar algo","Quisiera dejar algo claro","Deseo dejar algo claro"],"collocations":["to make something clear","to make it clear","to be clear","to clarify"],"example_sentence":"I want to make something clear: I will not do it again.","example_es":"Quiero dejar algo claro: no volveré a hacerlo.","example_en":"I want to make something clear: I will not do it again.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No pretendo decir que","english_text":"I am not suggesting that","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to state that the speaker is not implying or proposing something.","main_translations_es":["No quiero decir que","No intento afirmar que","No pretendo afirmar que"],"collocations":["I am not suggesting that you should quit","I am not suggesting that it''s a bad idea","I am not suggesting that we go now"],"example_sentence":"I am not suggesting that everyone agrees, but I think it''s important.","example_es":"No pretendo decir que todos estén de acuerdo, pero creo que es importante.","example_en":"I am not suggesting that everyone agrees, but I think it''s important.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No debería interpretarse como","english_text":"It should not be interpreted as","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"Indicates that something must not be understood in a particular way.","main_translations_es":["No debe interpretarse como","No se debe interpretar como","No ha de interpretarse como"],"collocations":["It should not be interpreted as a criticism","It should not be interpreted as a guarantee","It should not be interpreted as a promise","It should not be interpreted as an endorsement"],"example_sentence":"It should not be interpreted as disrespect, but as constructive criticism.","example_es":"No debería interpretarse como una falta de respeto, sino como una crítica constructiva.","example_en":"It should not be interpreted as disrespect, but as constructive criticism.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"En términos generales","english_text":"Broadly speaking","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to introduce a general statement or overview of a topic.","main_translations_es":["En general","De manera general","En líneas generales"],"collocations":["Broadly speaking, the market is expanding","Broadly speaking, we can conclude","Broadly speaking, the results are positive"],"example_sentence":"Broadly speaking, the country''s economy has improved this year.","example_es":"En términos generales, la economía del país ha mejorado este año.","example_en":"Broadly speaking, the country''s economy has improved this year.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"En términos concretos","english_text":"In practical terms","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to introduce a concrete or realistic explanation of something.","main_translations_es":["En términos prácticos","En la práctica","De manera concreta"],"collocations":["In practical terms, this means...","In practical terms, we can see...","In practical terms, the cost is...","In practical terms, it''s easier..."],"example_sentence":"In practical terms, the project will cost ten thousand euros.","example_es":"En términos concretos, el proyecto costará diez mil euros.","example_en":"In practical terms, the project will cost ten thousand euros.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"A primera vista","english_text":"At first glance","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to indicate an initial impression based on a quick look.","main_translations_es":["A primera vista","A simple vista","A primera impresión"],"collocations":["At first glance, it seems...","At first glance, the data suggests...","At first glance, the results appear..."],"example_sentence":"At first glance, the painting seems simple, but upon closer inspection it reveals many details.","example_es":"A primera vista, el cuadro parece sencillo, pero al observarlo más de cerca revela muchos detalles.","example_en":"At first glance, the painting seems simple, but upon closer inspection it reveals many details.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"A largo plazo","english_text":"In the long term","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"adverbial phrase","definition_en":"Refers to a period of time far in the future.","main_translations_es":["A largo plazo","A futuro","En el futuro"],"collocations":["in the long term","over the long term","in the long run","for the long term"],"example_sentence":"In the long term, investing in renewable energy will generate economic benefits.","example_es":"A largo plazo, la inversión en energía renovable generará beneficios económicos.","example_en":"In the long term, investing in renewable energy will generate economic benefits.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"A corto plazo","english_text":"In the short term","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"During a brief period of time; referring to the near future.","main_translations_es":["A corto plazo","En el corto plazo","A corto término"],"collocations":["in the short term","short‑term plan","short‑term benefits","short‑term outlook"],"example_sentence":"In the short term, the company plans to increase its sales by 10%.","example_es":"A corto plazo, la empresa planea aumentar sus ventas en un 10%.","example_en":"In the short term, the company plans to increase its sales by 10%.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"En el peor de los casos","english_text":"In the worst-case scenario","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"idiomatic expression","definition_en":"It refers to the most unfavorable possible outcome.","main_translations_es":["En el peor de los casos","En el peor escenario","En el caso más desfavorable"],"collocations":["In the worst-case scenario, we could lose everything.","In the worst-case scenario, the project will be delayed.","In the worst-case scenario, the system may crash."],"example_sentence":"In the worst-case scenario, we will have to cancel the event.","example_es":"En el peor de los casos, tendremos que cancelar el evento.","example_en":"In the worst-case scenario, we will have to cancel the event.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"En el mejor de los casos","english_text":"In the best-case scenario","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"idiomatic expression","definition_en":"Used to describe the most favorable possible outcome.","main_translations_es":["En el mejor de los casos","En el caso más favorable","En el escenario óptimo"],"collocations":["In the best-case scenario, we succeed","In the best-case scenario, costs are lower","In the best-case scenario, the project finishes early"],"example_sentence":"In the best-case scenario, the project will be completed in three months.","example_es":"En el mejor de los casos, el proyecto se completará en tres meses.","example_en":"In the best-case scenario, the project will be completed in three months.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"En última instancia","english_text":"Ultimately","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"In the end, after everything else has been considered.","main_translations_es":["Finalmente","A fin de cuentas","En definitiva"],"collocations":["Ultimately, we decided to go ahead","Ultimately, it comes down to cost","Ultimately, the results speak for themselves"],"example_sentence":"Ultimately, we will decide whether the project continues.","example_es":"En última instancia, decidiremos si el proyecto continúa.","example_en":"Ultimately, we will decide whether the project continues.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Al fin y al cabo","english_text":"After all","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to emphasize a conclusion that follows from what has been said or to point out that something is true when all factors are considered.","main_translations_es":["En definitiva","Al final","A fin de cuentas"],"collocations":["after all is said and done","after all, it''s worth trying","after all, we are human"],"example_sentence":"After all, we all make mistakes.","example_es":"Al fin y al cabo, todos cometemos errores.","example_en":"After all, we all make mistakes.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"En resumen","english_text":"To sum up","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to introduce a brief summary of what has been said.","main_translations_es":["En síntesis","En pocas palabras","Resumiendo"],"collocations":["To sum up, ...","To sum up the findings","To sum up the report"],"example_sentence":"To sum up, the project was a success.","example_es":"En resumen, el proyecto fue un éxito.","example_en":"To sum up, the project was a success.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Para resumir","english_text":"To summarize","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give a brief statement of the main points.","main_translations_es":["En resumen","Resumiendo","Para concluir"],"collocations":["To summarize, ...","To summarize the findings","To summarize briefly","To summarize the main points"],"example_sentence":"To summarize, the project was a success.","example_es":"Para resumir, el proyecto fue un éxito.","example_en":"To summarize, the project was a success.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"En esencia","english_text":"Essentially","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"In a basic or fundamental way; basically.","main_translations_es":["Básicamente","En resumen","En esencia"],"collocations":["essentially the same","essentially a matter of","essentially, …"],"example_sentence":"Essentially, the project aims to improve air quality in the city.","example_es":"En esencia, el proyecto busca mejorar la calidad del aire en la ciudad.","example_en":"Essentially, the project aims to improve air quality in the city.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"En pocas palabras","english_text":"In a nutshell","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Briefly; in a concise summary.","main_translations_es":["En resumen","En síntesis","Resumiendo"],"collocations":["to put it in a nutshell","in a nutshell, ...","the story in a nutshell","the whole thing in a nutshell"],"example_sentence":"In a nutshell, the project was a success.","example_es":"En pocas palabras, el proyecto fue un éxito.","example_en":"In a nutshell, the project was a success.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"La cuestión central es","english_text":"The key issue is","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to introduce the most important problem or topic.","main_translations_es":["El tema principal es","El asunto central es","Lo fundamental es"],"collocations":["The key issue is whether…","The key issue is how…","The key issue is that…","The key issue is the lack of…"],"example_sentence":"The key issue is how to improve education in rural areas.","example_es":"La cuestión central es cómo mejorar la educación en las zonas rurales.","example_en":"The key issue is how to improve education in rural areas.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Eso nos lleva a","english_text":"That brings us to","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to transition to the next point or topic.","main_translations_es":["Esto nos lleva a","Esto nos conduce a","Esto nos dirige a"],"collocations":["That brings us to the next point","That brings us to a conclusion","That brings us to the final step","That brings us to the heart of the matter"],"example_sentence":"That brings us to the conclusion that we must act now.","example_es":"Eso nos lleva a la conclusión de que debemos actuar ahora.","example_en":"That brings us to the conclusion that we must act now.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Hay otro ángulo","english_text":"There is another angle to consider","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means that there is an additional perspective or aspect that should be taken into account.","main_translations_es":["Existe otro ángulo","Hay otra perspectiva","Se puede observar otro ángulo"],"collocations":["We should remember there is another angle to consider","It''s important to note there is another angle to consider","Before concluding, consider that there is another angle to consider"],"example_sentence":"There is another angle we must consider.","example_es":"Hay otro ángulo que debemos considerar.","example_en":"There is another angle we must consider.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No perdamos de vista que","english_text":"Let us not lose sight of the fact that","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase urging someone to keep an important point in mind.","main_translations_es":["No olvidemos que","No perdamos de vista el hecho de que","Mantengamos presente que"],"collocations":["let us not lose sight of the fact that","we must not lose sight of the fact that","do not lose sight of the fact that","it is crucial not to lose sight of the fact that"],"example_sentence":"Let us not lose sight of the fact that health is the most important thing.","example_es":"No perdamos de vista que la salud es lo más importante.","example_en":"Let us not lose sight of the fact that health is the most important thing.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Conviene recordar que","english_text":"It is worth remembering that","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"idiomatic expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to indicate that something should be kept in mind.","main_translations_es":["Vale la pena recordar que","Hay que recordar que","Es importante recordar que"],"collocations":["It is worth remembering that...","It is worth remembering that you should...","It is worth remembering that the rules apply"],"example_sentence":"It is worth remembering that punctuality is a sign of respect.","example_es":"Conviene recordar que la puntualidad es una muestra de respeto.","example_en":"It is worth remembering that punctuality is a sign of respect.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Si somos sinceros","english_text":"If we are being honest","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to introduce an honest statement.","main_translations_es":["Si hablamos con franqueza","Si somos francos","Si lo decimos con sinceridad"],"collocations":["If we are being honest, ...","If we are being honest, I think...","If we are being honest, the truth is...","If we are being honest, we must admit..."],"example_sentence":"If we are being honest, we should admit our mistakes.","example_es":"Si somos sinceros, deberíamos admitir nuestros errores.","example_en":"If we are being honest, we should admit our mistakes.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"En rigor","english_text":"Strictly speaking","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to indicate that a statement is true only when considered in a precise or technical sense.","main_translations_es":["En realidad","En términos estrictos","En sentido estricto"],"collocations":["strictly speaking, ...","strictly speaking, the answer is","strictly speaking, it''s not","strictly speaking, we should"],"example_sentence":"Strictly speaking, the project is not finished.","example_es":"En rigor, el proyecto no está terminado.","example_en":"Strictly speaking, the project is not finished.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"A decir verdad","english_text":"To be honest","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to indicate that the speaker is about to speak truthfully or sincerely.","main_translations_es":["A decir verdad","Para ser sincero","Siendo honesto"],"collocations":["to be honest, I think","to be honest with you","to be honest about","to be honest, it''s"],"example_sentence":"To be honest, I didn''t like the movie.","example_es":"A decir verdad, no me gustó la película.","example_en":"To be honest, I didn''t like the movie.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No me malinterpretes","english_text":"Do not get me wrong","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A request for the listener to avoid misunderstanding what the speaker means.","main_translations_es":["No me tomes a mal","No me saques conclusiones equivocadas","No me malinterpretes"],"collocations":["Do not get me wrong, but…","Do not get me wrong, I’m not…","Do not get me wrong, I love it","Do not get me wrong, it’s just…"],"example_sentence":"Don''t get me wrong, but I think you should reconsider your decision.","example_es":"No me malinterpretes, pero creo que deberías reconsiderar tu decisión.","example_en":"Don''t get me wrong, but I think you should reconsider your decision.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Sin ánimo de ofender","english_text":"No offense intended","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement used to indicate that the speaker does not mean to offend anyone.","main_translations_es":["Sin intención de ofender","No es mi intención ofender","No pretendo ofender"],"collocations":["no offense, but…","no offense taken","no offense, just saying","no offense, I’m being honest"],"example_sentence":"No offense intended, I think you should reconsider your decision.","example_es":"Sin ánimo de ofender, creo que deberías reconsiderar tu decisión.","example_en":"No offense intended, I think you should reconsider your decision.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Con el debido respeto","english_text":"With all due respect","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite phrase used to preface a statement that may be critical or contrary, showing respect while disagreeing.","main_translations_es":["Con todo respeto","Con el mayor respeto","Con el debido respeto"],"collocations":["With all due respect, I must disagree","With all due respect, that''s not accurate","With all due respect, here''s my opinion"],"example_sentence":"With all due respect, I think your proposal is not feasible.","example_es":"Con el debido respeto, creo que su propuesta no es viable.","example_en":"With all due respect, I think your proposal is not feasible.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Permíteme disentir","english_text":"Allow me to disagree","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite way of saying that you do not share someone''s opinion.","main_translations_es":["Déjame disentir","Permíteme estar en desacuerdo","Permíteme discrepar"],"collocations":["Allow me to disagree, but...","Allow me to disagree with you","Allow me to disagree for a moment","Allow me to disagree on this point"],"example_sentence":"Allow me to disagree, but I think that solution won''t work.","example_es":"Permíteme disentir, pero creo que esa solución no funcionará.","example_en":"Allow me to disagree, but I think that solution won''t work.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Lo plantearía de otra forma","english_text":"I would frame it differently","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"To present something using different wording or perspective.","main_translations_es":["Lo expresaría de otra manera","Lo diría de otro modo","Lo presentaría de forma distinta"],"collocations":["to frame it differently","frame it in a different way","reframe the issue","look at it from another angle"],"example_sentence":"If I had to explain the problem, I would frame it differently.","example_es":"Si tuviera que explicar el problema, lo plantearía de otra forma.","example_en":"If I had to explain the problem, I would frame it differently.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Eso cambia las cosas","english_text":"That changes the picture","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means that the situation or understanding is altered.","main_translations_es":["Eso altera la situación","Eso modifica las cosas","Eso cambia el panorama"],"collocations":["That changes the picture completely","That changes the picture significantly","That changes the picture dramatically"],"example_sentence":"That changes the picture, so we’ll have to rethink the plan.","example_es":"Eso cambia las cosas, así que tendremos que replantear el plan.","example_en":"That changes the picture, so we’ll have to rethink the plan.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Eso fortalece tu argumento","english_text":"That strengthens your argument","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"statement","definition_en":"It indicates that something makes your argument more convincing.","main_translations_es":["Eso refuerza tu argumento","Eso consolida tu argumento","Eso respalda tu argumento"],"collocations":["This evidence strengthens your argument","A strong example strengthens your argument","Such data strengthens your argument","That point strengthens your argument"],"example_sentence":"When you present concrete data, that strengthens your argument.","example_es":"Cuando presentas datos concretos, eso fortalece tu argumento.","example_en":"When you present concrete data, that strengthens your argument.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Eso debilita la postura","english_text":"That weakens the case","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means that something reduces the strength or persuasiveness of an argument.","main_translations_es":["Eso debilita la posición","Eso debilita el argumento","Eso debilita la postura"],"collocations":["This evidence weakens the case","Such arguments weaken the case","It weakens the case considerably","These facts weaken the case"],"example_sentence":"If the witness lies, that weakens the case.","example_es":"Si el testigo miente, eso debilita la postura.","example_en":"If the witness lies, that weakens the case.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Eso respalda la idea","english_text":"That supports the claim","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"sentence","definition_en":"It indicates that something provides evidence for or backs up a particular claim.","main_translations_es":["Eso respalda la idea","Eso sustenta la idea","Eso avala la idea"],"collocations":["as evidence that supports the claim","which supports the claim","to support the claim"],"example_sentence":"That supports the claim that climate change is real.","example_es":"Eso respalda la idea de que el cambio climático es real.","example_en":"That supports the claim that climate change is real.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Eso entra en conflicto con","english_text":"That conflicts with","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To be in disagreement or incompatibility with something.","main_translations_es":["Eso está en conflicto con","Eso contradice a","Eso choca con"],"collocations":["conflicts with","is at odds with","clashes with","contradicts"],"example_sentence":"That conflicts with the company''s policies.","example_es":"Eso entra en conflicto con las normas de la empresa.","example_en":"That conflicts with the company''s policies.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Parece contradictorio","english_text":"That appears contradictory","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means that something seems to be in conflict or inconsistent.","main_translations_es":["Resulta contradictorio","Se muestra contradictorio","Parece contradictorio"],"collocations":["That appears contradictory to the earlier statement","That appears contradictory at first glance","That appears contradictory, but further analysis clarifies","That appears contradictory in context"],"example_sentence":"That appears contradictory to claim that the climate is changing while the scientific evidence is denied.","example_es":"Parece contradictorio afirmar que el clima está cambiando mientras se niega la evidencia científica.","example_en":"That appears contradictory to claim that the climate is changing while the scientific evidence is denied.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No estoy cerrado a esa idea","english_text":"I am open to that idea","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating willingness to consider or accept a suggestion.","main_translations_es":["Estoy abierto a esa idea","No me opongo a esa idea","No rechazo esa idea"],"collocations":["open to suggestions","open to new ideas","open to possibilities","open to feedback"],"example_sentence":"I''m not closed to that idea, so we can consider it.","example_es":"No estoy cerrado a esa idea, así que podemos considerarla.","example_en":"I''m not closed to that idea, so we can consider it.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Estoy dispuesto a reconsiderarlo","english_text":"I am willing to reconsider","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating readiness to think about something again.","main_translations_es":["Estoy dispuesto a reconsiderar","Podría reconsiderarlo","Estoy abierto a reconsiderar"],"collocations":["I am willing to reconsider the proposal","I am willing to reconsider my decision","I am willing to reconsider the terms","I am willing to reconsider the offer"],"example_sentence":"I am willing to reconsider it if you present me with new arguments.","example_es":"Estoy dispuesto a reconsiderarlo si me presentas nuevos argumentos.","example_en":"I am willing to reconsider it if you present me with new arguments.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Eso es discutible","english_text":"That is open to debate","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that something is arguable or not settled.","main_translations_es":["Eso es debatible","Eso es cuestionable","Eso es discutible"],"collocations":["open to debate","subject to debate","open for debate"],"example_sentence":"The argument you presented is open to debate, so we won''t accept it without further discussion.","example_es":"El argumento que presentaste es discutible, así que no lo aceptaremos sin más.","example_en":"The argument you presented is open to debate, so we won''t accept it without further discussion.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No me convence del todo","english_text":"I am not fully persuaded","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that one is not completely convinced.","main_translations_es":["No me convence del todo","No me convence completamente","No me convence por completo"],"collocations":["I am not fully persuaded by his argument","I am not fully persuaded yet","I am not fully persuaded about the decision"],"example_sentence":"I am not fully persuaded by the theory presented at the conference.","example_es":"No me convence del todo la teoría que presentaron en la conferencia.","example_en":"I am not fully persuaded by the theory presented at the conference.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Tu argumento es sólido","english_text":"Your argument is sound","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that someone''s reasoning or evidence is solid and reliable.","main_translations_es":["Tu razonamiento es sólido","Tu argumento es firme","Tu argumento está bien fundamentado"],"collocations":["Your argument is sound, so we can move forward","If your argument is sound, the conclusion follows","A sound argument is persuasive","Your argument is sound and convincing"],"example_sentence":"Your argument is sound, so we should consider it seriously.","example_es":"Tu argumento es sólido, así que debemos considerarlo seriamente.","example_en":"Your argument is sound, so we should consider it seriously.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Eso carece de fundamento","english_text":"That lacks foundation","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means something is unsupported or has no basis.","main_translations_es":["No tiene fundamento","Carece de base","No está fundamentado"],"collocations":["lacks a solid foundation","lacks any foundation","lacks foundational support"],"example_sentence":"The accusation that he stole the bank is unfounded; that lacks foundation.","example_es":"La acusación de que él robó el banco es infundada; eso carece de fundamento.","example_en":"The accusation that he stole the bank is unfounded; that lacks foundation.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No es una conclusión inevitable","english_text":"That is not an inevitable conclusion","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement asserting that a particular outcome is not unavoidable.","main_translations_es":["No es una conclusión inevitable","No constituye una conclusión inevitable","No resulta una conclusión inevitable"],"collocations":["However, that is not an inevitable conclusion.","Thus, that is not an inevitable conclusion.","In any case, that is not an inevitable conclusion."],"example_sentence":"That is not an inevitable conclusion, but we should keep investigating.","example_es":"No es una conclusión inevitable, pero debemos seguir investigando.","example_en":"That is not an inevitable conclusion, but we should keep investigating.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Puede haber una explicación alternativa","english_text":"There may be an alternative explanation","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It suggests that an alternative explanation could exist.","main_translations_es":["Podría existir una explicación alternativa","Existe la posibilidad de una explicación alternativa","Hay una posible explicación alternativa"],"collocations":["Consider that there may be an alternative explanation","It''s possible that there may be an alternative explanation","We should keep in mind there may be an alternative explanation"],"example_sentence":"There may be an alternative explanation for this phenomenon.","example_es":"Puede haber una explicación alternativa para este fenómeno.","example_en":"There may be an alternative explanation for this phenomenon.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Lo dejaría en que","english_text":"I would put it this way","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to introduce a particular way of stating something.","main_translations_es":["Lo expresaría así","Lo diría de esta manera","Lo plantearía así"],"collocations":["I would put it this way: ...","Let me put it this way","I would put it this way, if you will"],"example_sentence":"I would put it this way: that everything turns out well.","example_es":"Lo dejaría en que todo salga bien.","example_en":"I would put it this way: that everything turns out well.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Estoy de acuerdo en lo esencial","english_text":"I agree in principle","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"To express agreement with the general idea or underlying principle, without committing to all specifics.","main_translations_es":["Coincido en lo esencial","Estoy de acuerdo en lo fundamental","Comparto la idea esencial"],"collocations":["I agree in principle, but...","We can move forward; I agree in principle","I agree in principle with your suggestion"],"example_sentence":"I agree in principle, although some details may vary.","example_es":"Estoy de acuerdo en lo esencial, aunque algunos detalles pueden variar.","example_en":"I agree in principle, although some details may vary.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"No estoy en desacuerdo con eso","english_text":"I do not disagree with that","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that the speaker does not oppose or contradict that.","main_translations_es":["Estoy de acuerdo con eso","Comparto esa opinión","No difiero con eso"],"collocations":["I do not disagree with that point","I do not disagree with that view","I do not disagree with that statement","I do not disagree with that assessment"],"example_sentence":"I do not disagree with that, but I think we could improve the proposal.","example_es":"No estoy en desacuerdo con eso, pero creo que podríamos mejorar la propuesta.","example_en":"I do not disagree with that, but I think we could improve the proposal.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Eso es justamente el problema","english_text":"That is precisely the problem","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that something exactly constitutes the issue.","main_translations_es":["Ese es precisamente el problema","Eso es exactamente el problema","Ese es el problema justo"],"collocations":["That''s precisely the problem","And that''s precisely the problem","Which is precisely the problem","That''s precisely the problem we face"],"example_sentence":"That is precisely the problem we have been discussing.","example_es":"Eso es justamente el problema que hemos estado discutiendo.","example_en":"That is precisely the problem we have been discussing.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Eso va al corazón del asunto","english_text":"That goes to the heart of the matter","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means that something addresses the most important or central point of an issue.","main_translations_es":["Eso llega al meollo del asunto","Eso toca el punto clave","Eso va al fondo del asunto"],"collocations":["gets to the heart of the matter","goes straight to the heart of the matter","hits the heart of the matter","addresses the heart of the matter"],"example_sentence":"That goes to the heart of the matter and allows us to find a solution.","example_es":"Eso va al corazón del asunto y nos permite encontrar una solución.","example_en":"That goes to the heart of the matter and allows us to find a solution.","mnemonic_en":null},{"spanish_text":"Da que pensar","english_text":"That gives food for thought","section_name":"Discussion and Debate","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means something that provokes reflection or consideration.","main_translations_es":["Da que reflexionar","Invita a la reflexión","Hace pensar"],"collocations":["gives me food for thought","provides food for thought","offers food for thought"],"example_sentence":"His argument gives food for thought.","example_es":"Su argumento da que pensar.","example_en":"His argument gives food for thought.","mnemonic_en":null}]'::jsonb) as x(
  spanish_text text, english_text text, section_name text, part_of_speech text, definition_en text,
  main_translations_es jsonb, collocations jsonb, example_sentence text, example_es text, example_en text, mnemonic_en text
)
where not exists (
  select 1 from public.cards c2
  where c2.deck_id = dk.id
    and lower(c2.spanish_text) = lower(x.spanish_text)
    and lower(c2.english_text) = lower(x.english_text)
);

commit;
